e reminded me that there is fun in everything, and I brought many happy memories to me and my son.',''),(236,'The ability to play any Rockstar games I purchased on Steam has been stripped away just as it has for many other people due to the ridiculous social club requirement attached.Below is the support ticket.https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3103521022You have a single account (for a launcher!?), anything happens to it and Rockstar deems you not the owner despite obvious evidence, that’s it. Your games are now rendered unusable. The compromised account permanently tied to Steam with no option to unlink.The only option being to repurchase all Rockstar games once again somewhere else if you fancy playing them again (remind me why Rockstar have any incentive to adjust social clubs current implementation).In GTA 4’s instance, it didn’t even have social club when I purchased. Rockstar added it in an update in 2020 (The same update which also removed content from the game due to licence expiry). In what way does the EULA or any other measure give the right to REMOVE no longer licenced content from copies purchased previous?Say you own a film on DVD / BluRay, it has a wicked car chase scene. Later down the line, the movie company loses the licence from the car manufacturer of one of the cars in the scene. Can the movie company then come and take away your film and hand you another copy with the car removed from the chase scene?',''),(237,'Logging in is an absolute joke that makes all desire to play the game vanish.',''),(238,'When rockstar deletes your social club account and they cannot reimburse you with a functioning CD key. Don\'t bother wasting your time with rockstar support.',''),(239,'too many hackers and cheaters',''),(240,'Platforms announced for GTA6 and yet again, PC is being sidelined as an afterthought for later. PC players have brought in hundreds of millions for Rockstar in GTAV and yet they still, after all this time and countless m