 with my kids mother. We don\'t fight, or argue, or say hurtful things to each other. We are parents, and friends.I now have 3 kids. My third child is, wait for it, ALSO 4 YEARS OLD. The woman I am with was going through a very similar situation at the time of my own separation, and we just stumbled in to each others life unexpectedly. We have been in a relationship for a year now, and are very happy together.Moral of the story, you never know what life holds in store for you, and if I would have given up when all the odds were stacked against me, I wouldn\'t be where I am today. This silly little game helped me realize that. Thank you, ConcernedApe',''),(491,'good',''),(492,'very cute game and fun to play',''),(493,'Stardew Valley is probably the greatest indie game ever conceived!Firstly, I must admit that I was never into farming games. This game truly changed me. In my opinion, it is close to perfection, even closer after they added the co-op.Basically, you can experience a great story where you take the role of a character who inherits their deceased grandfather\'s farm. But the best part is, it\'s not only about farming. You have an amazing quest system, resource management, relationships, fighting, mining and fishing.When I started Stardew Valley, I created my farm based on my grandfather\'s farm. It even has our family\'s surname. My family owns orange orchards, chicken coops and a warehouse. In addition to this, my grandfather also used to run a small store of agricultural and animal supply products.Unfortunately, he has passed away peacefully a few weeks ago. Thanks to Stardew Valley, I will always have the opportunity to remind myself of him. For me, he was an amazing man, an amazing grandfather, an amazing father. May he rest in peace.Games like these are the ones that stay in your memory for your entire life!Thank you for reading.',''),(494,'Buy it for full price. The creator deserves it, because nothing truly compares to SDV. I own this game on Steam, 