ation message. Either way, this game is mostly unplayable if you wanna play with military expansion. The most I could do to enjoy this game with its unique features is to just be pacifist. How fun.Please don\'t buy this game. There\'s so many other ways for you to spend your money or enjoy the game without spending any money. Just watch Youtube videos instead.[NOTE] I will continue to edit my review from new patches if any changes occur.',''),(622,'Overpriced. Loads of bugs. Repetitive. arcade like mechanics. More of a button clicking game than a strategy game.',''),(623,'It sucks the hours away but makes me feel a big \"Eh, I didn\'t have any fun\".It\'s early access.Paradox changed the military and (African) colony systems. They are as not-fun as the last version. There are more bugs (I\'ve had a quarter of Africa stolen underneath me and I\'ve stolen a different quarter away, I don\'t know how or why, Colonial Administrations are broken).When you go to declare war, the game says \"The entire world may defend this country if you attack, or it might not\".Large countries will join overseas wars when they lack a navy to fight it.Assimilation events seem to forget you cannot assimilate people in their homeland but constantly fire for people in their homeland.The economic and political mechanics seem fine.But they seem more fit for a 21st century game than a 19th century one.Online players seem obsessed with making a mass-immigration, multicultural, open borders, coop-owned welfare state, with zero factory automation and an infinitely growing construction sector in a zombie economy.I\'d like to import cotton from India to return cloth that undercuts their market. Struggle to keep a country from collapsing during the Springtime of nations. Build a centralised, modernised nation out of an unregulated, untaxed kingdom. Destroy cottage economies. Discover how the Arab slave trade is still in my African colonies, that I cannot simply outlaw it, and that only my most ardent Christians care to do something about it. See the rise of pan-nationalism in Europe. Watch professional armies run over prestigious countries inside half a year, start a naval arms race, open conscription centres and then say \"It\'ll be over by Christmas\" before realising war has changed.But that isn\'t here.That\'s not the game.You\'re a tax-heavy, centrally planned economy from day 1. You can be a quirky atheist state by the 1850s, a technocratic feminist big-government welfare state by the 1890s. I clicked an event to guillotine my King just before a civil war fired and everyone went home chuffed to bits instead of having something bad happen like a revolution with a Napoleon or Stalin. I had to smother my land in farms because my dominions wouldn\'t feed themselves.Political groups and their law choices are lacking. Religious groups die off. University professors feel anachronistic as to be separate from the represented Upper and Middle classes. Factory owners just follow on from the University professors with no new reform desires. Factory workers have no place in the system - there\'s 1 factory related law for them, the rest is just \"I want to own the means of production, to be taxed greatly, to have universal welfare paid for by a non-existent small government, to compete with women in the workforce, we have achieved trve communism today comrade\", this feels even less internally consistent and period accurate than the other political groups.I don\'t understand war and I don\'t know if a WWI slog fest can naturally happen like in Victoria 2.',''),(624,'Front system sucks!! Lost an easy war because a majority of my troops just sat around confused. Would definitely wait another 3 war patches, not this one. Still same old Vicky',''),(625,'A week ago i was diagnosed with a terminal illness and the doctors have given me a year at best. I\'m so glad i was able to play this before i go. I don\'t know how many of you will see this: but I recommend you to play this game if you see it. Gameplay,atmosphere,graphics. everything is masterfully crafted. If you read thank you and good bye.',''),(626,'Just couldn\'t get into this one like I did with the first entry. This game was trying so hard to be different from the first, that it just ends up feeling like a *******  version of the first. It may float the boat of others, but It just didn\'t do it for me.',''),(627,'If you are looking for good coop game with friends. Look no further then this. Very nice game play mechanics but totally hate the unnecessarily complex puzzles. It sucked at launch but after so many updates its very good.',''),(628,'It sucks to write this, but this game feels like an overall downgrade to the first Dying Light. The parkour in particular is worse than it\'s predecessor. Specifically, parkour feels more floaty and cumbersome, and inputs (at least on keyboard+mouse) are glitchy.From an atmospheric standpoint, the game doesn\'t feel like it\'s been well thought out? It feels out of place that there\'s a mob of human bad guys casually standing 15 feet away from a large group of zombies and that the two groups never interact with each other - especially when the zombie group has special infected. It feels like they simply inserted \"enemies\" for the sake of enemy density/difficulty.One of the main points of the game is to be outside during the day, and to not go into indoor structures during that time as all the volatile infected and such inhabit them. However, volatile\'s will still occupy indoor places even when it\'s nighttime, thereby making loot and/or questing those areas difficult and/or impossible. This hurts the most early on when you have no items/skills.There\'s more loot to equip in this game like a chest piece, shoes, sleeves, etc, with stat bonuses to make your character better. The loot you find is tied to your characters power level, and the higher the power level the better quality the loot. The stat bonuses are basic, and overall the systems in place for loot and itemization feel tacked on.The voice acting is decent, and the developers tried having more meaningful dialogue/plot*. Sadly, it\'s overlooked by the overwhelming amount of time spent doing the things in the game that make you question why the things that were fun in the first game don\'t feel as good in the sequel.Get it when it\'s on sale I guess if you\'re a big fan of the first game.EDIT: Beat the game, the story takes a massive nose dive after a certain point, so the previous positive thing I had to say about this game now has an asterisk. Game may be better with coop, but seems to have the same coop limitations from the first game (can\'t coop last mission maybe?).',''),(629,'Last played: March 2022. Will update when I have played on a more recent version.I had enough fun with this game. But I had to force myself to finish the story. The combat was mostly unsatisfying, and the movement did not feel as good as I expected it for being the sequel to Dying Light, very often. I do recommend it, but be aware that it is not so much an improvement over Dying Light 1 as simply \"another\" Dying Light game. I also had a bug with a quest that I could not finish despite multiple updates, I was never able to return a certain item to the yellow marker, and that issue remained until I finished the game.The story and dialog were also boring as fu**, honestly, and I found myself skipping entire chunks of it because I could simply not give a single sh**. I played purely for the fun of the gameplay, and the \"world\".',''),(630,'Its like they took all the fun things from the first game and said ♥♥♥♥ it lets remove all of that .',''),(631,'I\'ve always considered Dying Light a masterpiece and still believe it to be one of the best games out there. The latest update made the game even better. Thanks to the game developer :))At the beginning of the game it may be difficult and you are afraid to go out and finish the missions but in the end it is the infecteds  that will get away from you.',''),(632,'This really is my Dying Light 2 Stay Human',''),(633,'I\'ll start off by saying I was a major fan of the first Dying Light! I put a good amount of hrs into my first play-through and thoroughly enjoyed it. It had its shortcomings, mainly in story/missions but overall was a blast to play. Fast forward a few years later came the announcement of Dying Light 2 and I couldn\'t have been more excited. Now that I\'ve actually beat it...I can say this is a very big disappointmentBy no means would I call Dying Light 2 necessarily a bad game though, it\'s just one that feels like a major downgrade compared to the first and given that the first is 8 years old now, that\'s not good. I do love the graphics of this game as it\'s downright gorgeous and on top of that PC performance outside of a few hitches/stutters runs pretty damn smooth. Parkouring is just as addictive as ever and the main focus of traversal throughout the game and beating up zombies is definitely satisfying but that\'s really all I can say. Basically it\'s areas improved upon the first in some ways but very minuscule and the areas they really missed on why people loved the original were monumental missteps. I swear the devs completely misunderstood what made the first game so beloved. First off, why did they feel the need to add this arbitrary rpg system for the game with useless level items for weapons and equipment? Let me tell ya, the gear levels make hardly any difference at all. The introduction of inhibitors to level stamina/health instead of just upgrading skills is also beyond stupid on top of the fact most can only be found at night.Speaking of night, until a recent update night/day were barren and had no zombies or special infected. So what\'s the solution? Let\'s now make nighttime so filled with volatiles it\'s almost impossible to maneuver around without a chase. Also in regards to skills, who\'s bright idea was it to make the skills this insanely grindy to level? It\'s a singleplayer game, co-op with friends, there\'s no PVP mode so what benefit is there to making this such a chore? For context, it took me roughly 20 hrs to unlock all skills in the original. After beating Dying Light 2 with 28hrs put in, I still have about 10 skills on both parkour and combat and funnily enough the skills in this game seriously lack any impact to overall gameplay and are quite boring again where as the first really changed the game. This game also suffers immensely from Ubisoftitus where the game has hundreds of activities to do but they\'re the same cookie cutter copy and paste things you see in every game to date with little to no variation. It\'s boring and lazy. The real killer of this game though is just how miserable the writing, questing, and characters are. I\'ll admit the original didn\'t exactly have a fantastic story but I least enjoyed Crane and Jade and her brother were decent characters as well. Side quests in the original too were also a lot more fun. I opted to pretty much avoid side missions in this as they all tendto play out the same and were just non-stop fetch quests. The main missions don\'t fair much better with long drawn out sections mindless climbing and dull action. However, what drags this game completely is the characters and writing. Seriously, I don\'t like a single character here! The motivations don\'t match nor are any of them likeable! Lawan especially is one of the worst written female characters I\'ve experienced in quite some time. The endings though are truly the main problem as it\'s quite honestly terrible regardless which one you get AND is pretty much a really bad ripoff of The Last of Us ending. There\'s just too many convenience\'s within the story, characters showing up, god awful plot twists (seriously that ending plot twist is so ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ stupid! 28 hrs for that twist is laughable). Forgot to mention too the final boss battle with Waltz is HORRENDOUS! I cannot believe a boss battle this bad made it into the final product.I had some enjoyment with it but this is a pretty miserable sequel in comparison to the first which I love and even played recently and still found 1000x better. So no, I don\'t recommend this as it\'s just boring as hell, a chore to play, and written so poorly. I can only see it being worth it if playing with friends for co-op purposes but in truth, there is a ton of better co-op options than this. It\'s not terrible per say but it\'s certainly not that good either. Keep in mind I played this solo so its issues are far more pronounced where I feel it\'d definitely be more tolerable with friends.',''),(634,'This game will make you go mad with things like:-NPCs teleporting when you\'re going too fast (for example running :))-An average of 3 cutscenes per minute in story quests-Game requiring all people in the lobby to open doors (which are cutscenes) in story quests-Cutscenes where the only thing you do is open the door-Parts between cutscenes where all you do is walk 200 meters in a straight line until you hit another cutscene-A lot of network issues-Everything glitching out-Coop progress is saved only on host save (quest progress)-Story making absolutely no sense-NPCs teleporting in general',''),(635,'Boring',''),(636,'Kyle crane isn\'t in this one... 0/10',''),(637,'the first one is far superior',''),(638,'Broken game. Every time I fall off the roof running away from volatiles, I accidentally hit alt+f4.......But for real, the reason i got this game is to play multiplayer and i thought desyncing in DL1 is bad. It\'s double in DL2. I keep falling off the roof even though I successfully jumped on the next roof on my screen so poor \'ol me gets absolutely devoured on the ground at night.GOOD STUFF, BUDDY.',''),(639,'99% dialogue1% gameplaylost my mind from all the yap',''),(640,'fun mechanics, painful achievements, horrid story, funny bugs, grindy',''),(641,'Don\'t get this game if you intend to play CO-OP, it\'s a total scam.The game does not let you share loot, not even Military Tech, which is used to upgrade the Nightrunner Tools and the resource is very limited, note that not enough Military Tech is found to upgrade all Nightrunner Tools already by design. It does not matter if you\'re the one hosting the game or joining. If your co-op partner opens a chest or evenMilitary Airdrops you\'ll find it opend and empty from loot, even the Military Tech.When talking with support and giving them detailed description of this issue we recived the following response \"We do acknowledge and always confirm this when asked by players - things are going to behave differently in a co-op session by design - it is essentially solely the host\'s game, while other players join in and help the host, while having fun doing so. It was the same in DL1 and we\'ve recreated the experience in DL2.\" How is making Military Tech unobtainable for the host \"helping the host\"?WE did NOT have this problem with DL1. Played that game with my partner and the DLC, never experiencing loss in loot, even when looting across the map of DL1. I repeat, do NOT buy this game if you intend to play in co-op thinking it works the same as in DL1, couse it does not.',''),(642,'Glitchy game got stuck in couple of missions because it would just glitch out or during parkour because the With horrible and predictable writing, when i had to save one character from an arrow otherwise i wont get the good ending, and extra playable content as per some game guides, it was it for me, no choice whatsoever.The first real main mission is just me against bandits and i\'m just risking my life and killing people without the \"allies\" appearing and then i have to storm a bandit base all by myself, like what is this lmao.Another huge pain was the annoying prologue tutorial and the lack of guns which were the best part about the first game and i was surprised it turned into a modern sword fighting game, 9/10 times i can just get a 2 handed rare weapon (i