istinct from each other.Good mission variety. There are 8 mission types, each with different objectives. There\'s also mutators that make missions easier or more difficult.Fun player hub where you can get drunk, dance and play minigames.Many customization options.Free cosmetics. Everything you see in the store is buyable with in-game currency, there\'s none of that microtransaction crap.New content is free.Great soundtrack.Friendly community.Only needs 3 GB of storage.ConsPoor optimization. Things like having too many lights or having many particle effects will drastically reduce your FPS.Can get a bit boring after a while.ConclusionDeep Rock Galactic is one of the best co-op games out there. It\'s fun, challenging and has great combat. The best part is that new content is free, including the cosmetics and it doesn\'t shove microtransactions down your throat (because there are none), unlike most games these days.',''),(652,'This is the game where you are willing to buy DLC\'s just to support awesome developers. Gimme an R! Gimme an S! Gimme a Rock. And. Stone!',''),(653,'rognk amd stnome',''),(654,'Truly a wonderful game. Simple yet well done style, great optimization and performance, good learning curve, great variety in gameplay. Also better with friends or even with randomsSome tips:- be careful on Haz 2, because it spawns one of the most dangerous enemies: unpromoted gunners with cluster nades- as an engineer you gotta be extremely careful whenever you pick Turret Whip, Deepcore, Deepcore with hyperprop, deepcore with fatboy.. honestly just pick whatever, you gonna TK your teammates one way or another- as a driller you should NEVER follow the map and only drill straight to your objectives. Ignore things like \"ceilings\", \"height\" and \"gravity\", you legally can\'t fall as long as you don\'t acknowledge you\'re up in the air. Also remember that your C4 is great at wiping out large groups of enemies and quickly mining big volumes of dirt/resources/scouts- only