ng trashtalked by a based mission control-come back alive from your first elite deep dive-realize that you haven\'t bought all the DLCs yet-reached rank of a legendary miner at level 100-relish your journey through Hoxxes for days-send a message to mission control that you vote for DRG as your game of choice for Labor of LoveBless developers that devote themselves this much to their games and the community.My thousand hours of playing this game is an unforgettable and fun experience, and so it is for everyone else who Rocks and Stones when coming home. For Karl.',''),(662,'Bugs do be crawling under your skin for real, boy.',''),(663,'too addicting',''),(664,'Left 4 Dead, but in randomly generated caves with destructible terrain, 4 diverse classes, and you fight bugs instead of zombies. That’s the shortest way to describe Deep Rock Galactic.',''),(665,'You can play it without spend any money, but if you want, its better buy the DLC on discount because the ship and some items on it cant be Obtained from game. just like.....more collection I think. dont know,. play fun guys',''),(666,'It\'s times like this i HATE steam for making it only a up or down vote.  100% a terrible system and thasts the mioan reason this is a downvote because its basically right around a 5-6 rating.This game, game-play wise is amazing.  It\'s very cinematic, the combat is beautiful and runs amazingly.  There are a ton of different weapons and play styles.  The actual battles are fantastic and fun to play.  they tend to be quite short lasting only a few minutes realistically but are great at that size.  would be way better to have some larger scale battles that last more then a few in game rounds.However,thats it.  you play the first battle few battles and thats the whole game.  VERY rare special missions if any, and they are usually just slightly altered battles that you have already done.  This reminds me of another mech game that was turn based and the best part of it was main quest/main campaign special missions that were lengthy and difficult.  They would have large effects on your campaign and often net game changing gear.  There is none of that here, its still difficult at times but never does it feel like a true challenge, and if it does the rounds are so quick you can easily retry and only lose minutes of progress.  The battles also never really get longer then 4-8 rounds (Each round is a real time 4.5 seconds ish)All the different objective types just boil down to kill the enemy.  i have never retreated nor have i felt i need to try and actually complete objectives.The game seems like the devs wanted to make a really fun combat system but forgot to add literally anything else.  Story is there in the beginning and then basically goes away.  there is some flavor text occasionally thats nice but no real story arc, and no special missions to really elevate this game past just bite size encounters that get VERY quickly repetitive. that boils down to the biggest problem.  its fun at first but you quickly get bored because every battle is almost exactly the same with no form of special missions.this is not a bad game and can still be enjoyed i only am downvoting because it could have been SO MUCH MORE (Especially with how long its development cycle was)',''),(667,'The small amount of maps and mission type variety is just painful',''),(668,'I enjoy mechs as much as the next mech enjoyer but man this is... pretty boring and repetitive after a few hours.',''),(669,'\"Phantom Brigade: An I Plan; I Go, Marvel of Mech-tactical Brilliance\"Phantom Brigade mech-stomped onto the scene recently, and I must say, the experience is captivating and entertaining. Developed with a keen eye for detail and a love for strategic gameplay, Phantom Brigade stands out as a shining gem in the realm of \"I plan; then I go\" tactics.\"I plan, I go\" (or \"we plan/we go\" is a game mechanism where your moves are planned out in short bursts of time.  Once your movement, defense, and attack plans are complete; they are executed in real-time in an armor-shredding display of destruction.  This mechanism was pioneered by strategic games like Combat Mission and developed with a more tactical focus by games like Shadow Tactics and Frozen Synapse. This mechanic injects a thrilling dose of unpredictability into every encounter, keeping players on the edge of their seats as they meticulously plan their moves and witness them unfold in real time. The result is a harmonious blend of strategy and action that feels refreshingly dynamic.Although not taken to the nth degree, the game\'s commitment to realism extends to its destructible terrain, a feature that adds a layer of depth to battles. Watching buildings crumble and landscapes transform in the wake of intense firefights between lumbering tanks and towering mechs, adds a visceral and immersive quality to the gameplay, making each skirmish feel like a true battleground.The arsenal of weapons available in Phantom Brigade is nothing short of impressive. From beam lasers to energy swords and railguns, the game provides a satisfying variety of tools for players to customize their mechs and adapt to different challenges. Crafting and a technology tree further enhance the strategic depth, allowing for meaningful decisions and specialization as you progress.  Do you want stealth at the sacrifice of speed? The decisions are yours.The heart of Phantom Brigade lies in its ability to let players assemble and control large mechs. Managing pilots and fine-tuning these colossal war machines adds a layer of personalization and attachment that makes victories all the more satisfying. The liberation of territories, rendered with great graphics, becomes a visual feast as your mechs stomp through landscapes, toppling trees, and leaving destruction in their wake.In conclusion, Phantom Brigade is a triumph in the world of tactical gaming. It\'s a great blend of established gameplay mechanics, destructible terrain, diverse weapon selection, lite crafting, meaningful technologies, and solid graphics.  Phantom Brigade is a great choice for fans of strategic depth and immersive mech combat. The joy of planning and executing maneuvers, managing your mechs and pilots, and liberating territories is an experience that will keep you hooked for hours.  Dollar per hour; it\'s well worth the time!  And if multiplayer were added - wow! It would be even more amazing!',''),(670,'If you enjoy mechs and XCOM play this game',''),(671,'\"We weren\'t expecting special forces!\"',''),(672,'Big Stompy Mech fun.I mean, sure, I could write a big, in-depth review - but this is mostly just a Fun game. Simple with enough mechanics outside the combat to be interesting, and the combat itself is quite well done. The only real issue I have is a lack of a proper story, and how easy the final mission is (which is unlocked the moment you have two adjacent territories to the capitol territory, and since it\'s positioned in the middle it has a very low threat rating compared to everything else past it.)All in all, as of time of writing it\'s just a simple turn-based mech game where you issue orders in turns that are 5 real-time seconds long and either concuss enemy pilots and steal their shirts, or blow them up with overwhelming firepower and/or just slamming them in the face with an axe.8/10, I enjoy',''),(673,'Fundamentally a really really good game with a very fun combat system, unfortunately it saverely lacks content, lacks variety in equipment after a while, not even more than 6 or 8 slots for all mechs so you can\'t even use all the stuff you get aside from scrapping it, capturing Provence is the same boring stuff not really any special missions to spice up some regions.All these notes are after around like 3-4 provinces completed but it really didn\'t show any sign of improvement in progression aside from capture zone and nothing to really reward you.What the good needs is a good sense of progression, more variety and options. Even if the gameplay is super fun it still gets tedious without a good incentive and that just leads to everything being boring.Hopefully with updates or mods this game gets better',''),(674,'It is a fun game and like others have said in this instance there should something other than \"YES\" or \"NO\" when giving a critique. Like I said the game is fun, but something is clearly half-baked here. A lot of the maps repeat, there really isn\'t any story to speak and things get stale to a point where playing feels like a chore.  You put so much tome into the game already, might as well see it to the end. More sunken cost at work here then a desire to keep playing.',''),(675,'Absolutely blown away by this work of art. Once it clicks everything comes together beautifully.',''),(676,'Amazing game, at first I was rather unsure about the idea of being able to essentially tell the future then respond to it. However after playing the game, I ended up enjoying it quite a lot, and it is not as easy as I thought it was going to be. So all together, I think that this game has a unique and well executed idea as well as smooth game play.',''),(677,'i like the game its fun and all but it really gets dull after the first area of the game its just the same fights with the same kinda mechs and tanks where is the variety i got a good amount of time in the game and i dont really wanna sink more time into it its a fun game i love the graphics the gameplay and the general idea but after a while it gets really stale and un fun oo look the same engagment i had literally a fight ago it gets really boring after some time and the game dosent do much to set itself apart from other games so i hope they take the time to work and improve on this game and make it more fun add more kind of mechs and customizations you can do add more cool weapons heck maybe add a multiplayer so people wanna keep playing maybe add really huge mechs to fight or own and please add some more advanced AI because man the AI in this game are just really dumb they just run at you and shoot theres no real strategy on the AIs end just because you put 10 enemy mechs on the field dosent make it hard there all really easy to kill or make their pilot launch away but i hope the devs read this its not an attack just constructive thinking make this game awesome dont just add boring ideas and expect it to work think outside the box',''),(678,'I really enjoyed this game. The meticulous 5 second planning is addictive. I\'ll probably spend just as much time on this game as I have for XCOM. I haven\'t gotten that far into the game yet so maybe there\'s stuff down the line that I haven\'t reached or unlocked yet which will make this game even more of an experience; I don\'t know.Having said that, I\'ve seen a few comments and reviews and I have to admit, there are a few things that I wish this game had, at the moment.Not sure if the devs will continue to support this game and by how much, but my feedback is (not in order of importantce):1. Allow full replay of each mission after you complete the mission with the option to save the replay for future playback (including actual health/damage at specific time in playback)2. Allow access to inventory during Salvage3. Show estimated time of arrival when in world map (and travelling to a set destination)4. Always show possible ranges of offensive action when a unit is actively selected, during planning stage (i\'m not sure how this is triggered just yet, it seems to come on whenever it seems \'appropriate\'.5. Battle field topography overlay (to more easily see terrain details)6. Full Controller / Steam Deck support!7. Ultra wide screen support (the tracking of actions on the timeline is a bit off)',''),(679,'You\'re Telling Me I Gotta Keep Playing This Until 2025?...actually, I\'m fine with that.',''),(680,'LIKE THIS IF YOU\'RE EXCITED FOR MONSTER HUNTER WILDS',''),(681,'This was my first entry into the Monster Hunter franchise, and it turned out to be the best purchase I’ve ever made. The game captures the sensation of being a hunter, from the challenge of identifying the monster, down to the best equipment you can use to defeat them. The game also pushes you to track down the beasts you hunt, which lives up to the name.Overall, the gameplay is incredibly addicting and the community is amazing as well.',''),(682,'I\'ve got something like over 1k hours on console. There is a reason that more people are playing MHW than MH Rise. An absolute masterpiece, and some of the most fun I\'ve had playing a game ever. Excited to come back to it on PC once I can convince one of my idiot friends they are missing out.',''),(683,'One of my friends introduced me to a game that included arm wrestling and I only started playing to beat them via button mashing. After 3 days of recovery... I played again for the actual gameplay. And I think I\'ve found the virtual form of crack.I have been awake for too long on too many nights playing this game. My eyes have literal dark circles and bags.My SO is worried about me. I can\'t stop grinding. I can\'t stop thinking about this game at work.I can\'t go to sleep without dreaming about killing another monster to make into new gear.My friends compete now in regards to progression.I don\'t know what reality is anymore.Help me. (:',''),(684,'i wish i have enough love for this game to start to play new save again.',''),(685,'Just came back to this gem a few weeks ago. Now Wilds got announced. I\'m on cloud 9.For all the people on X fka Twitter and Reddit asking if it\'s still worth to play in 2023. Yes, totally. This game is just so insanely good. Gear progression is so satisfying. (don\'t you dare skip that part with Fatalis/Plunderblade exploit)Learning Monster patterns, finding openings and exploiting them with your weapons is so rewarding.Learning weapons and picking up new ones is always fun. Theres also the perfect amount of downtime you can enjoy after heated hunts. Contemplating your latest failures while gathering some honey to cool down. Chefs kiss. Exploring the maps, finding secrets, doing research or deliveries. Capturing Wildlife or even being extremely lucky and finding the shiny ultra rare Wildlife. Unlocking decorations for your personal room which you can litter with the Wildlife and Trophies you found along the way.  Buy the game already!So many little tricks to learn, practice and skills to hone. Weapons are generally easy to pick-up but have \"hidden\", or rather not so obvious tricks you can explore, exploit and master. Utilizing your knowledge of a monster and going in with a new weapon just to obliterate said monster with the arsenal of tricks you build up feels unbelievably satisfying. People who never played Monster Hunter and think the gameplay looks like Soulslikes and thus comparing the weapons to Soulslike combat usually don\'t have an understand of how complex and fun these weapons are in comparison. At least in my totally unbiased and based opinion. Guard-pointing, iFrames, counters, weapon gauges to manage, kinsects. Combos, canceling combos into finishers, clutch claw shenanigans... and so much more. 9.99/10 melee combat. 12/10 unironically industry leading animations. And don\'t get me wrong.. I like soulslikes. I have over 300 hrs in DS3 and ER combined.But something about these weapons.. they just have the perfect weight and feel to it. The differences between a heavy 2hand Greatsword or a Sword and Shield that transforms into a huge Battle Axe compared to some Dual Dagger, your more typical Sword and Shield or the Insect Glaive are like day and night. The weight and Impact of heavy weaponry feels so overpowering and the nimbleness of the light weapons will turn you into a literal acrobat dancing across the battlefield. All the animations also are truly top of the line industry leading. Oh.. and for me, a masochist, somebody who loves to clutch and to continuously improve on my playstyle... there is a great speed-running community, which still seems pretty active and will inspire you to become better. You think you know your weapon? You have over 100 hunts with that bad boy? You feel pretty confident in your abilities? Oh boy. Buckle up buddy, because you\'re in for a ride. Go check out some speedruns with your weapon of choice and you feel like you\'re back to square one. It\'s crazy how some people can script these fights, perfect knock-down chains at the exact right moment, mix and match their combos perfectly and exploit every move the Monsters can throw at you. aaamayzin. (insert Jesse Lee Peterson soundfile) If you haven\'t bought this yet.. What are you doing?! I wish more people would give this game a chance. For example that funky guy I know. I wish he would just pick it up and play it with me. :) especially now that it is on it\'s biggest sale ever. I\'m not even sponsored. Frick.TL;DR: Masterpiece.',''),(686,'1 Pixel away from completing the extremely really very fun investigation missioni hate this game0/10',''),(687,'After over 700 hours, I decided to do a whole brand new fresh playthrough as we wait for Monster Hunter Wilds.  What does that say?  The game is epic. Pick up the expansion too. Put money in here instead of any ♥♥♥♥♥♥ EA or UBISoft game.  Never regret your decision. :D.',''),(688,'Switch Axe',''),(689,'This. Game. Is. AMAZING.​There are 14 different weapon categories, and each weapon has its own upgrade tree with over 50 upgrades to choose from. Along with this, each monster that you are able to hunt has 3 or 4 types of unique armor with different damage resistances, and every monster has a different set of armor. This makes playing the game always feel fresh and dynamic.​And if you somehow happen to get bored while playing along, you can play co-op with a friend!​9.5/10',''),(690,'2018 : when the game came, i really wanted to play this game. But my pc is potato and also i have no money to buy.2022 : i bought mh rise and also buy sunbreak. 202