 Indistinguishable from reality.☐ Like your fave song on repeat.☐ Could you turn that down?☐ I\'d rather listen to Nickleback.☐ Dial-Up Connection Noises.Audience-☐ Crotch Goblins (Kids)☐ Filthy Parasites (Teens)☑ Regular Meatbags (Adults)☐ All of the Above (Everyone)☐ Unfit for Mortal Consumption. (Nobody)Story-☑ GOTY Worthy.☐ It\'s REALLY good.☐ Decent but engaging.☐ What was happening again?☐ Plot? What Plot?Difficulty-☐ Dean Takahashi 100% this game.☐ Just press \'W\' and you\'ll be fine.☐ Easy to learn / Hard to master☐ Comp PvP levels of try-hard.☑ Souls-like.Grind-☑ None☐ Ranks/Leaderboards Only☐ It\'s optional, but helpful.☐ Risks breaking immersion.☐ No thanks, I choose life.Game Time-☐ Refractory period of CoD players.☐ Less than a day, easy.☑ Avatar wasn\'t this long...☐ The Spongebob time-card guy died.☐ Oh look, the heat death of the universe.Price☑ But wait, there\'s more!☐ Buy one tire, get three for free! ☑ Average Steam sale cost.☐ Check between the couch cushions.☐ Potential money laundering scheme.MTX-☑ 100% Optional, as all MTX should be.☐ Pay for Convenience type stuff.☐ It\'s distracting, but optional.☐ Are you sure this isn\'t Bliz/Acti?☐ Hey EA, hold by BudLite!________________________________________________________Hell Let Loose is an exceptional shooter that nicely blends Military Simulation elements with casual arcade-like concepts into an amazing experience that leans more into the MilSim side of things. Communication, adaptability, and inter-unit cooperation is key to winning and you will NOT be able to run n\' gun like you can on a game like CoD or Battlefield. Solo players are best advised to find a squad and either join or request to join and pay attention to the designations. A squad that shows the \'mic preferred\' option will probably want you to have one, likewise a squad marked as \'logistics\' probably isn\'t the best choice to get stuck in the ♥♥♥♥ on the front lines.The community is one of the most open and welcoming but also the most adamant about their gatekeeping.New players are more than welcome and the vets are usually fairly happy to teach if you\'re willing to learn, and the more interested in the finer mechanics and gameplay the more likely you are to succeed. Chances are if you hop in wanting a high K/D ratio or to play one-man-army with a sniper role or in a tank you\'ll be hard pressed to find success. Likewise in the reverse, expect to be the squad\'s favorite person if you pick up a much needed role like support, which drops supplies needed for garrisons, or engineer which repairs vehicles and builds fortifications. Or, if you\'re a more casual player (like me) just snag rifleman or medic, toss out ammo or heals like it\'s going out of style and you\'ll do just fine.The game is very easy to pick up and play if you have a decent rig, but it will take a long time to master. The high skill players can pick out the slightly darker gray pixel of a German helmet in a window from 200m away with ease, or can accurately predict your movement behind a hedgerow and that\'s if the sheer volume of fire doesn\'t get you first. Hell Let Loose, in my opinion, is not a game you play for a competitive environment. It\'s a game you play for the sheer scale and immersion, which is only amplified when you begin to play with friends and/or in an organized squad. Nothing is quite as fun as pulling out a clutch back cap of a point, or participating in some intense last stand at the final few minutes of a match. If you want large-scale, slower paced and immersive game then definitely pick this one up on the next steam sale.',''),(858,'I bought the game.  After training I just spent 35 mins trying to join a server to play. It was impossible - either there were no places, or a queue.  If I actually joined then I was immediately kicked out because either my ping was too low or my experience was too low.  A warning  - this game is a waste of time as well as money.',''),(859,'this game has changed my li