ntrols vs the mouse, a huge negative for me, especially for the camera. Have not found a blank slate starter zoo option, just a build completely from scratch or pick already full zoo option. Very black and white without any true options available.',''),(867,'Brings back childhood memories of Zoo Tycoon and I love it for that! This game goes so in-depth into the management of a zoo - from keeping the animals happy to the visitors, there is a lot to keep an eye on. If you like management games and love animals as much as I do, I truly think you will enjoy this game!',''),(868,'If you want to stare for a long amount of time at cute animals and see how they eat, swim, run, paint, climb and make a lot of cute things and if you like to build them a healthy and beautiful environment or all kind of buildings and decoration for your visitors, buy this game. It\'s awesome!I didn\'t even bother to play career, just a few missions as tutorial, and then I went to franchise where one can buy and sell animals from an online players\' market. With all the DLCs now you can breed your favorite animals and make a profit too.Step by step you can learn to build very nice and elaborate things, for example a temple shelter in your African savanna or a viewing gallery that has that shelter on the other part of a glass wall. The landscaping part is also easy to understand and very well done, so you can make all kind of land and water features, like waterfalls and caves in the mountains.Planet Zoo it\'s by far the best game for you if you want to play with animals and build a park exactly as you like it. You even get to build, if you want, a huge savanna, with many, many animals in it, without fear that the peeps will complain that they don\'t see anything in it, because you can make suspended paths or gondolas or even a subterranean passage that has a viewing bubble in the middle of your habitat. You can even build barriers and habitats with moats and just an invisible barrier.This is by fa