this way after demon of hatred, the actual worst boss.',''),(997,'zZzZ...　＜⌒／ヽ-､＿／＜/＿＿＿＿／￣￣￣￣￣￣￣　　　∧∧　　　 (　･･)    [F*king Isshin]　 ＿|　⊃／(＿＿／　└-(＿＿＿_／',''),(998,'Valheim really nails a lot of things that the survival genre sometimes struggles with:The sandbox gameplay that never rushes you is balanced with a meaningful progression system that keeps you fixed on certain goals and milestones.Acquiring and consuming better food makes you more capable in combat and exploration, but you will never simply drop dead due to hunger, making sustenance feel more like a reward than a nagging requirement.The building system is rewarding.  Your shelters must be constructed with adequate support and ventilation of smoke in mind, and interior comforts increase the amount of rest you gain, incentivizing you to not just build a house, but a nice house.You can construct paired portals to fast travel across the map, but certain raw materials cannot be carried through them, which creates interesting logistical choices between shipping materials over long distances by cart or by boat, and building outposts to process and craft your materials closer to where they are mined.  Additionally, certain crops can only grow in certain biomes, which further incentivizes setting up multiple bases.  Thankfully, the rewarding nature of the building system makes the prospect of building a new base an opportunity rather than a burden.Like most games in this genre, a good amount of time is spent gathering resources, but the amount you need never seems onerous.  It can be time consuming, but this is often because you will get interrupted by monsters drawn to the sound of mining ore and chopping trees, which breaks up what could otherwise be a monotonous task.And lastly, the game\'s unique graphical style is gorgeous.  Low polygon counts and simple textures free up resources that are spent on beautiful lighting, atmospherics, and color composition.This type of open-world survival/building game isn\'t for everyone.  It\'s heavy on atmosphere, but light on story, and there are some routine repetitive tasks involved.  But if you\'ve ever enjoyed another game in this genre, or are curious and looking for one to start on, Valheim strikes an amazing balance that accentuates the genre\'s strengths while minimizing its inherent flaws.',''),(999,'Need more Wood',''),(1000,'My biggest advice is don\'t spoil whats in the game by looking up everything in each biome. Try to keep as many things as you can a mystery. Once you loose that sense of adventure it wont be as fun. Other than that, this game is incredible. It\'s hard, very hard and even frustrating at times but it makes everything that much more of an accomplishment once you get the thing your trying to do done. This is the first review i\'ve made on a game but I had to make a comment on this one. This games got my full support!',''),(1001,'I guess I sorta like this game.',''),(1002,'The difficulty spike from Black Forest to Swamp is so unbelievably high when you\'re playing solo.Fighting 2 abominations, 3 skeleton archers, 3 draugr archers, 2 blobs, all at once, all alone, is LITERALLY IMPOSSIBLE.No amount of poison resistance is gonna save me from the ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ tree monstrosities punching me back to the stone age and getting sucked to death by the leeches.And then they break my portal there, twice, forcing me to remake all my gear from the ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ stone ages, to make a trash raft that takes me a solid 20 minutes to get back to the swamp, only to just die again, forcing me to do the same thing.It\'s WAY too difficult solo.I tried building stuff in the swamp so things couldn\'t spawn -- but no, literally had a draugr just spawn inside my base walls so clearly that mechanic isn\'t working.',''),(1003,'For over 30 hours I tried hard to like this game. I played it with my wife, but she didn´t like it.I played it with my friends, but they didn´t like it. I played solo, I tried mods, I looked up guides. I gave it chance after chance, because usually I like this type of game and most people online seem to love it but I just can´t get into it. I do love the atmosphere, but that´s about it. My biggest problems with it are the clunky combat system and the grind. I have also felt like hitting a wall after killing the first boss in several of my saves.In my latest attempt I spent hours exploring burial chambers, looking for surtling cores. I died at least a dozen times, killed five times that many skeletons and ended up with a grand total of one core. I´ve made it past the bronze stage before, but everything I did after that felt like even more of a chore to me, except for building my base. But even that part is more fun in other games.I guess even an overwhelmingly positive rating does not mean it´s for everyone.',''),(1004,'amazing game plagued by lack of content after years in early access and many more to come, considering how horribly long they take to add new stuff',''),(1005,'I do like the game, but is too difficult to play solo and replayability is sad.  It is possible (I\'ve cleared 2 maps starting each with new characters because of patches), but not much fun after awhile and too frustrating.  There is a HUGE difficulty increase when you get to swamp.  I find Bonemass on this new map since new patch I\'m playing and all mobs from swamp are spawned and most are 2 stars.  Tired of having to use arrows and can\'t survive melee at all even with maxed out iron gear.  You have to kill Bonemass and once you clear Mountain and get silver gear, then can you have decent melee in the swamp.  Swamp should be the last boss, place sucks.  And tired of eating every 5 minutes in this game.  I like hard gameplay, but this is annoying hard.  I guess if you\'re playing with a group it would be fun, but not everyone has a group of friends like that.',''),(1006,'I play this with friends and I got to say on a positive note the atmosphere is nice and building is fun, but the game is painfully slow something a