u need, with a great price, buying this game in sales is literally a steal cause of how cheap it gets compared to what you\'re getting, and yet, a company like Activision still gets 60 dollars for a SINGLE 12+ years old game with nothing new. Halo: The Master Chief Collection is what a lot of game companies need to learn from. Gathering all the quite old but great games you\'ve made and putting them in a collection with more features that lets any new player to get into the game quickly and enjoy it no matter how old the game is. Not even considering how great the main game\'s story, gameplay, soundtracks, multiplayer and everything is, I\'m much more impressed about how great this collection is and how well this great idea is executed. I\'m so glad that I decided to play Halo and you will most likely be too after you play it, it can be very likable for pretty much every gamer. a 10/10 experience',''),(1147,'Halo: The Master Chief Collection has finally made its way onto Steam, marking a momentous occasion for both longtime fans and newcomers to the iconic series. This collection bundles several Halo games into one, providing a treasure trove of nostalgic moments and some noteworthy upgrades.Pros:Legendary Collection: The Master Chief Collection assembles Halo: Combat Evolved Anniversary, Halo 2: Anniversary, Halo 3, Halo 3: ODST, Halo: Reach, and Halo 4 into a single package. This comprehensive anthology offers a rich storyline, varied gameplay, and countless hours of content.Enhanced Visuals and PC Optimization: With improved visuals and optimizations specifically tailored for PC, each game feels rejuvenated while maintaining the essence that made them iconic. The addition of adjustable field-of-view (FOV) and other PC-specific features enhances the gaming experience.Multiplayer and Customization: The multiplayer suite is robust, featuring classic multiplayer modes and custom game options. The customization options are extensive, allowing players to tweak settings to suit their preferences and relive their favorite Halo moments.Seamless Integration and Cross-Play: The game\'s integration with Steam ensures a smooth transition for PC players, complete with cross-play support and a unified progression system across both PC and Xbox.Cons:Technical Issues: Despite substantial improvements, the launch faced some technical hiccups, including occasional crashes and connectivity problems. However, ongoing updates and community support have significantly addressed these issues.Progression Challenges: While cross-play is a commendable feature, progression challenges may arise due to differences in skill levels between PC and console players, impacting the overall balance in multiplayer matches.Overall, Halo: The Master Chief Collection on Steam is a treasure trove for Halo aficionados and a solid entry point for newcomers. Despite initial technical hurdles, the collection\'s immersive campaigns, revamped visuals, and extensive multiplayer options make it a must-have for FPS enthusiasts seeking an epic sci-fi adventure across the Halo universe.',''),(1148,'Why does this require a microsoft account?',''),(1149,'I never write reviews, but this adaptation pissed me off. The main in-game function that made this game popular when it first came out was couch co-op, and they haven\'t bothered to put it in over the many years it has been out. Like most, I purchased this at the time to play with my kid (daughter), but found out afterwards I couldn\'t. In addition, for those that say use nucleus, you shouldn\'t have to use an outside mod for a base function that was in all of the halo games. After three plus years of owning the game, it still isn\'t fixed.',''),(1150,'It\'s Halo. On PC. Why are you looking at reviews?',''),(1151,'Epic.',''),(1152,'wort wort wort',''),(1153,'Highly recommended. Halo CE - 4 all in one place with modern multiplayer. This game had a very rough launch and it took 343i years to get it to an acceptable state. Now the experience is highly polished, stable, and one of the best ways to enjoy classic Halo outside of OG hardware/networking.',''),(1154,'When Mister Chieve said \"boo\" I Flooded my pants (HEHE Flood). It was like the tiem ravemind told arbiter \"you swill search a likely placer, and you will searc another\" Greatest game collection ive evr played',''),(1155,'Mister Chef',''),(1156,'It\'s Halo. If you like Halo you will like this...because it\'s Halo. If you don\'t like Halo you will most likely not like this...because it\'s Halo.',''),(1157,'lord halo: mister chiuef. mind telling me what youre doing with the convnenatn bomb?mister chef: sir convanent',''),(1158,'open gameinspect murder scenetrack down killerbeat up killers husbandbeat up killerturn in killerbeat up a third guy for no reasonfall through map 4 timesget drunkbeat up fourth guybeat up copfall through map againjob well done time to drink',''),(1159,'SUPER cool ideas, very ambitious and pretty immersive. You can do things like hack a terminal and toggle the security so it\'ll shoot all the previously happy workers in city hall just minutes into playing without realizing what you did. Vents are everywhere, and they all connect, just not always in a logical fashion—a huge portion of ducting went through my character\'s apartment in the opening tutorial sequence which I thought was just commentary on dystopian lives.At the end of my session my main takeaway is that it feels very, very buggy, to the point where I\'m not having fun. Yes, it\'s early access. Yes, I understand that it\'s not done. I just would have trouble personally charging for this at the moment since it feels like a demo, or a proof of concept, with a few buffered edges on the highly visible things.I REALLY like the case system, and I think that this is the correct sort of game to use this kind of system since linear games will just... railroad the experience and make it oppressively sterile. It still needs a bit more work, though. The UX is not absolutely horrible, but there needs to be a cleaner, faster way to sort through your collected bits of info. It also needs to not automatically link some things, as it removes the \"ah ha!\" moments, while also accepting alternative but comparable forms of comparable evidence, rather than just examining a body to glean all the relevant details each time (at least in the case of murders).I was hoping for an emergent gameplay experience, and in some ways it is; you can generate a city (very cool), go into any building (very cool), dig through people\'s stuff (cool, but limited variety), and solve cases from multiple sources (cool, but also lacks some variety). NPCs have lives, which is also neat, but they are very sterile in practice if they aren\'t involved with a case.This feels like an excellent framework that needs a couple of years to really flesh out the generative stuff you have to sift through, like vmails, help postings, etc., to make it feel less like Skyrim style \"Radiant\" quests with \"infinite gameplay\". It\'s cool for a bit, and definitely worth experiencing for an hour or so, but it kind of feels like a tech demo to show off the impressive map generation.In ~3 hours I played, I ran into the following notable things:Multiple containers doors/intractable objects not spawning properly, with objects floating in the air or in full viewMany areas are generated with very narrow geometry, making some areas difficult to squeeze around (odd for things like laundromats, etc)Changing or confusing descriptions of NPCsNames in written things, like vmails, either being \"[first name]\" or \"  \" occasionallyHarsh in-world lighting and art style make it difficult to accurately ID folks based on their photosHandcuffed NPCs offering to talk, but not allowing me toUnable to collect prints from handcuffed or unconscious NPCsContainer interactions taking precedence over notes without shoving it into my character\'s faceNPCs phasing through walls or tight geometryObvious evidence, like spent casings for rounds, not really matteringThe ability to buy a gun, and hold it like a banana in your hand(This one\'s a design choice, but one that works against immersion—you\'re an ex-cop!)Ambiguous labeling for things (\"Security\" vs \"Surveillance\", etc.) that, honestly, could be labelled better in generalThe gun design thing is a real confusing choice. From what I\'ve read, it\'s so NPCs have a way to buy murder weapons. It\'s claimed that using a weapon would potentially mess with \"proc gen\", presumably because you can kill NPCs that way, but I\'ll argue that your ability to buy them only dilutes the experience and serves to waste the player\'s time and currency.As I opened: you can have turrets gun down people indiscriminately. Just lead people and get them shot. There\'s a sword, too, which makes even less sense for an ex-cop analog to use, but it\'s perfectly viable and readily available. Why hamstring yourself from including another noir/crime story trope to throw into the mix? The game needs more than it has now, not less.Design choices like this lead me to believe that it\'s possible that the game could be finished and end up in that strange middle ground—hyper immersive (or \"realistic\"), but with a very narrow scope in mind that prevents it from becoming the full-spectrum sandbox like it\'s absolutely primed to be. On top of this, performance wasn\'t anything to write home about. DLSS inclusion is nice, since the game chunks real hard in some cases (X5900 / 3080). There were some performance issues while walking around, guessing it was a loading issue as things would pop in as I went around corners, etc.TL;DRSuper ambitious, cool idea, but narrow focus and confusing, expressively made design choices. Execution to be determined. I\'d sit on the sidelines until this one makes it to the finish line.',''),(1160,'Gosh. The game does not hold your hand, because it cannot hold your hand; it\'s too big of a world. In the tutorial mission I found myself conducting industrial espionage on a five star hotel and becoming a diamond thief - completely on accident - and now I have to find a fence to sell my stolen goods. I also know that the average Head Chef at a five star hotel makes 42000 crows in a year and my little B&E racked up fines worth over 26000cr, and once I find somewhere to sell these diamonds, I will know how many diamonds a Chef is worth in this world. I still have no idea who killed my vic, and that has, sadly, taken a backseat to playing 4k Minecraft Payday.11/10 game. Maybe more. It\'s Deus Ex: Roblox Revolution Noir. The only problem with this game is that it will make you choose between a comfy warm mug of tea and a Holmes experience, or three fingers of Jack and being like real life Humphrey Bogart.',''),(1161,'In the world of gaming, where sequels and remakes often take center stage, \'Shadows of Doubt\' emerges as a breath of fresh, innovative air. While it\'s not without its flaws, this game is a bold leap into what feels like uncharted territory, breaking away from the well-trodden paths of standard video game formulas.The freedom to approach cases in various ways—whether through breaking into seedy hotel rooms or analyzing a discarded receipt—offers a level of immersion that is as rare as it is captivating. Each case presents a new puzzle, with varying culprits and clues, challenging players to truly think like detectives.The game\'s commitment to a fully simulated world is its crowning achievement. The level of detail in tracking each citizen\'s life—from their daily routines to their personal interactions—adds an unprecedented depth to the gameplay. This meticulous design invites players to lose themselves in the game\'s rich, noir-esque universe, making every discovery and piece of gathered evidence feel earned.While \'Shadows of Doubt\' is ambitious in its scope, it\'s this very ambition that gives it a raw, unpolished charm. It\'s a game that isn\'t afraid to take risks, and it\'s these risks that make it stand out in a crowded market. The potential for growth and refinement is vast, and with continued support from the developers and the community, this game could evolve into a benchmark for innovative gaming.In conclusion, \'Shadows of Doubt\' is more than just a game; it\'s a daring venture into the future of interactive storytelling and immersive gameplay. It\'s a must-play for anyone yearning for something different, something that challenges the norms and offers a glimpse into what the future of gaming could hold. Here\'s to hoping that the game receives the love and support it needs to flourish and continue breaking the mold.',''),(1162,'You can fistfight an old lady at the bar while drunk. Also commit crime to solve crime. 10/10Edit: gRaMmAr',''),(1163,'I managed to catch a murderer just as they were leaving the crime scene and solved the case in roughly two minutes. Another case took me three actual days to solve because of a misplaced piece of evidence.One of the best detective games ever made :D',''),(1164,'Needs more stuff, but the basics are very fun. Some bugs and performance issues are present, but overall a very solid game. So long as the team is dedicated and keeps working how they do, I could easily recommend this game to anyone looking to get into a decently complex immersive sim.',''),(1165,'Best open world detective game on steam.',''),(1166,'Deus Ex but as a detective, I\'m having a blast already, I can\'t wait for it to grow !',''),(1167,'At first the game was fun, but in the last 5 hours I have not been able to complete a single mission without some type of case stopping bug from getting in the way. Not only that, any case that I was able to start outside of murders was giving me absolutely no information to go off of at all.- A vandalism case where a man was \"outraged\" and \"wanted revenge\" and all of the information they gave me was they had \"green eyes\", were \"non-binary\", and were\"tall\". No job, no address, no phone number.  Figure it out in a city of 400 people.- A case asked me to steal a folder from someone. The only information I was given was \"they live in X building, have gray hair\". The apartment building was 16 floors tall. The final straw for me, after playing for hours without a case being able to even get started, was when I finally got another murder case. I run to the scene, on Gray Street, but low-and-behold there is no body. I hack the cameras to see if there\'s any indication of a murder, nope, nothing in the past 24 hours. Then the game states \"CASE FAILED, INFORMATION DESTROYED\".On it\'s face the game is a great concept, but it feels like a buggy mess in it\'s current state and I just cannot recommend it like this.',''),(1168,'It was just another night in Great Holstebro.I was on my way back to City Hall after arresting the only man in town with facial hair, no glasses, an average build, and a name starting with D. I had had another case in my backlog for a while, one I thought impossible. Tracking down a criminal, one of average build, blue eyes, long brown hair. Age of 36. I\'m not one to shy away from abandoning a case gone cold, but with 3000 crows and a Physique Sync Disk, one I had never seen before, on the line, I figured I\'d sit on it for awhile.Anyways, as I approached the corner of Baker Parade and Meyer Boulevard, I saw her. A woman. Short, but proportional for her height, one might call her... average. Her hair was long, like the arm of the law, and brown as the sewer water flooding every basement in this damned city. As I approached I decided to give her a closer look, and then I saw it. Blue eyes. 36 years old.I asked her name, she was cagey, wouldn\'t tell me. Impossible, I have a maxed out Charm Sync Disk. I asked if she knew someone, wondering how she would react to being confronted with a description matching her own. Again rejected. I couldn\'t arrest her in the streets, too many people around, too much noise. I opted instead to sneak a Bloodhound tracker on her when she wasn\'t looking, but this only prompted an attack. She drew her Lazarus-5 and opened fire. No reaction from the crowd. As I attempted to defend myself with my trusty truncheon, several others drew as well and began firing on me (ColePowered please add self-defense laws). I was gunned down... but my tracker remained.After I awoke, I frantically scanned my map, hoping to locate the perpetrator, and there, I saw it. A green dot. Approaching Basement 01 Benitez House. I ran as fast as I could, hoping to catch her in her apartment, where she would have no reinforcements. Going through the door was a no-go. What if she was still armed? I\'d have to sneak through the vents.As I approached the first grate, I looked through, and there she was. Pissing. I waited, and soon she got up, washed her hands, and began brushing her teeth. Directly under the vent. I burst through, truncheon in hand, and put her to the ground. Then the cuffs came out. With the criminal subdued, I searched her apartment for any signs of her true identity. And there it was. A work rota. Street Stall Vendor, 8:30-20:30, Monday-Friday.Eliza Burton. We got her.Just another night in Great Holstebro.',''),(1169,'not gonna lieim high and just want points',''),(1170,'did an infidelity case while drunk.no, not me. my character.stumbled upon a murder scene while drunk because i mistook it for the cheater\'s apartment.tried to leave but enforcers got me.woke up with bullet holes and a headache with no money to pay for my medical bills.10/10 would solve while drunk again.',''),(1171,'Overall I really like the concept of this game as well as the art style, but it needs a lot more work to be complete. I had fun walking around exploring the different aspects of the game for a while, but it very quickly got repetitive and boring. It doesn\'t help that the \'city\' is so small and set up like a grid. This game has potential, but I won\'t be back to play it again unless major improvements are made.',''),(1172,'An extremely innovative detective game with tons of replayability. Love getting to know a new city and learning to be suspicious of all its inhabitants, one person at a time.',''),(1173,'It\'s interesting and stylish but right now it doesn\'t seem like there\'s much to do. Only a couple of the types of jobs work for me, the ones involving envelopes all seem completely bugged and some of the other types start too vague. I don\'t know if I did something wrong but 7.4 hours and I only got one murder case.',''),(1174,'I\'m pretty impressed, this game has so many amazing possibilities and mechanics that I am definitely keeping an eye on the development and evolution of this game. Probably the most interesting game I\'ve found in 2023 for under $20. Yes there\'s some bugs but I don\'t even mind them at the moment. There is still hours and hours of gameplay. If you have had a  desire to be a detective at one point or another in your life then this is one should definitely be on your list.',''),(1175,'THIS IS BUGGY AS HELL but it\'s fun to find murderers and you can turn on cheats to fix bugs. honestly put some polish on it and it hits. also maybe allow me to murder myself. eye for eye. try it on a later date.',''),(1176,'Cannot wait to see what else the devs add to this game given what they\'ve already released Early Access with.Stalking stalkers? Hunting hackers who are constantly a step ahead, monitoring you through the surveillance on the island? Unravelling an entire enforcer conspiracy forcing your detective to move island? Being hunted by other detectives for all the diamonds you \"Took for evidence\" mid-investigation, that just somehow ended up at the local pawnshop... You just misplaced them, right? Probably should\'ve used the Black Market instead.',''),(1177,'Incredible so far and I still haven\'t even scratched the surface of this game in 20 hrs. I give my glowing recommendation.',''),(1178,'You play as a student in the most famous magical school of wizardry, and will follow along the expected milestones of the academic year—you’ll attend classes, learn new spells and skills, help both teachers and classmates and unravel a mystery regarding a powerful enemy. It’s as Harry-Potter-esque as it gets. If you loved the movies and books, this game is a must-play.The gameplay is just as you’d expect for a student in the HP universe, complete with the selection process in charge of a talking hat, socializing with (or antagonizing) your colleagues, wandering around the castle and getting into trouble. Short of impersonating Potter himself, this is the closest experience you will get to enrolling in a Hogwarts school year. Of course, there is no Voldemort, but the story is sufficiently similar, and you will still feel like the prophetically-foretold boy who lived.You can customize your student’s looks, clothing and even your magic wand and broom. The options are not a lot, but still serviceable enough. Naturally, you can belong to any of the four Hogwarts Houses, and you will be given the corresponding uniform and colored accessories. You’ll find a lot of clothes in your adventures, and each item provides different bonuses to your character. Interestingly, you can change the looks and keep the features, which means that you can always look the way you want, and have the combat perks you most like or need. This is an excellent feature.Despite the emphasis on the wizarding experience, I believe the star of the show is Hogwarts itself. The castle is huge, rendered beautifully, and chock-full of secrets and places to explore. Ever wanted to wander around the school and grounds and see the places barely mentioned in the movies? Now’s your chance. And it’s every bit as fantastic as you imagine. Discovery is the name of the game, and every single location you’ve heard of in the books is here, and then some. Mind you, this is Hogwarts, not London—so no Ministry of Magic and such. Want to dare visiting the Forbidden Forest at night, looking for the dangerous arachnid lair? Try your luck at finding the common rooms of the other houses? Venture into the Library’s forbidden section? You can do all that. NPCs are quirky, diverse and in tune with the Potterverse. You will finally get to meet Peeves!Interestingly, there’s no curfews or hard enforced rules. Considering this is a school, and the importance of norms in the movies, this is weird—but perfectly understandable, from a gameplay standpoint. Still, there are moments when stealth is the better approach to trouble, and the student is perfectly capable of hiding and defeating opponents while unseen.Unlike with many games these days, I found myself avoiding fast travel almost every time. It’s nice to walk to the surrounding villages, and even nicer to fly there on your magic broom. You will find merchants, wild animals, rogue trolls, abandoned ruins and dark wizard camps. You can even explore ancient tombs, and there are many puzzles scattered all over the place for you to solve, courtesy of the late Merlin. Solving them will grant bonuses that aid you in several ways.The story is interesting, usually predictable and mildly convoluted. It also echoes Potter\'s journey with small twists here and there. The dark figure of the mysterious looming enemy is still present, only this time the goblins play a bigger part. As usual, there are undertones of real-life problems, like racism and segregation.An interesting choice regarding ethics is the use of the Unforgivable Curses. This topic is dealt with somewhat lightly, but the implied values and decisions are still there. Will you become a pre-teen murderous criminal and use these curses indiscriminately? Your choice. As for me, I decided I wouldn’t—and this meant a whole branch of the skill tree was unavailable to me. While you can’t pickpocket and rob to your heart’s desire, you can most definitely steal from every home in Hogsmeade, even in front of the owner, with no consequence at all. From a modern gaming perspective, I expected something less immersion-breaking.The music is fantastic. Not Williams, but deeply reminiscent of his work. Once again, the similarity was pushed to the limit, stopping only short of exorbitant royalties. You’ll recognize the notes and motifs over and over, and it’s never invasive in terms of gameplay. Some comments from your character can get repetitive, though—and the flu stations suffer from the same.The Room of Requirement is at your disposal as your main base of operations. You can decorate it to your heart’s desire, and gradually expand its size and functionality as the story progresses. Different props and magical stations will become available to find or purchase, and you can place them wherever you want. Eventually, you’ll get your own magical spaces to keep fantastic beasts like the famed magizoologist of the movies. The potion-making mechanics, however, are cumbersome and—at least to me—almost completely unnecessary.True, there is little variety in the enemy department. Combat mechanics are a bit simplistic, but serviceable. The student is not very agile, but it works well. Sometimes the enemies will feel bland. Unlike Voldemort and his minions, these guys lack depth and personality, and you will frequently end up fighting and defeating mindless golems and statues that always act and look the same.The graphics are really beautiful. And not only the world: the map, the cards, everything contributes to the gorgeous look of the game. A general sense of quality can be seen everywhere. The details are wonderful and always in line with the Potter universe.The voice acting is excellent, varied in mood and accents. The only ugly detail is the sound editing, especially the pitch slider for the main character’s voice, but this is also present with other characters and even cats. This produces weird sound aberrations that are sadly somewhat common.I did encounter a pair of bugs, but not game-breaking ones. In a weird case where my character clipped into a wall because I tried to use the broom too close to it, the reverse action solved the problem. I am aware of the complaints by other players, but for me it was a stutter-free experience, with no crashes at all, although texture popping can break the immersion from time to time. Loading times are not annoying save for the \"shades loading\" that always happens at launch.I used the Xbox One wireless controller to excellent results.In terms of mechanics, Hogwarts Legacy is plagued by a sign of the times: lots of errands, collecting items, fetching quests, and the like take place in a very large open world. The beautiful castle and scenery help in that department, and you\'ve got travel points, a flying broom and a magical steed to aid you in your travels. Thankfully, there are no microtransactions, gems, crystals, or any other annoying token currency so common today. Sadly, no Quidditch!I could not help but to feel a little empty at times—in Hogwarts Legacy, the sense of “game-ness” is a bit painful, given the wondrous world and potential for immersion. The game could be much better with a bit more complexity, from more interaction with the environment to maybe better customization options. However, the game is complete and functional as it is, and I understand why these design decisions were made.The price is a little high to my liking, but with a 15-20% off it would be fair.Playing Hogwarts Legacy has left me a sense of wonder I have seldom felt in a game lately. Even the story itself evokes that of Harry, and purposefully so. But it works. If you are a Potter fan, this is a must buy. You\'ll thoroughly enjoy the experience. This is the best alternative yet to be a Hogwarts student.Charmingly recommended.',''),(1179,'I completely beat the game thus at this point it doesn\'t hide any more secrets from me, tho it doesn\'t change the fact that it had been a huge fun and Hogwarts Legacy was the game I really needed and I don\'t exclude replaying it in the future as it\'s become my personal favorite game of the 2023. It\'s not perfect, but absolutely deserved a positive review!Pros: beautiful, addicting world full of satisfying, but often undemanding fights. Using magic was exteremely fun and gave multiple possibilities of having a great combat experience (you can try stealth, defensive plants, potions, choose to learn unforgivable curses or just use mastered spells) quite nice character development-you can spend talent points on improving your magic skills and upgrading your equipment items. absolutely stunning beasts and landscapes offering tons of activities, side quests, puzzles, exploration the Room of Requirements being in general your base  where you can prepare your gear, brew potions, grow plants and breed beasts. It can be also decorated both by conjuring items from the collections and by changing its style with the help of your own slave, I mean house elf  engaging and fun side quests full of unexpected twists and sometimes heartbreaking situations compensating for the boring main story quests unlimited in time or the main story despite not giving actual moral consequences of your actions,in some cases you can get a better reward and/or piss off the NPCs large freedom of action the possibilities of customizing your character (from their appearance, voice to the gear they use) various and interesting side characters, at least some of them fun, but again quite simple puzzles a versatile game for many hours and for every generation. Thanks to the fact that you play as a fifth-grade student, the plot seems more mature and at the same time it gives the opportunity to learn all the basics. a decent optimization, beautiful graphics and atmospheric musicCons: my biggest complaint is in spite of a huge level of immersion, the lack of an actual moral system. We can pour out dark magic all over Hogwarts and no one will even bat an eyelid. And no, we can\'t be bad per se, just rude. Even if you choose a bad ending  and decide to open the repository, except for the mysterious death of Professor Figg, there are no consequences and you can still win the House Cup and be praised for what you\'ve done. There is no penalty for robbing houses or using unforgivable curses. I think the biggest consequence I had was Natty asking calmly BLOODY HELL HOW DID YOU LEARN THIS SPELL  choosing a House is a small matter, apart from making friends from your House  faster I suppose or getting an additional quest when it comes to Hufflepuff. little varied life at Hogwarts,  the first night will be the last you spend in your dorm . I feel there could be more interactions with fellow students and more activities within the house you belong to (you can\'t really storage the loots or use your room). Also the character can\'t sit, so furniture like sofa and chair are just a decoration. boring main story. I get you\'re supposed to feel like a gifted chosen one, but the result was average for me. no actual storyline from Ravenclaw there could be more potion ingredients etc. so it\'d be more complicated to find them many NPCs were boring, unlikable and poorly written characters I won\'t miss, like for example  I wasn\'t even sorry when Figg died  no Quidditch (maybe a chance for a DLC in coop in the nearest future?) you can\'t romance Sebastian and Poppy :// but I get, it\'s a family friendly game cutscenes in Ancient Magic and Merlin\'s Trials spots cannot be skipped no photo mode therefore you can\'t take beautiful screenshots:(It was a great adventure that gets you back to your childhood dreams and reminds you that your inner child is still there, evoking many pleasant memories. As a Potterhead I\'m really impressed by the whole universe and how smart the devs created a story before the chosen one and only Harry Pottah. Play it and see for yourself:)',''),(1180,'The game is entertaining and fun for first few hours, then it gets repetitive and boring with shallow RPG elements and not so interesting main character with boring dialogues. One of the very few games I have dropped midway during a playthrough.',''),(1181,'not a fan of harry potter but this was a heck of a game',''),(1182,'The game is exactly what i expected it to be and better, the map is huge, Hogwarts its self is huge. The game seems alive with the paintings talking and stands of armour fighting lots of secret doors and puzzles to always play around with. Well developed game keeps you always doing something the dialog isnt boring i found which is rare its movie long sometimes but entertaining. Fighting aspect is awesome i mean your a wizard over all i really enjoyed the game, good game.',''),(1183,'I am not sure how I feel about this game. I got the game at full price. I guess I\'ll start by listing all the pros and cons I have.Pros:Beautiful environment. Really feels like you are in the movies when navigating Hogsmead and HogwartsCombat is pretty good. although it starts feeling repetitive Navigating Hogwarts. Looking for secrets and walking the halls felt great.The classroom quests. Loved the intro classroom scenes. Feels like the moviesCons:Might be a hot take but might have been cool if they added some Bully like elements without mods where you had to show up to class on time or bully students by attacking them starting a fight until you are stopped by teachers will try to apprehend your character Grinding for a bit makes you too strong quicklyadding mods to your armor and weapons is nearly pointless. I Change my gear too much to make it worth taking the time crafting the perfect gear unless max level. Even then there isn\'t a lot to do with your newfound powerCannot recruit followers. Would\'ve been pretty cool if I was able to recruit friends after helping themBroomstick controls suck! Could have been an easy fix if we could change the controlsNo quittage to play. even if it was for  No new game plus. need a challenge to use my forbidden spells and OP powersStory is mid. I started to get the point where I wanted to skip and a lot of my decisions don\'t matterEntering the forbidden forest. There should be points docked for getting caught entering or leaving the forbidden forestNo guards at night in campus.(only one quest had them) Wished they had the 5th years go on regular patrols and getting caught will send you back to the dorm and dock points from your houseSummaryI know I am writing this review pretty late. It has been a while since I last played Hogwarts. The way I feel about this game is that this game feels like it needed more time in the oven. I never kept up with the development of the progress so I had no expectations and this game came out of nowhere for me. I heard that it has been delayed quite a bit. The castle is amazing. The exploration of Hogwarts is best thing about the game. About halfway through the game I did start to get bored. I felt like skipping scenes because they felt like filler. The side quests were a mix of bland and aright. transmogs are pretty cool but the gearing is terrible. I swapped out my gear every few encounters. upgrading or modding isn\'t worth it for it as you quickly swap out you gear as soon you get the materials for it. This game feels like It could have been a pretty good mmo. just thinking about that kinda wants that. raids would look so cool having a bunch of wizards shooting their wands at a boss. It is a hard game to truly recommend. I am still conflicted whether I regret my purchase or not. I guess I have mixed feelings.',''),(1184,'Not a perfect game, but I really enjoyed my time with it. 8/10: Highly Recommended.A quick preface: I haven\'t thought about Harry Potter since like... 2008? It\'s been a while!Pros- Excellent Visuals- Hogwarts and Hogsmeade are an absolute joy to explore. I spent WAY longer than the game expected me to JUST exploring and finding all the collectible field guide pages I could.- Transmog is available right away and at no cost. You don\'t have to go into battle looking like a clown just because the stats are good. You can change them on the fly anytime you want! - The combat system is great! Took me a minute to get into the groove, but once it clicked it absolutely clicked!- The spells are fun to play around with. Experimenting to see what spells combo well against a given enemy was really enjoyable.- Respectable difficulty. It\'s not too hard to push me to frustration, and not so easy it puts me to sleep. In the opening hours I found myself healing a lot... later on I barely took damage. I\'d say it veers on the \"easier\" difficulty side but fine none the less. No harm in rewarding player skill.- Some of the bosses were visually impressive and fun to fight.- Story was fine. There were moments it felt needlessly dragged out. However, I was distracted with other things.- Flying around on a broom felt good! The controls were odd... but I got used to them quickly.- I encountered very few glitches and bugs. Far less than I was expecting.- Minus the occasional hiccup towards the end of the game Hogwarts Legacy ran smoothly. Minimal performance issues.- This game doesn\'t require you to know anything about Harry Potter to enjoy it. There are loads of easter eggs for fans of the series to enjoy. However, not recognizing the easter egg doesn\'t take away from the experience. I had forgotten SO much over this last decade and even then... a lot came rushing back. Was never punished for forgetting stuff though.- Some great characters and side quests representing 3 of the 4 houses. Natsi and Sebastian are clear standouts.- I was giggling silly during the Polyjuice potion section. That was exactly what I wanted from Hogwarts school mischief.- Taking place a good hundred years before the events of the Harry Potter series was a good idea. Helps keep the stories out of each-others way.Cons- Enemy variety is low, lot of quantity over quality in the later battles.- Puzzles variety is good, but not quite good enough. It reminded me of the Korok puzzles in Zelda.. There\'s just SO MANY of them... so despite a decent lineup on paper it feels like they are repeated over and over again. Same issue here.-GEAR LIMITS! Why? Why does there NEED to be a limit on gear like that? Do you have any idea how SICK I am of dropping everything, fast traveling to a shop, and dumping my entire inventory every 5-10 minutes!? I can shove a monster 3 times my size into a handbag... I THINK i can carry one more hat!!!! Even with the Merlin Trials, this was ANNOYING!!!- I did not enjoy the Stealth mechanics in this game. Total snooze fest.- House points didn\'t really matter like they did in the books/movies. That was disappointing and makes some of my actions feel like they had no consequence.- No house specific quests... total missed opportunity there. - No Quidditch. There is an In-universe reason for this... but every time a characters mentions it, (and they do often) that feeling that there\'s something missing wells up in me again.- The Magical Beasts were cute! Yet, I barely even touched the upgrade system... simply because I didn\'t have to! Every few minutes I\'d find better gear than I was wearing and just swapped it out. As a result, I feel like I wasted my time in the vivariums.- The Room of Requirement was neat... but I mostly ignored it. I never got to invite anybody into the room so it was just there to grow plants and brew potions really...- The hamlets scattered around the world are... uninteresting. Could\'ve used a bit more love to make them memorable.- Where\'s the Whomping Willow? I wanted to get punched by a tree!In conclusion, I think I can say this is the best Harry Potter game ever made. The world is a joy to explore, the combat system is engaging, and the story has good presentation. The game is mostly held back by its own RPG systems and those couple of things it\'s missing.',''),(1185,'This game is absolutely incredible.I did not think it would be possible to make a mainstream game that is actually good, in this day and age of crappy AAA games. But there has been an incredible amount of work and passion that has gone into getting this game just right, reflected by the massively long credits.Overall I was impressed at how many elements of the original and best games were still kept, whilst adding in new aspects to the gameplay. The mystique and intrigue of the wizarding world is perfectly pulled off in and it keeps you entertained for hours. The music is absolutely brilliant and (apart from the blatant racial diversity shoved in your face) I loved the complexity of the characters you interact with and overall story arc.The number one thing for me was that they brought back FLIPENDO!!!!!!!! LONG LIVE FLIPENDO!!!!!!!!!!',''),(1186,'There are at least 50 cats in the game. You can pet them all. 10/10',''),(1187,'I identify as a wizard',''),(1188,'This... this is how AAA gaming should be.I seriously played this until 4-something in the AM, on \"school nights\", it was so enthralling.The only negatives I see are:* The tutorial prompts sometimes step on each other and it takes several tries of the suggested steps to make them go away.* There\'s four achievements for getting to the middle of the game - each one unlocked by being a different house.  So, don\'t expect to 100% this one.* The descriptions for some of the \"dueling achievements\" are... obtuse, but it\'s a minor issue.',''),(1189,'An absolute gaming masterpiece. The visuals and gameplay are astonishing. I don\'t even remember when I was this excited to keep playing a game.If you are a fan of the Harry Potter movies, there is no doubt in my mind that you will love this game.Hogwarts Legacy is, simply put, terrific in every way.',''),(1190,'If you\'re a fan of Ubisoft games, maybe Bethesda open-worlds, maybe if you\'re super really into HP universe, maybe this one will work for you. Otherwise - don\'t bother. It\'s the same repetitive open-world boring design that was outdated ten years ago. Honestly, I got distracted by pretty Hogwarts to think before buying, and it was actually fine until I was put into the open world 1-1,5 hour in. Then it was so underwhelming I felt that I\'m wasting my time. I googled to see if it will get better, but no, it\'s literally a ubisoft game in HP universe. It\'s just sad. There\'s so so much you could have done with this universe, but they went for the most generic type of game since shooters of 2000s.',''),(1191,'For someone who is a large harry potter fan from childhood and a gamer, this game is fairly disappointing for the following reasons:1. Terrible and uninteresting story line2. Lack of reputation for your actions (No consequences)3. Very few companions4. Repetitive game play5. My favorite spell (Patronus Charm) is not in it6. Enemy types are extremely limited7. Main character has no personality8. Most of the classes you only go twice9. Cannot get any of the deathly Hallows (Permanently)10. Game is entirely fetch questingI could go on a lot more about this game and it has some great qualities but is overall quite disappointing.',''),(1192,'You can pet cats, but you can\'t imagine how inconvenient travel was before I invented floo powder',''),(1193,'Man, I really wanted to like this game, but there is just so many things that make me want to put it down. It says I have 30 hours in it, but no joke, probably near half of those are from me pausing and going AFK cause I got bored. Now, don\'t get me wrong, I love open world repetitive task stuff as much as anyone else, but this game fails to satisfy in so many different areas. The Hogwarts castle itself is honestly amazing. The rest of the game, however, is.... lame. Unfortunate. I feel like I would enjoy this game a lot more if I was younger.My background: Ive read the books, seen most of the movies, and played Order of the Phoenix on XBOX 360. That one was pretty good for its time iirc. I would say I\'m a fan, but not crazy about it. Pros: If we are just talking strictly Hogwarts here, and nothing they did outside caste grounds, this game has plenty of secrets, people, side quests and collectibles, etc. to keep you engaged and mesmerized by the truly amazing castle. The game truly feels *cool* to play, and makes you feel immersed most of the time.- Great graphics.- Exploration is great.- Music is great.- Immersive. Cons: Game just gets boring man, and its disappointing. So many things are just lame.- Inventory system, loot system, and economy in general is dumb. I guess there is plenty of preppy British clothing and wizard cloaks and things that fits the style, but man, the transmog system sucks. You have to manually change the appearance of every new item back to how you had it previously.... There is no immersive reason to be equipping ridiculous looking gear for stats, its all made up anyway, why make this process so INSANELY annoying??? Limited loot spaces as well makes you constantly either go find vendors to sell all your trash, go to your room to break them down for materials, or go do endless remote tasks to increase your storage space.... This system is so bad in so many ways....- Combat. The system itself is not bad per-se. Its just basic, easy, and needs to be focused on WAY LESS than they do. You fight the same 5 enemies the entire game, and if for some sadistic reason you play on a higher difficulty, you will just be spamming for so many hours in this game. The system is so shallow, that caring about gearing is just pointless, so it makes all the collecting, economy, crafting system, and consumables feel like a waste of effort.- Story is written like its E for everyone (literally rated ESRB 13+). I understand why, but YIKES the story is just so boring. Your character is just a saint who is so uninteresting. The side character design is fine, its just the story lines both main and side are beyond boring. You feel like you are going through the motions....- World outside of Hogwarts. Why? Why is it so big? So I can fly on a broom with awful controls more? No wonder they didn\'t make Quidditch, their flying mechanics are BARELY serviceable as a basic means for transportation. But yeah, the rest of the open world is WAY too big with literally nothing in it except endless random check box style side objectives. Who knows how long 100%ing the game would take. The storylines try and send you through the different areas, but I don\'t see the point. - Quantity > Quality. I would rather the game have less areas, less objectives, less random overlapping spells, and focus more on quality hand crafted areas and story, not just empty forests for an excuse to add 1 of 10 spawn points for a specific animal that literally nobody will care about.- The custom room and animal stuff. You are tasked with going through so many tutorials on collecting animals to farm materials around the world and keep them happy and create your own personal player housing I guess, but the whole thing feels pointless. Its like, Fallout 4 level of pointless. Like I said earlier, there really isnt rewards to shoot for anyway with crafting or modifying gear. Its all a waste of time and not satisfying in the slightest.I really tried getting invested. I really did. The fact that a beautiful Hogwarts game with open world and flying in it can manage to get so boring so fast that I can\'t even finish it is pretty sad. Some people love it. I can\'t call it a bad game, but ive had it installed for 6+ months now, and I\'m just never in the mood for it. Maybe I\'ll revisit it later, but Ive already seen enough of the castle and stuff to get the gist. Hogwarts exploration sim 9/10.Open world RPG 6/10.',''),(1194,'Finally, an excellent Harry Potter game that really brings the world alive.',''),(1195,'naa',''),(1196,'Has a great deal of tediousness, You can definitely tell they did things to artificially extend and add to the game. The combat is either foolishly easy or ridiculously hard. Cyberpunk police (old school you know if you know) was better designed. I love Harry Potter. This game falls flat personally. While I got it on sale. Wish I had never bought it.',''),(1197,'It\'s whimsical, magical, bisarre and with really nice graphics and good looking environments and it all feels like a really good visualisation of Hogwarts and its nearby areas.The fighting feels good as well.However - even though it has lots of good things going for it, at the same time it feels quite generic and non-engaging.The looting is boring, to say the least.The dialogues are pretty well done but at the same time maybe they are dragging out a bit too long, beacause I always end up stop listening.The skill tree has some great things but you get it all way too fast.The stealth is not really exciting either.It all falls a bit flat and it wasn\'t before long I found myself wanting to be done with it rather than longing to continue.TLDRGood but some stuff is lacking to keep it interesting.6.5/10',''),(1198,'The bugs in this game are an absolute disgrace. It\'s very rarely actually playable. Ive got under 4 hours and i\'ve already had countless bugs that have broken or lagged out games. At the moment I cant even log in to play because \'servers saturated\'. This game is a joke.',''),(1199,'DO NOT BUY THIS GAME NOW.  Seriously, wait a year or two and maybe then they will actually get off their collective butts and fix some of the serious bugs that they have in the game.  Also maybe by then private leagues might have the tools that they need to be able to admin games.  Also half the teams are missing and you will need to spend money to get them.  The comsetics are nice in theory but most of the time you don\'t really get see them so they don\'t mean squat except when you are looking at your team.  It\'s taken them almost two years to get past the Beta phase with a somewhat playable game that has lots of flaws.  Give them another year or two to actually maybe fix the game.  It\'s Cyanide so who the hell knows.  Maybe they will finally be fixed in Blood Bowl 4.',''),(1200,'They implemented a new system where it bans you if you concede a match, I see what they were going for but the problem is they have bugs in the game still that just do not let you play a match and so it counts as a concede. Nothing better than getting a black screen in game loading to only get banned for 12 hours because the game wouldn\'t load properly. Don\'t buy this game.',''),(1201,'The initial bugs have been ironed out and I\'m enjoying the implementation of the 2020 Blood bowl rules in this new edition. The AI is still pretty limp, but does follow a sequence of fairly sensible processes, but it still poses no threat to an average player. The Blood pass system is actually pretty good. The only benefits to paying is to get visual upgrades, which is fair and actually tempting to me, as I like to upgrade the appearance of my players, as they upgrade level wise. So there is incentive there for me to buy visual upgrades for my preferred teams. The gradual introduction of new teams is a good way to keep things fresh too.',''),(1202,'I like this gamer.  I\'m playing Blood Bowl, on a computer, whenever I want to play.  Crashes have been minimal for me, and I enjoy the new teams.  Looking forward to setting up a personal league once that\'s possible.Perfect, no.  Fun, yes.',''),(1203,'Keep working on it devs you\'re getting there. I\'m a tabletop player just looking for a video game to fill the time in between league games.',''),(1204,'Cash Grab game, just play Blood Bowl 2',''),(1205,'Even the BB3 started with bad foot, it\'s getting better with every patch ^^',''),(1206,'I love Blood Bowl, I play it a lot, and have played it a long time, and in all honesty BB3 does a pretty good representation of it. I\'m pretty sure the RNG is unbelievably wonky because either every roll goes in my favour or every roll goes against both of which detract from the experience. I don\'t think I\'ve had many games where if we were able to look at the stats they\'d be remotely near balance. I know it\'s RNG but surely that has to happen at some point? So if you want the full Blood Bowl experience of being salty cause of dice or feeling like an absolute BB god because of them then this is going to give you both those feeling in abundance. The lack of league tools is a huge issue because it means you just can\'t really play with your friends which was the real joy of BB2. The micro transactions I don\'t care about, the unstable servers I can live with, the waiting 10 minutes for a game I can handle. I\'m just sad that Cyanide had a chance to do sometime great, with what I think is the best rule set blood bowl has ever had, but the experience is so horribly skewed by the absolute nonsense of the crazy RNG.',''),(1207,'It\'s basically the tabletop game.',''),(1208,'Fail to load into the game get banned from playing - current experience of this patch',''),(1209,'I preordered this game and from what I\'ve seen so far it\'s both better and worse in some areas compared to Blood Bowl 2 as of the current patch of this review so I\'m only going to give a few exemples.some of the good and bad parts (in my opinion) are like this.Good:#1 you can jump over downed players even without the jump skill (haven\'t done it outside the tutorial but I\'ve seen the option for that).#2 it doesn\'t give you the option to use the apotecary on hired players for the match + won\'t give SPP to those players either (if I remember correctly dead players can\'t get MVP).#3 the Nuffle Prayers are interesting when they happen, but with my luck it\'s usually 4-6 in favor for the opponent in my games and when it is in my favor it helps both sides or causes most of my opponents to concede.#4 the coach you have for the team can give a set of animated emotes/reactions.#5 it\'s much easier to customise the players and their names.Bad:#1 there is technically microtranactions in the game that uses Warpstones, but you can unlock some for free through the battlepasses which are only used for mostly cosmetics, different cheerleaders and coaches + unlock the new team on level 1 battlepass instead of level 50 battlepass.#2 there are a couple of bugs and glitches remaining (most of the launch ones have been fixed) where the 2 most annoying ones for me are A: the visual glitch that shows the players moving to a different spot rather than the spot they actually went or the circle showing where the ball is sometimes shows the circle on a different spot, B: if you click a player to move to a different spot before or during kickoff event it sometimes freezes where it usually helps to right click (on mouse) before clicking the player again to unfreeze it.#3 if you want to pause the game then there\'s no longer a chat where you can tell the opponent why you are going to pause the game to let them know if it\'ll be long enough so they can do a toilet break or go grab something to eat/drink.#4 after spending the petty coins then you can\'t use your actual gold to buy some advantages if you have more gold than you can spend (I guess they did a way to spend the gold though team/coach expenses that you roll a d6 if you will lose gold or not.#5 you can no longer get rid of team re:rolls after buying them if you get enough good skills that you don\'t need as many team re:rolls.so in summary from my games so this is based on my opinion:if you easly get angry when it goes bad for you in games then id say this game is a 8.5 out of 10 in salt level.in gameplay wise it\'d say 7.5 out of 10 due to some bugs and glitches + stuff I haven\'t mentioned.in visual graphics compared to Blood Bowl 2 it\'s either 9 or 9.5 out of 10.in audio wise it\'s 8 out of 10.The controlls for the players compared to Blood Bowl 2 then it\'s 5 out of 10 due to it can be confusing to use or read how to use them.',''),(1210,'Don\'t be experimental like me, just play Blood Bowl 2. By the time I had a \"feel\" for the game, 3 hours passed.It\'s unbearable. The biggest criminal is the slow animation times, even if the game \"trys\" to refund the clock, I refuse to wait 10 seconds for a single damn tackle. That is my number 1 gripe. The game gives you 2 minutes per turn (8 extra minutes, that is a resource) but the game sort of putters, considering what you want, which takes time, YOUR time. And I ask the developers, if I\'m playing against the A.I. why am I being timed? I have no interest in online play, I just like playing Blood Bowl. Oh and with all these issues, its hilarious that they want you to buy a \"battle pass\", get ♥♥♥♥, finish your game before you ask for extra money.Do not be like me and waste $30 on this, it\'s buggy, even the tutorial is bugged, you CANNOT complete the tutorial unless you select Online Mode. I\'ve always thought people give Cyanide Studios too much ♥♥♥♥, but I get it now, they are ass. The sad thing is I bought this with my budget instead of a different game, but ♥♥♥♥ you CS, I\'m going to take a bit more money and buy the game I chose this one over.',''),(1211,'I long defended this game, rough launch but it will get better over time, I thought a lot of ppl completely overreacted when there was a shop currency and customization features would obviously be in the battlepass. but for every step forward they make so much more issues for themselves. The only thing the bloodpass has going for it is you have plenty of time to complete it to get your free team, the amount of content you get in the free version is incredibly poor in comparison to damn near any other battlepass from any other game so lvling is feels incredibly bad won you get 1 reward pass the next 5 locked away till you get your next handout. The game still runs extremely slow, plenty of bugs, server lag in menus, responsiveness in clicking units or making selections this is a main issue which turns away new players with the timer being 2minutes default hard to keep under control when it take 5 seconds for any action