sing expatiation for money makes sense but locking the ability to use mounts behind a pay wall? scummy to me',''),(1219,'Somehow this game just gets worse and worse. This most recent update (S4) is basically unplayable with all servers crashing over and over and basic things like inventory and maps not even being accessible or functioning correctly. I would say it\'s an embarrassment to Amazon but this is pretty much how corporations work now. Get way too rich way too fast, expand into areas they no nothing about while claiming to be experts...then put out inferior products that we are just stuck with. All while promising they are listen to customer feedback and trying to get better but they actually get worse and worse. Blatant money grabs are the regular for video games now it seems. Modern capitalism is how much can you scam before people catch on and you dissolve and write it all off with your real money hidden off shore. I\'ll be moving on and not spending anymore money on this game.  It\'s fair enough to say I got my monies worth with the hours but a lot of the time has been spent idly farming waiting for real content to be released which rarely happens. I would not recommend a new player invest time and money into a game that is just going to frustrate them and not really live up to the MMO expectation (a long term game with a large player base and regular worthwhile content). They just keep re-using the same stuff with slightly diff skins and call it new.',''),(1220,'I have played this game nearly everyday since launch. I really wanted to start a game from its infancy and see it evolve into a popular game and be one of the \"OG\" players. At the start there were a LOT of bugs, and gold/item duping. This is the first MMO I have ever played that shut down the trading between players and auction house, and they have done so on multiple occasions. After about a year and a half, things started to improve a little at a time. Season 1 and 2 were mostly enjoyable. However, Seasons 3 and 4 are getting significantly worse. Season 3 wiped the gear from all the prior gameplay. They made it significantly easier to get BiS gear, but significantly more difficult to make any money in the game unless you own territory which generates cash. Regular players struggled to make ends meet, the about of farming needed for materials for end-game crafting was exceeding 10 hours a day, and there was a daily money sink to get the items needed to craft necessary gear for end-game activities. On top of that, the best method of making money previously was selling gear drops from mutated expeditions, but they nerfed this so that almost every drop is now bound to the player and there is nothing to sell. It became a money sink to also do mutations because of the consumables required to do them. They also introduced races and have nearly wiped out invasions as they used to be done. The day-to-day gameplay is forced into specific 2-4 hour sections of the evening and you are no longer able to play how you want, when you want. If you want to push a territory, you can only do so for 45 minutes every 3 days at a specific time. Are you in Europe, Asia, etc? Too bad, you never get to do this content now. Want to do invasions? We only do them in large bulk 3 days on 3 days off, and half the time they are being reset or cancelled. As a strong company you can easily hold 6 territories and milk money from the server with this system as AGS has set a schedule for everything so you are never threatened by over exerting yourself. With the introduction of Season 4, not only was this the buggiest patch I think they never introduced, it had the least content of any major releases. They released new artifacts, which are just gear items that have additional perks. They released a new dungeon that is 10 minutes long, has the most boring end-game boss which is a re-skin of a previous boss, and features 2 extra bosses that also are just re-skins of previous bosses. The dungeon mechanics are just to run through, pull mobs into a clump, and kill them. It is brain dead, and boring. The only savior for Season 4 was the winter event, that they then nerfed so that players will have to log in every day to be able to get enough credit to be able to afford the rewards. This is their version of creating content and making their numbers appear higher. Many of my friends have stopped playing as the meta for pvp is absolute dogwater - everyone is in heavy and has infinite healing and/or CC so it is just a slap fest with no killing. Then they post a video of their roadmap for the next 6 months that has almost nothing on it that would be considered new content. There is nothing to encourage you to continue to play. This is like attending a school field trip where AGS holds your hand through all content, everything is strictly scheduled and there is no freedom of play.',''),(1221,'bought this game cause reviews said they\'ve fixed a ot of the major issues they had on launch but after playing for about an hour, i realised it\'s just not for me.movement felt so janky, I would consider the graphics \"okay\" at best for 2023 standards and the gameplay itself is so meh.so I went ahead and requested for a refund but only the base game is eligible for the refund... and the DLC is the more expensive part of the bundle...so I cant return this game which I hardly touched?',''),(1222,'After 1 500 h in this game, finally i will make my first review about this game :New World is the only MMO with a modern combat system in the worldu can play PVE like a modern Souls Gamesor u can play PVP like a Modern Game CO-OP Game that requires a lot of skills and has the potential to be an ESPORT Competitive gameand New World is the Only MMO that offers this, New World is the best even with its many flaws as an MMO.- if you hate Tab / auto aim, with 20 active abilities, and you love Action combat, THIS GAME IS FOR YOU - if you have only 2 - 4 hours to play in each day, this game for you, don\'t require Hard core or rushing',''),(1223,'its way relaxing than wow also you dont have to contend with activision billizard stupid luncherthe only problem i have with this game is i wish they cared about us Iranian players whom are stuck in our hellish country and playing video games are our only way of expressing some freedom and did not ban our ip adresses.you cannot call your game NEWworld then do something like this to a part of your player base whom are probably way much more dedicated to your game than most of other people from other parts of our own world.',''),(1224,'Hello community! After 143 hours of pure illogical engines and irrelevant quests I decided to not let them win. First of all I have encountered more bugs in the game than in my last trip to the forest. 1. Unable to finish the main quest due to the fact that the NPC will not spawn (this is not a minor bug like walking through textures. It\'s a major issue Amazon, a major issue!)- what is the devs reply on this? That they are working on it. How about working on it before asking 66,98€ for the full game?2. Unable to see the traps in the expedition.- basically I had to rely on my friends to tell me where to move in order to not be dead.I guess your reply will be that I have to change my system. I bet you this is not the case.However it would be again nice to offer us a game that is playable for those 66,98€ that you are asking.3. Now to end the nightmare, today, I just logged into the game, to finish the \"Season Pass\" which basically is the way they are saying to buy that f***ing DLC because else you are not able to finish all the cards nor to get the mount which is an asset/perk/mechanic, not an item. As I was saying, I started to play, and then, I found out the nicest surprise, because this is Christmas time.All my waypoints from the Wilds were gone. Sorry?Gone! Meaning I have to spend more time to reach each waypoint?Basically besides all the minor issues that this game has, i