 is broken. Every patch it downloads tens of gigabytes of files. Every minor patch the same thing. In couple weeks I have re-downloaded the the game size twice because of these updates. It is nice to come home to play and the game is waiting the downloads to complete.',''),(1231,'I can honestly say this game has so much potential but the devs or who ever is calling shots don\'t know what they are doing and constantly push out content that is either buggy/doesn\'t work or that players don\'t enjoy. From nerfing everything under the sun to making events that are supposed to be fun grindy asf. Just don\'t touch this. I\'m not even mad i\'m just disappointed that a game with such potential is so easily squandered by incompetence.',''),(1232,'New World, Amazon\'s MMORPG, offers a fascinating yet divisive experience that comes with its set of advantages and disadvantages:Captivating World Design: The game boasts stunning visuals and immersive environments, creating a visually appealing open-world experience. (Pro)Intriguing Crafting and Economy: A robust crafting system and player-driven economy provide depth and engagement beyond combat mechanics. (Pro)Dynamic Combat Mechanics: Real-time action combat feels fluid and offers strategic depth, adding an engaging layer to the gameplay. (Pro)Territory Control and Factions: The territorial warfare and faction system offer a dynamic and competitive multiplayer experience. (Pro)Exploration and Quests: Exploring the vast world and undertaking quests initially feel engaging, though they may become repetitive over time. (Con)Grind and Progression: The grind-heavy progression and repetitive tasks might deter some players seeking a more casual experience. (Con)Server Queues and Stability: Periodic server queues and stability issues at launch have impacted the overall gameplay experience. (Con)PvP Balance Concerns: Some players have voiced concerns about the balance issues in PvP encounters, affecting fairness. (Con)In summary, New World presents an enchanting world design, engaging crafting mechanics, and dynamic combat systems. However, it faces challenges in repetitive quests, grind-heavy progression, server queues, and PvP balance concerns, making it a divisive experience for players seeking a polished and less grind-centric MMORPG.',''),(1233,'Massive Pay to win due to the new update. It Locks you from leveling up without spending another $30. Terrible Business practice. If you think or if any Devs thinks otherwise..... well there is a game called warframe and it outperforms New world 10 fold without LOCKING YOU OUT. Warframe just came out with their newest update and It is growing larger and larger it has been growing for over 8 years and it has not slowed down. Extreme good graphics and story and game play while being completely FREE TO PLAY! It only costs you $0 to get it $0 for ALL THE DLCs and $0 for all the weapons and Characters. You can even get CURRENCY that you can BUY with YOUR MONEY for FREE VIA trading. It really makes a lot of games look like a joke',''),(1234,'Trap game. Run!!Was promised B2P! Dlc appears with barely any content and in MMOs, mounts is even a beginner quest that is FREE... and a free mount to make things less painful. but not only did they not release free mounts in the base game, even the ability to ride mounts is behind a paywall. It just feels like it was too tough to make mounts and they ended up introducing them in this horrendous and unprofessional way.Felt Amazon was respecting the player-base with the promise of no P2W but not anymore.. Season pass is another questionable decision along with the exp potions etc. I moved to ESO. It is not perfect but at least I feel the devs respect your money and time and it is up to you how to proceed with the game.  I feel New World somehow lost it.',''),(1235,'Reviewing mmorpgs is always a hard task.now i\'m over a hundred hours in and feel like i can write at least a halfway informed one.I like the gathering a lot 