 my save.',''),(1298,'Been a fun of the series since MH2 on PSP. I have been waiting to play this game ever since but was not able to because of being poor lol. I can finally play this after getting a job and it was all worth it!My biggest problem is the guardian set. It defeats the essence of the game. Sure you can just store it and don\'t use it. But the mere existence of it is sad. It just feels that they just want to sell iceborne and it feels not like the MH I know and love.But still 10/10, my fav game series of all time.',''),(1299,'the best mistake you could possibly make with your life',''),(1300,'I\'m writing this just want to annouce that Monster Hunter Wilds got trailer',''),(1301,'Almost 2024 and approximately 10k+ hours of gameplay from another account and I am still playing this.',''),(1302,'Don\'t be put off by the Mixed reviews, as the majority of those came about as a result of the final two monsters being too difficult for the average player to complete on their first try.  This game has 71 large boss type monsters in it, so don\'t let that get you down.  They\'re a goal to look forward to.A few years after the release now, and this is still the current definitive Monster Hunter release.  The Iceborne expansion brings the already good base game up to an incredible Roster, which will give hundreds of hours of gameplay for gamers of all experience.Know that the game had minor technical issues upon launch, which have been hammered out now that the final content updates have been released.  World has a large Modding community on nexus Mods with support for making the game have better performance, adding in Quality of Life features, or even new Monsters and Monster Variants to the game for more hours of content.',''),(1303,'Soloing Alatreon and Fatalis took over a month of my life to do, but were experiences I will never forget. Seeing their dead bodies finally hitting the floor after countless attempts gave me more catharsis than I have ever felt in my life.',''),(1304,'This game has to be the best game I\'ve ever played. I\'ve been hunting since 2008, and this release is the best one yet. Even better than MHR and all other releases after this so far. I completed the platinum trophies for both base game and Iceborne. And I enjoyed every minute of it. Now that I\'ve heard Monster Hunter Wilds is coming out in 2025, I\'ve decided to do it all again on PC. This is the best game so far.',''),(1305,'I love this expansion (other than the weird new save stuff and the performance issues)I think the monsters they added were a great addition and I loved the new area. I also had a lot of fun with the clutch claw mechanic they made. I understand the complaints about how tenderizing monsters kind of hurts the loop of the fight, but setting up wall bangs is super fun and satisfying. I wouldn\'t buy it at full price but if you own MHW and can get it on sale it\'s a must have.',''),(1306,'Coming back to this on the Steam Deck reminded me that Monster Hunter has always felt at home on a handheld to play with friends.',''),(1307,'Uuuuuuuhhhh Well. I really dig it. Kinda can\'t have monster hunter world without iceborne. It makes the game waaay better. More to do, more monsters, harder monsters, still plays great, new areas, better weapons, i\'m not mad at it that\'s for sure. A very solid monster hunter experience.',''),(1308,'Amazing DLC that pretty much doubles the content and adds some amazing monsters.It had a rocky launch, hence the mixed reviews but I\'ve experienced no problems whatsoever, if you loved the base-game, get this.',''),(1309,'This is the perfect expansion for a Monster Hunter game. New monsters, new mechanics, and new locations makes World that much better. The save data issues that led to the mixed rating are also completely fixed. If you want more Monster Hunter World, this is it.',''),(1310,'⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⡯⠟⠛⠋⠉⠉⠉⠉⠉⠙⠛⠓⠿⠿⣟⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⡯⠞⠋⢁⡀⠤⠀⠒⠀⠀⠀⠐⠒⠠⢀⠢⠀⠀⠀⠉⠛⢿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⡿⣿⠽⠛⠃⣀⠔⠉⠀⠀⠀⠀⢀