,''),(1361,'(first off excuse my poor english, am not a native speaker) this is genuinely one of my favorite rouguelikes ever, up there with the likes of issac and dead cells. The gameplay is incredibaly snappy and responsive with dashes and attacks comming out as soon as you click the button. The variety in your builds is also so different, each item has 2 inscryptions (basically modifiers that you get for having a certain number of items with that inscryption) and you can basically make an entire build out of each one, that along with the massive number of skulls in the game make even runs where you are going after the same build (aka a physical run or a magic run) feel unique and special.',''),(1362,'skelington',''),(1363,'I love the art, I thought the story was actually pretty cool when I got a good streak going from beating the game on normal, then going from Mirror 0 -> 1 -> 2 -> 3 in a couple of hours.Then I got to the dark hero phase 2 on mirror 3, died around 40%, and I can\'t seem to get much traction going again.Now, I\'m basically save scumming to learn the encounters(quit when you trigger Reassembly and try again), because I don\'t want to spend 40+ minutes getting to a boss to practice it. This is especially pertinent with the buffed adventurer encounter in act 4. If you\'re not already an expert at the game and you don\'t do well enough in an encounter, your run is basically over, so might as well just restart the adventurer encounter/map/boss if you didn\'t do it well enough. Making it out of an encounter with around 40HP is basically a death sentence, since you have to play extremely well to recover, and if you\'re extremely good, you probably aren\'t beating encounters with 40HP left.If you\'re not already amazing at the game, you need to figure out how to make a broken build, which is RNG and youtube videos, basically. I was watching a dark mirror 3 run for tips, and essentially the winning strategy was to get a couple early legendary items, luck 