wise i promise you will regret.Let us come to main drives without giving any spoilers;Story: You play as a character named as Arthur Morgan like any human being could know. When focusing on the main missions, you could easily spend between 40 to 50 hours depending on your way of playing. This is important because after playing that long in a game you just become integrated with your character, the other characters and the environment. Soundtracks: There are more but these 3 are my favourites;May I Stand Unshaken, That\'s The Way It Is, House Building Theme.Voice Actings: Just omg, i can still hear Arthur’s saying \"i said don’t thank me” in my head. Beside that, the characters like Dutch van der Linde, John Marston and Sadie Adler’s voices are so well performed too.Graphics/Visuals: There is not much to say about, it is quite good.To sum up, you probably have played this game before but if you have not, just do it!Recommended for sure 9/10.',''),(1450,'I dare not say this is a gamethis is another part of life i love itt :)))',''),(1451,'cried',''),(1452,'The ability to play any Rockstar games I purchased on Steam has been stripped away just as it has for many other people due to the ridiculous social club requirement attached.Below is the support ticket.https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3103521022You have a single account (for a launcher!?), anything happens to it and Rockstar deems you not the owner despite obvious evidence, that’s it. Your games are now rendered unusable. The compromised account permanently tied to Steam with no option to unlink.The only option being to repurchase all Rockstar games once again somewhere else if you fancy playing them again (remind me why Rockstar have any incentive to adjust social clubs current implementation).In GTA 4’s instance, it didn’t even have social club when I purchased. Rockstar added it in an update in 2020 (The same update which also removed content from the game due to licence expiry). In what wa