d a lack of multiplayer. Working together or in competition with your friends would make this game so much better.',''),(1822,'Game is all around great, but this recent update completely wasted my 40 hour save. It was corrupted and nothing I could do to get it back and running.I\'m very disappointed.Sidenote - Yes, I have already went back into early branches of the game, saved, then upgraded to the next. Still didn\'t work.',''),(1823,'190 hours in about a month and a half, the game is addicting. I have really enjoyed both games I have started. My first game I started on v0.3. For an early access game, I had very few issues. On my first play-through I reached a 50 million net worth with about 45 stores or so. When 0.4 came out I decided to start a new play-through as I didn\'t feel like figuring out what items needed to be fixed across all of my stores. There were of course some bugs on the new version but the dev team has been awesome about fixing them as quickly as they could even with the holiday\'s almost upon us. They dropped updates on the 13th, 14th and 23rd addressing the worst of the bugs.Gameplay:I personally love this style of game. A bigger city and more business would be great, but I think it’s already really good and more fun than most business sims I have played. 0.4 improved the driving which was one of my biggest issues besides the office-based businesses. Both were fixed which has improved the game and made it more engaging and fun. Being able to build out your various businesses, headquarters, and distribution networks is really satisfying.Areas that could improve:Late game:I feel like I am mostly just sleeping and doing all the happiness activities. So, it would be nice to see more activities and things to do in the city. I realize you can be very hands-on and design all of your stores, do your own deliveries etc, but I think most of us agree that would just get very repetitive and tedious.Character models:Currently not the greatest and maybe some love will be given to them eventually.Headquarters:The ability to move your HQ employees to a new HQ without losing your distribution plans, HR assigned employees, Purchase manager orders etc. Maybe a moving company could be added for when we want to move our HQ to a new location or something like that. Writing everything down when I upgrade to a new HQ is a pain.Add a Store Designer:One thing that would make life really great, would be having a store designer. It could be software you buy for your computer that gives you a new activity to do on your computer. It could also boost your happiness instead of having to game all the time. My thought is you could choose one of the floor plans and the business type. Then you could fully design and layout our store, save the design, and have the interior designers install it. This system could also be used to preview downloaded blueprints so we can get a better view of them before we waste money installing a design that we are not happy with. The current blueprint system makes it tough to see the designs so a designer could solve that problem while making it easier for us to design our stores before we open them. Having a lot of shipments get dropped off and grabbing them 4 items at a time with a dolly can be a pain and is time consuming. Closing:Overall, I love the game, though I do partially agree with a couple of the negative reviews that say there isn\'t enough variety between businesses as far as managing them goes.Thanks to the dev team for being responsive and quick to fix major bugs. Thanks to the community that has made so many helpful blueprints that have save me countless hours. Can’t wait to see what Big Ambitions brings in 2024!',''),(1824,'I\'m not one to leave reviews normally, this is one of the only reviews I have ever left for a game,  but this game deserves it and needs to get out there. I LOVE THIS GAMEIt has a perfect combination of manually setting everything up and idly watching your money go up, and in business sim type games very rarely is it set up so easily for you to be able to create a business and then have the money flow into making your next one bigger and better. Combine that with the fact that the devs have been consistently updating since launch and have added several community suggested things to their game and this is a game set up for greatness. If you like the idea of having big number get bigger, but having to work to get it there, then get this game. 10/10 would recommend everytime',''),(1825,'A fantastic game that is so addictive. Roll on the Christmas break so I can stop working and get right into this and start working. Great work guys!',''),(1826,'Game is coming along great, more content being added all the time, devs interracting with steam forums, which is nice for a change.',''),(1827,'Now this right here is a hidden gem of a game - insanely fun to play, and it can be as simple or as complex as you want it to be in terms of gameplay and running your businesses.The downside - its New York. ♥♥♥♥ that city. But solid game. 10/10 - buy it full price.',''),(1828,'Almost 24 hours played in the first two days, I might get fired in real life but I am making big bucks in the game',''),(1829,'Game itself is fine but it wont let me get past the quest line where it wants me to open a second business. The only thing holding me back is that it wont let me set the fast food store as the \"second Business\". I\'m not sure why this matters at all but it does apparently. Every person i see playing the game on YouTube tho just has it auto set itself to second business and after doing like an hr and a half of digging i cant seemingly find anywhere to set it as a second business. The F1 tab it wanted me to go look at just told me what i needed to have the business be functional and nothing about being able to set it to be first or second.Cant recommend the game with a flaw this big in it. I even tried restarting my save 3 times to see if it was a 1 of time thing.  Couldn\'t even find anything on google about it either. they just need to make it so you can easily set it as a second or third business and so on and the issue would be fixed.',''),(1830,'Really immersive, challenging and fun.  I\'ve been a real estate investor for years, and a lot of the reality of that world is in this game...large capital outlays when starting an investment, and needing teams to keep the work going to a profit.  Would like to see more development for interpersonal interactions for the Sim player, like a personal life, relationships and friendships, even romantic ones.  But overall, really enjoy this game.',''),(1831,'♡♡♡♡♡♡♡♡♡♡⣤⡶⢶⣦⡀⠀⠀⠀⣴⡿⠟⠷⠆⣠⠋⠀⠀⠀⢸⣿⠀⠀⠀⣿⡄⠀⠀⠀⠈⠀⠀⠀⠀⣾⡿⠀⠀⠀⠹⣿⣦⡀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢀⣾⣿⠀⠀⠀⠀⠈⠻⣿⣷⣦⣀⣠⣾⡿⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠉⠻⢿⡿⠟⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⡟⠀⠀⠀⢠⠏⡆⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢀⣀⣤⣤⣤⣀⡀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⡟⢦⡀⠇⠀⠀⣀⠞⠀⠀⠘⡀⢀⡠⠚⣉⠤⠂⠀⠀⠀⠈⠙⢦⡀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⡇⠀⠉⠒⠊⠁⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠘⢧⠔⣉⠤⠒⠒⠉⠉⠀⠀⠀⠀⠹⣆⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢰⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢻⠀⠀⣤⠶⠶⢶⡄⠀⠀⠀⠀⢹⡆⠀⣀⠤⠒⠒⢺⠒⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠤⠊⠀⢸⠀⡿⠀⡀⠀⣀⡟⠀⠀⠀⠀⢸⡇⠈⠀⠀⣠⠴⠚⢯⡀⠐⠒⠚⠉⠀⢶⠂⠀⣀⠜⠀⢿⡀⠉⠚⠉⠀⠀⠀⠀⣠⠟⠀⠠⠊⠀⠀⠀⠀⠙⠂⣴⠒⠒⣲⢔⠉⠉⣹⣞⣉⣈⠿⢦⣀⣀⣀⣠⡴⠟',''),(1832,'⠠⠀⠈⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠄⠀⠀⠀⠁⠀⠀⠀⠈⠀⠀⠀⠙⠛⠿⣶⡄⠀⠀⠀⠄⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠐⠄⠀⠠⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢹⣿⡆⠁⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⡈⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠄⠀⠀⠁⠀⠀⠀⠀⣸⣿⡇⠀⠈⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠐⢦⣤⣴⣾⡿⠋⠀⠀⠀⣷⣤⣤⣼⣿⢰⣄⠀⠀⣠⡆⠀⠁⠀⠀⠀⢻⣿⣿⣿⣿⣾⠀⠉⠉⠁⡇    ⠀⠀⠀⣼⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣦⣤⣤⣤⣇⠀⢀⣾⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⡿⠿⠿⠻⠿⣿⠇⢠⣾⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⡟⠁⠀⠀⠀⠀⢳⣾⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢾⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣏⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢧⢹⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢸⠀⠻⣿⣿⣿⣿⣿⡆⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⣼⢀⣴⣿⠿⠛⠿⣿⠧⢄⠀⠀⠀⢀⡼⣿⡿⠁⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠈⢣⠀⢻⣿⡇⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢸⠀⢸⢻⣿⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⢀⡴⠁⡠⠁⠀⠹⣷⡀⢀⡤⠖⠉⣀⠔⠁⠀⢀⣿⣿⢁⡤⠖⠉⠀⠧⢼⣿',''),(1833,'meow',''),(1834,'meow',''),(1835,'Even though this game has an overwhelmingly positive rating I must admit I\'m a bit disappointed. This is a luke-warm recommendation because, frankly, the game is very eye pleasing and some of the characters are fun to watch. To trip the silly robots or watch them dance is fun for a while. At the discounted price I\'d say go ahead and enjoy this pleasant little cat adventure. You\'ll find that the puzzles are of varied difficulty. My biggest drawback, however, is that the game is WAY too linear. Too many corridors where you feel like they haven\'t even tried to give the impression that you have a choice. I\'m not suggesting open world, but at least a few more ways of solving the same puzzle as to make it feel like you\'re not just following along a scripted sequence.',''),(1836,'Stray: Where Being a Cat is Harder Than it Looks. This game gives you the purr-fect excuse to roam a cyberpunk city as a savvy cat with a backpack. Forget nine lives; you\'ll need at least that many to navigate the urban jungle. From evading robots to mastering feline parkour, it\'s a catventure like no other. It\'s not just a game; it\'s a meowsterpiece. Warning: May cause sudden urges to nuzzle your own cat while questioning why they don\'t wear backpacks',''),(1837,'AAAAAAAAAA CATSSSS',''),(1838,'The intro was pretty good, where you were a cat and had to solve things as a cat. Then you get a robot that can do everything for you as a human and the game suddenly becomes nothing to do with playing the game as a cat losing it\'s appeal.',''),(1839,'It\'s not really that I\'ve expected a different game, it\'s that it\'s less of a game and more a \"narrative experience\". Which is, in fact, laughable, because the story itself is boring. This game possess no redeeming qualities, expect for a cute cat. The game is really short, simplistic and, most of all, boring for its price. I beat it literally under 7 hours, and I wasn\'t rushing: I tried to clear every sidequest there was (there weren\'t much activities outside of the main plotline though). The gameplay is the main flaw of this game: it\'s just a bunch of simple mini-games, like really simple, plus platforming, which was programmed a specific way so you can only jump up and down in specific spots. Yes, you heard me right, this is literally a PRESS X TO WIN game, there\'s no free platfroming. Moreover, most of the time you just walk from point A to point B.It\'s really one of those \"flavour of the month\" games which is only somewhat memorable because \"haha funny cat is the main character\".',''),(1840,'this is a horror game',''),(1841,'Each meow I did healed my soul by 0.001%. Now my soul health is at