ickly.Also, taking the high speed train and going +200kmph is pretty damn cool man.',''),(1985,'The best (and only) multiplayer train simulator.',''),(1986,'WHENEVER MY GF IS MAD AT ME WE PLAY THIS AND THEN SHES NOT MAD AT ME ANYMORE! cOLlaBOrATIoN!!!<3 -THE GF',''),(1987,'Amazing coop experience. The game keeps throwing different ideas at you. Some love letters to other games/genres included.Recommended for people who play games more regularly. If you try to introduce your friend to video games with this one, they might struggle a lot. Might be awkward to play this with your partner if you have relationship problems (probably).',''),(1988,'the chapter with cutie, the elephant queen stuffed toy, serves as one of the most violently twisted and viscerally traumatizing sequences ever written in gaming history',''),(1989,'A CO-OP MASTERPIECE.10/10',''),(1990,'Started with a friend, ended with a relationship',''),(1991,'EA/Origin link that breaks with no actionable info. This is terrible UX and EA should be ashamed of how much pain they put players through.',''),(1992,'Genuinely one of the most memorable experiences I\'ve had the pleasure of sharing with my partner. I feel this game was a great showcase of what a co-op experience should be. Truly magical in every way.',''),(1993,'ea launcher sucks ♥♥♥♥ and told me i don\'t own the game after i just paid them for itsomeone please alert me when i can own this game without using the god awful ea launcheri\'m sure the game is probably fun but dealing with ea isn\'t',''),(1994,'this is one of the best games to introduce someone to gaming and games in general.a deep(-ish) story, a LOT of different gameplay styles and minigames, an ever changing environment, tonnes of cooperative and a few pvp side activities.we had a lot of fun playing the game over the course of several weeks in short sessions and we can only recommend trying it out, if you have someone that is hesitant to try out playing on a controller or just doing something together and not have \"gaming time\" be a solitary pastime.though ♥♥♥♥ that book. he\'s annoying as all hell!',''),(1995,'My boyfriend and I loved this game! The story is so wholesome and the mechanics of the game are really great to play together. We really enjoyed playing it and even after hours of gameplay we didn\'t get bored. Probably the best co-op game we\'ve ever played! :)',''),(1996,'The game itself is great, but the EA desktop client is garbage. It takes at least 10 minutes to set up a coop match if it works at all. The rest of the time the EA client doesn\'t let me log in or it says my friends are offline when they are clearly connected. Don\'t buy games from EA.',''),(1997,'the worst online integration with EA play, EA is aware that friend\'s pass barely works for anyone, keeps closing forum posts about the issue with various excuses time after time and had no plans to fix it for years. I really wanted to play it, but I\'m not gonna dance around this ♥♥♥♥ for the money I paid to them, refunded. The game itself is good tho, but their decision to go with EA play makes it impossible to actually play it. Be aware new buyers, you might go into limbo of trying to just connect to each other to play. Steam remote play is notoriously bad as well, even on good internet connection, so unless you can play it local - stay away.',''),(1998,'To say that it was super fun to play is to say nothing. Had a really great time playing it with my girlfriend, following the story, and feeling for the characters.',''),(1999,'I love this game. It\'s absolutely wonderful, has great writing, a long story, always finds new fun mechanics.The problem is EA. I don\'t need to tell you all what a ♥♥♥♥♥♥ company EA is.If I wanted to use EA play I would have bought the game on EA. If I wanted EA play to advertise random ♥♥♥♥ I don\'t care about to me on my desktop I would have turned that option on. If I wanted EA play to collect my data I would have turned that option on. If I wanted to use an EA account to play with friends I would have bought this on EA.Stop injecting your ♥♥♥♥♥♥ launchers into otherwise good games. Ugh.',''),(2000,'Fun game to play with friends',''),(2001,'i enjoyed it a lot with one of my best friends , be sure to play it with the right person so you enjoy the game (:',''),(2002,'Very creative and fun, highly recommend. Always something new to do and never gets boring',''),(2003,'OK but for real, Spec Ops the Line\'s white phosphorous segment has nothing on the Cutie the Elphant section',''),(2004,'Instead of 1:1 meetings, corpo should focus on playing this game. 11/10',''),(2005,'Great game to do chores to while your spouse struggles on the jumping puzzles.',''),(2006,'i love my autistic blue husband who likes to give me blueberries, he\'s so very dear to me',''),(2007,'I wish there was a middle okay button, especially due to my personal experience. I\'ve played many farm games, some including Stardew, Story of Season games, Harvest Moon games, Rune Factory, and even other indie games like Cornucopia, and Dinkum. For single player I would recommend this game as long as you enjoy an incredible amount of grinding and semi-tedious work. For Multiplayer (which is why i initially bought it as up to 8 players multiplayer is insane and something you don\'t see often in the farming game community) I can’t recommend it. There are many things this game does right, the customization, and the whole magic system them-self is incredible, but there\'s so many little things that seeped through unchecked that you wonder how did this happen without anyone noticing.One grievance I have regardless of the way you play is how there are no sprinklers, while yes, you have magic to magically water your plants (which as far as I know we still have no way to see the grid/plants that skill will water) you will eventually have 3 farms to go back and forth to, and you are forced to farm to continue the story, which isn\'t a problem it is a farming game. However if you like to multitask, I.E farm in multiple locations you will be forced to transverse back and forth to each city and use your mana on a skill to water all your plants, every day. Sprinklers would alleviate this problem but I don\'t see them ever adding it. This issue is small in the grand scheme of things, but when you take into account the heavy reliance of magic, you can understand the frustration. Moving around quickly requires mana, but so does watering all your crops, now imagine having to water all your crops in all 3 farms and having to use mana to move around quickly. You can startt connecting the dots on how quickly you will sap ur mana, and then have to stare at your mana and will itself to recharge or take out your watering can and water your crops. There are of course items that increase your mana, but when you are playing in multiplayer (how I choose to play) you have to share these items with other players, which pigeon-holes some of your players into being the one in charge of  watering if you want to get anything other than watering your crops done. While this can be alleviated with having longer days (you can have up to 40 minute days), it is still a chore. Another minor issue I have is with the museum, there are so many things to collect (due to there being 3 different locations) but no actual checklist in-game that helps you track it. While yes it would be a QOL thing, its a QOL thing that many members of the community have wanted, and modders them self have come to fix the problem. However, I would never recommend to a person that solution to a games problem is to \"download mods.\" My main issue comes with multiplayer and the overall lack of attention and care it deserves. I am a member of their discord, and I have seen people asking for a chat notification when someone sends a message for 3 years, and we still have not received it. A modder had to take it into their own hands to create a mod that allows a notification icon to pop up, and god forbid you are on mac because that mod then doesn\'t work. it is quite frankly unforgivable in a multiplayer game to have a non functioning chat, and when asked about it many devs share the sentiment that they believe \"these players can use another software (i.e discord) to voice call\", or something of that sort. I personally have a friend that can\'t use a microphone that makes playing this game incredibly tedious as in order to chat with us he has to tab back in and out of discord in order to send a discord message, which also forces us to constantly look at discord to ensure we read his message, or else a message will go into the sunhaven text chat and be unread for minutes if not a whole play session. Another multiplayer grievance is how the story is essentially separate for everyone. The story says you need 1000 orbs to continue? Congrats everyone needs 1000 orbs each, essentially doubting the amount of grinding, mixed with the fact that there are no sprinklers to help farm in multiple locations, and you can sere how you will easily just be sleeping away your days to make it through the story for one singular person, especially when these story currency is also the same currency to actually purchase seeds to make more currency. When playing multiplayer this feels less like a cooperative game and more so a tedious single player together experience. In conclusion, for single player, if you want this game? knock yourself out, but if you\'re getting this game for its multiplayer function, I would advise against it.',''),(2008,'If you like farming community sims, you will most likely enjoy Sun Haven. There are some really nice quality of life improvements in it that I hadn\'t seen in the genre before (i.e. being able to change the length of day) and the addition of utility magic to do things like watering/mass mining/fishing etc was really exciting! I think there are definitely some things in here that will become a norm in the genre moving forward.Pros:- QoL improvements you don\'t usually see- Beautiful spritework- Music is pretty catchy, I caught myself humming along with it- Visual character customization is fantastic, a lot of species options you don\'t normally see- Lots of decoration options for your home/farm- Large variety of crops & livestock- Eating food provides permanent buffs so cooking actually has a functionCons:- Doesn\'t feel as polished as Stardew did at launch, but they\'re continuing to add content so I\'m optimistic that it will get there- I felt like you run out of dialogue with the romanceables kind of quick. That\'s probably my fault for talking to NPCs every time I saw them, which was possible since I had my days cranked up to 40 minutes a piece. But still I think a large dialogue pool would go a long way to increasing the longevity of the game. Right now I\'m in my second year I think and I started getting burnt out of the same-y ness, but that\'s an issue I\'ve had with pretty much every farming community sim.',''),(2009,'Unfortunately due to recent happenings in the community, i have decided to not recommend this game. Is Sun Haven fun? yes, sure, however (BIG however) the Devs have a lot of problems that they downright refuse to acknowledge. 1) there are no credits in the game. at all. none of the people who have worked on the game are getting any recognition for the game whatsoever, even after being put out as a full release, and having 4 large updates, there\'s no signs of credits being added. 2) communication for this game is frankly abhorrent. the switch release has still not been put out, they regularly put out updates with large known bugs and without telling all the updates, even though they hadn\'t put out a release date, so they could have worked on the game more. 3) (nail in the coffin) all translations are done either by computer or by unpaid volunteers, and one person who, besides being unpaid, has put a lot of work into the translation actually being implemented in the game, and nowhere in the game or on the steam page have they been credited. The game is alright, but there are a lot of glaring problems and i cannot with good conscious recommend spending any money on this game.',''),(2010,'i like this game a lot, but i have to be brutally honest. the art is such an ick. i hate to be that guy...stop using the \"its just their artystyle\" excuse for bad anatomy. i would like to see a portrait update whenever the lead artist improves, they draw scenery and such well, but characters are their downfall. there is bare minimum story to the characters other than what they are, a doctor, demon, a heroine etc. a lot of dating dialogue is the same. it doesnt feel like youre marrying someone, it feels like youre buying a ring...idk. thhe more i critique this game the more people come for me, but theres so much i would love to see as well as other fans that the devs just deny, they dont cater to the fans. the game is overpriced for the state its in and quickly becomes a chore, profiting is confusing. the achievement percentage for getting to fall says a lot about the game. i do recommend it, maybe once its on sale. its just not at the stage to be what it wants to be.',''),(2011,'Diving into Sun Haven felt like revisiting the good old days of Harvest Moon 64, with a dash of Stardew Valley charm. This game has its own flavor, and it\'s pretty darn tasty.The storyline is surprisingly engaging, adding a nice layer to the farming simulation. The RPG features are a welcomed twist, allowing you to really make the game your own. Sun Haven isn\'t just a copy-paste of its predecessors; it\'s got its own groove.Crafting, mining, fishing, and cooking - yep, it\'s all here. But what\'s cool is that there are more towns to explore, each with its own vibe. No risk of getting stuck in a farming rut here. It\'s a nice touch that keeps things interesting.So, if you\'re a fan of the farming sim genre and need something to scratch that itch, Sun Haven is worth a shot. It\'s the kind of game that sucks you in, and before you know it, you\'ve lost track of time. Give it a spin and see if it harvests a special place in your gaming heart.',''),(2012,'If you like stardew and terraria this game is for you! It has mining, mounts, boss fights, exploration and everything in between. Want to spend your day fishing, do it, wanna battle monsters in the forest you can do it, wanna challenge some top enemies in the combat arena, DO IT! I love the characters, and the amount of romance-able characters is overwhelming but so welcomed. Each character is so unique in design and personality along with quests to boot. I love the art, it\'s phenomenal! The music is great and i\'ve played this and not put it down. Genuinely not had a game consume me like this one has for a very long time. I love the farm animals you can get, the customisation you have for your character along with decorating your house and farm. highly highly recommend.',''),(2013,'1. The controller support is almost non-existent, making this game virtually unplayable for me. The game page SAYS it has partial controller support but the reality is the \"controller support\" is so broken you CAN\'T use a controller to move, select, go back, or ANYTHING from the main screen. 2. The text is too freakin\' small, and there\'s no way to scale it. This is a pixel game. Why have a HUGE dialogue box but make the font itty-bity?I can\'t play this. I wanted to, but those two areas need to be addressed desperately. After looking into the discord, online discussions, etc., it looks like this game has been out for 3 years and there is NO improvement on what should be BASIC accessibility for the game. What??',''),(2014,'Stardew Valley....but make it DND. BAM. Great success.',''),(2015,'A fun Farming Sim with some in-depth skill trees. + Interesting characters.+ A fun story line.+ Massive skill trees.+ Multiple options for completing the story line.+ Multiple settings to turn off annoyance factors.+ Adjustable day length.- Skill tree loses it\'s luster towards the end game when skill points become harder to obtain and skill options are less influential to game play.- 2 soft resets where you have to start over again with new crafting materials, crops, resources and currency.- Travel between locations start to become tiresome after mid game going into end game.- No sprinklers. An assistance mechanic is introduced in the mid game to aid watering crops but it is still a time consuming and resource consuming process especially as farm size grows and multiple farms are introduced,- Snaccoons! Cute and fun mechanic during the first spring to limit short cuts and access to certain feature, they quickly turn irritating when they block previously accessible routes and mechanics in later seasons to down right frustrating when they return to block things every year.TLDR: Not the best available, fully expect to mod some to get the best out of it, but much better than the current Harvest Moon releases.',''),(2016,'Hi y’all! At first I would gladly recommend this game, but happened a really UNFORTUNATE BUT. I know, that’s not much, but I played 80h in this game and almost finished the main story… but due to some bugs in the game I’m quitting it. My save file is lost. I was almost in the end of autumn in year 2 but today, when I logged into the game I noticed that I’m in summer 23, year 1… I’m so mad and sad about this situation and I don’t have that much patience to go through everything again. Also, I should mention that, multiplayer for this game is not the best as well. Me and my boyfriend couldn’t play it together cuz game wouldn\'t connect us. Just in case, I’ve tried to fix the game somehow but it didn’t go well, as I’m writing this review and while I was searching for a ‘magical cure’ for my game I saw loads of people who had the same problem.',''),(2017,'Very similar to Stardew Valley, but with all of the quality-of-life improvements you would want, as well as a unique storyline and style. The quests are rewarding and so is getting to know the characters. This game is also easier than Stardew Valley in that it\'s less tedious and grind-y, but the combat is challenging and fun, making it one of my favorite parts. I can\'t wait to see this game continue to grow.',''),(2018,'Honestly I love what they\'re doing with this farm simulator. Sorry if I don\'t have much more to say... I\'ve played Star Dew Valley, Rune Factory 3 and 4... and a few others. So the question you may be having is how is this game different from those games?    *Well they are seemingly adding new content based on what others are saying.  SO it\'s still updating.    *It\'s more magical based then Star Dew... and magic has more constructive use then Rune Factory.    *Race system and race recognition.     *More RPG then Star Dew.    *Seasonal hazards. Let me explain why this is a positive not a negative... First one I encountered was the weed monster that spreads dandelions all over your farm. You can deal with him multiple ways... You can leave him be and he will leave on his one accord but that\'s boring... you can challenge him to a fun game of jump rope... you can get help in removing him from the locals... or you can leave him be and use the dandelions to level your farming skill.           There are a few other hazards I have yet to run into but that\'s an example.    Stuff it still lacks...    *As of this post, you cannot yet have children with whatever character you hook up with supposedly. But from what I hear it is in the works. Considering these are the races: Human, Elf, Angel, Demon, Elemental, Amari(beast people) and Naga... I am interested in just how much work they plan on putting into the possibilities of what your children will look like. There ARE HALF BREED NPC\'s in the game. So they could either go with your race as children or a mix of whoever you get with. which would be fun if they do that.     *Gender isn\'t a factor in character creation as of right now so they may just ask you what your gender is when the child feature comes out... I suppose that can be considered a turn off but the character models are simple enough it kinda doesn\'t matter. The only thing this would really effect is whether the child is adopted, or if your character is the father or mother.      Final thoughts: It\'s a fun game. You can play it with your friends, it\'s got a nice soundtrack... There is a lot of love poured into the making of this title. So I give it a recommend. Get it if what I talked about sounds appealing... but most importantly have fun! :D',''),(2019,'This game reminds me of MapleStory and  Stardew Valley all in one! I love playing this game!',''),(2020,'I can\'t believe how big this game is. I find something new every time I log-on. The character development is wonderful and the stories are so fleshed out. Honestly top tier gaming if you\'re into games like Stardew. Obsessed.',''),(2021,'if youre looking for a stardew twin, here it is',''),(2022,'I get to be a little fox girl, harvesting my wheat, baking my breads and making my lil pies and it is everything I have ever wanted.',''),(2023,'Game\'s good. You should get it.',''),(2024,'In love with the pixel art and been playing with my girlfriend~ 10/10',''),(2025,'if you need more stardew this is good',''),(2026,'kill momster',''),(2027,'Gud game. Now give me Monster Hunter Wilds :)',''),(2028,'Arcadey Monster Hunter is back and I\'m in love with it.I liked MH World but I started playing MH3 Ultimate for the 3DS so I like the more colorful side of the series. Graphically it\'s obviously inferior to World which makes it feel like a side game.The Graphic settings are well implemented with RE Engine and I can even use DLSS or DLAA, which in World lacks of any RTX features (it has DLSS 1.x which doesn\'t help at all and the AA is non existent.)I\'m happy with the game because it\'s freaking FAST.',''),(2029,'My Insect Glaive go soisoisoisoisoisoisoisoisoisoi