he next game is better.',''),(2033,'Mother hunter',''),(2034,'They ruined Hunting Horn.',''),(2035,'Long essay review :lMH Rise+Sunbreak is my second MH title to play it to the end, I was 1 of those who quickly judged the game based on looks at first, but after a while when I decided to actually play it, might as well see it through to the end. My god was I wrong, the gameplay is just beyond incredible, I loved the quick action paced combat fused with the wire bugs mechanic, although it looks alien at first but boy does it become second nature after a while. Yes the grind can be super tedious but to keep it authentic, I have avoided using any forms of cheats and carry by soloing everything I encounter for the first time to feel the thrill and challenge and honestly I have always been this way since world xD. The scrolls mechanic(changing play style mid combat) made the game waaay more interesting and fun thanks to the DLC. I really appreciate the game for what it offered and I truly hope that people give it a shot, its an amazing underrated experience that many may miss out and I hope to see more of those monsters in the future title too ;D. - Side not to rub salt on world players: LS and DB gameplay is superior in every aspect and way in Sunbreak lol',''),(2036,'Me kill rathalosMe happyMe want to kill moreMe more happy by me killing more Me super happyMe kill moreMe recommend game cuz killCome kill monster with me',''),(2037,'love love love this game. Just when you think you\'ve done enough, capcom spoils you with even more event quests. You could play this game daily and still find new ways to power up your weapons and stats. It\'s so fun to play with friends and share the love for the game. I love how they\'ve kept making the monsters strong with anomaly quests/investigations so it\'s never a boring quest. I can\'t recommend this game enough, definitely one of my favorites. <3',''),(2038,'I hit monster with big sword, monster no die... why? I hit monster with big