nd the game devs being a small indie studio, they\'ve got a lot of expectation from boxing fans, almost an unfair bar to match tbh, because it has been over a decade since we\'ve had a real brass tacks boxing game. So keep that in mind. BUT, remember when I said this game is a solid base IF it\'s done right? Well right now the devs are not doing anything right as of recently. The last few major updates seem to bring back all the bugs they had previously patched out, online play is still plagued with cheaters and exploit spammers not to mention match making in general, at least in my experience, has been VERY unstable. Now I am going to take all that with a grain of salt because again, small more than likely underfunded dev studio, it\'s hard to stay on top of that I am sure, but it should still be addressed quickly and swiftly and not weeks/months in between waiting to try and patch it in with a new major update. Speaking of updates this is addressing the BIG elephant in the room, Back in September when they announced through the community hub that Custom fighters and Career mode were coming by the end of Fall 2023. Which did not happen, the community note got taken down and the devs just refused to elaborate upon as to why, they also have not provided any sort of update whatsoever as to the reason it was delayed, or when we might actually see those two very highly anticipated game modes. That is a BAD sign from any company whether it be from a small indie dev team or a triple A company. I want nothing more than to see this game and this team succeed in their endeavors but I feel as though they\'re running out of time to really impress the community and live up to bare minimum expectations. And because of that I cannot recommend this. If you are currently contemplating buying right now I would say just hold off for the time being, wait to see how it develops/if it develops, and then take a look at buying then assuming all the problems the community is highlighting are fixed. Don\'t get me wrong. It\'s a good base for a boxing game to be built upon. But that\'s all I can say that it is right now.',''),(2072,'I gave them time. Nothing was done. If anything, things just got worse.',''),(2073,'This game is on the decline!! Six updates have been released and the game has gotten worst with every one of them. Missed deadlines, over promising and under delivering, terrible movement, stamina is a joke, while being in their Discord I got banned for speaking what was truth (I could care less about being banned from a discord) my message was and is this.....Stop supporting these companies that hand out half @ss games and hide under \"early access\". Companies put these games out like that because they know people will just buy whatever as long as they use the right keywords or come up with a clever marketing strategy. Stop falling for the banana in the tailpipe and eating everything that\'s pushed in front of you, I too would keep copying and pasting games and releasing half finished games if I knew people were oblivious enough to keep buying them!! Wake up yall, like for real. (This is the kind of talk that got me banned from their Discord fyi) #FreeSpeechLastly, I don\'t see how Steel City has ANY good leadership in their office, most of what were in those six updates should have never seen the light of day. Project management and testing has to be none existent but again....all that starts from the top. Another company in over their heads? Incompetence?',''),(2074,'This game was great until 12/8/2023, then they made everything too heavy and slow, speed is no longer relevant, just sit back and land a couple power shots, what was a great boxing game has become a turn based fighting game. absolutely terrible,',''),(2075,'Game lags so much think ceratin stages just a mess, all my other games are playing much better,on  Rtx 3060, on any setting, only this game, dont buy this crap, game good but lag make it terrible,',''),(2076,'nope',''),(2