posed to 3 which progressed into colonial era.',''),(2115,'This is one of the best RTS game i ever played.In this game i can learn about history and also having fun but the matchmaking took a while like 1-4 minute and the matchmaking kinda unbalance few month ago i was silver and i play 2v2 ranked and i meet 2 diamond player.sorry bad english',''),(2116,'Good gameplay, good campaign, enjoyed.',''),(2117,'Mixed Review, while the story single player aspect was good, it is VERY short. you can not play all civ\'s in single player it is just 5 out of the lot. an example would be the new DLC comes with a variety of new civs to play, yet only a single story mode with one of them is available. AOE4 is mainly about \"pvp\" vsing other people rather than learning the history of civs. quite disappointing compared to previous titles.',''),(2118,'\"I was born to do this.\"- Jeanne d\'Arc===================================================================Age of Empire (the second one) was my childhood Game. I was really excited to play Age of Empire IV as the nostalgia kicking in. As far as I remember, back then I didn\'t really think much about the Strategy and just create the units that I thought were cool. Now... Still the same, but at least I understand which unit counters which unit now LoL.This game is not for everyone, but for a Strategic Game, it\'s fun for General Players. I\'d suggest you start from the Campaign first to get yourself prepared for the other Game Modes. The visual looks much more improved (of course) than the Prequels and the game mechanic is still as easy/difficult as I remember. The audio (SFX and BGM) is iconic and still lingers in my mind as I type this review. There are less Civilizations than I thought it would be, but still fun to play nonetheless. For people who target the Achievements like me, be prepared to invest quite some time, and I suggest that you finish the Campaign of all available Civilizations first then proceed to the Mastery while handling specific Civilizations\' Achievements. Save the Arts of War for the last because they can be really stressful if you\'re not familiar with the Units, Civilizations, and Shortcut Keys.===================================================================I\'m gonna give this game a \"Wololo\" out of \"War Elephant\"',''),(2119,'it is Age of empires. just buy it.',''),(2120,'Age of Empires IV: Anniversary Edition is an excellent comeback to the popular real-time strategy game series. The images are fantastic, flawlessly portraying historical details. The single-player campaign covers numerous civilizations and is fascinating and informative. New civilizations increase strategic depth and replayability. Multiplayer is strong, with balanced matches and a variety of game styles. Documentaries, art books, and compelling music are included in the bundle. The game maintains simplicity and depth, making it appealing to new and veteran players. Overall, it\'s a must-have for strategy game lovers and a highlight in the genre.',''),(2121,'if you like RTS you will love this game',''),(2122,'It\'s the old age of empires in absolute god mode. Everything you loved about the first 2, remastered in 4K with additional game, unit and UX mechanics, but they managed to keep the key aspect of the game, that fragile flame of player UX extasy we all felt back then, alive and well. This new game has soothingly enabled all of us age of empires fans firstly to recover from the barbary that was... age of empires 3. No further comments; and secondly instead provided a game with aoe 4 that is so pure, it\'s like a loving kiss from back in the good ol\' days of youth and innocence when we all played that very first age of empires 1 demo on 500 Mb ram PCs with giant screens, which consisted of crossing soldiers and villagers past a shallow river to find (and annihilate) the small red village on the other side... The magic you felt playing those first ever 5 minutes of aoe 1, that very essence of what makes this game great, is brilliantly released into the game for you to harness once more. It\'s glorious. Top notch to all the devs - you get a 10/10 from an old-timer, over here! #Respect',''),(2123,'verri good gaym, but as a casual player i find it hard to keep up in multiplayer with sweaty tryhards with their smelly 2week-nonwashed fungi bacteria infested ballsacks that can smelt from 50 kilometer radius',''),(2124,'Nice',''),(2125,'Probably the best RTS to come out in years',''),(2126,'This game really knocks my nuthair back. Nuff said.',''),(2127,'After 2 Years, Battlefield 2042 is no longer a buggy technical mess, its already improved on map, gun, vehicle, smooth buttery performance and overall gameplay experience, also relatively quick matchmaking compared to that disastrous launch.But its still lacks on contents and atmospheric maps compared to its predecessors.',''),(2128,'I still to this day think that this game is the result of some deep sabotage within Dice. It\'s gotta be. It\'s like the team went on a long vacation and let their kids develop the game. I never gave a game so many chances like I did to BF2042. I uninstalled and reinstalled it 5 times. Right now it is uninstalled. I wanted to like this game. I tried to make myself love this game. It took me 187 hours to realize that it was never gonna get half as good as any title that came before it. I am writing this review because Dice is now begging people to vote for BF2042 in \"Labor of love category\". Now that is funny. Make no mistake. Even the best version of BF2042 is stll the worst game they have ever produced. Ever. Even Battlefield Hardline was a thousand times better and finished game than this \"thing\" is even right now. How Dice and EA managed to escape lawsuit is beyond me. As many of you might know, a lot of key Dice people left the company prior to BF2042\'s launch. Even they knew what was going to happen and of course didn\'t want anything to do with it. This game is a disgrace. And no matter how many cool trailers Dice makes trying to promote it, it will never be a true battlefield game. THE MORE YOU KNOW.',''),(2129,'My friend who I play CS 2 with said if I post a review , and it gets 75 likes and 30 Awards that he will buy me a RTX 3060 and 1 Kilo of Lemon . So im just gonna leave this here. Help a brotha',''),(2130,'here i will leave the cat, friends who pass by can pet it and give it a thumbs up　　　 　　／＞　　フ　　　 　　| 　_　 _ l　 　　 　／` ミ＿xノ　　 　 /　　　 　 |　　　 /　 ヽ　　 ﾉ　 　 │　　|　|　|　／￣|　　 |　|　|　| (￣ヽ＿_ヽ_)__)　＼二つ',''),(2131,'Let\'s be honest after 2 years it\'s a playable and fun game.',''),(2132,'it really is a horrible game even for 10$',''),(2133,'TL;DR: Better than release, get it on sale. I pre-ordered gold edition like a donut on xbox before i had my pc, game was terrible.  Since then, it has come a long way and although not the game that was promised, its improved a lot and once again has the battlefield feeling.pros: The map reworks are great and have the maps feeling like a true battlefield instead of the clean and polished maps they had on release. The destructible assets are a nice feature.Portal (BF Era) weapons are balanced nice and the skins/charms is a nice touch. specialists are now into classes with gadgets restricted to classes.  Game is less buggy and more smooth to play.full servers!!!cons: Portal (the love letter to fans) has been abandoned, no new maps etc. Minimal map destruction.Specialists are still there.The game still feels like a large scale TDM in Apex at times.Vehicles are still annoying AF (skill issue) Get this whilst it is on sale :)',''),(2134,'refunded... such a ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ let down and i knew it! But i was willing to give it a try now after it has been cooking awhile. No servers is full only the rush redacted or what ever ♥♥♥♥ name they called rush had players.... and then i played that for 10 min and dear lord its just not battlefield as i know it... DICE go home you are drunk! will not recommend even at this price