t. Some people believe that it feels more like a DLC rather than being an actual full game. Final thoughts? Well, definitely buy it on sale.',''),(2668,'If you’ve not played Marvel’s Spider-Man: Miles Morales before, the PC version is an easy recommendation on Steam Deck. Miles Morales is a tighter and more focused take on the formula than the original game with better combat and a brilliant use of licensed music. The story is perfect to experience during the holiday season as well. It has been about two years since its PlayStation debut, and Marvel’s Spider-Man: Miles Morales has aged brilliantly. It is yet another ‘perfect on Steam Deck’ experience from Sony.',''),(2669,'Great game but I can\'t believe someone decided that a 6 hour campaign is worth $75 AUD.I bought it at half price and I still feel ripped off.',''),(2670,'The way he leaps off of rooftops and flips backwards to face the camera before falling into a headfirst dive is just full of the exaggerated swagger of a black teen.',''),(2671,'I cant recommend this game. First it has crashed so many times on me. My comp is solid, drivers are updated, I dont have this issue with any other game, but for some reason it just hard crashes often. Second the story sucks. God the main antagonist is absolute garbage. A person who is playing the victim, is way overpowered for being a person, and is trying to play the hero at the same time. Its difficult to talk about without spoiling, but the character is constantly blaming our lead Miles and acting like its all his fault while 100% being as much to blame if not more. You lied to me... but does the same thing. I am a hero, but blows up buildings. A literal walking contradiction, boring re-skinned character. I never knew the tinkerer, but lets just say they re-imagined that character. The story is lame. Third where the first game was way bloated with too many sides and other stuff, this is very sparse. And still feels too long. I am at a point where I am 100% hate playing. I paid $30 and I was trying to hold off until it dropped to $20-25, I should have just held off. I stopped having fun within the first couple of hours, but hoped i would turn it around. But even trying to stick to only main missions still feels too long. Fast travel animation is boring. Swinging is not as clean as the first one and where I had some fun the first time around, by the end of the main story of the first game I was already fast traveling most of the time. The fighting mechanics feel tight at first, but dear god nothing is more infuriating then being punched from off screen or shot while in an animation killing your streak. Also like batman, like the first game its punch punch dodge. You can do more, but no point. Additionally gadgets dont recharge fast enough. While sneaking around it would be cool to use the remote mine, but most of the time I have none left. Maybe I dont understand the mechanic that allows me to gain more, but its driving me nuts. The game is stripped down. 4 gadgets as far as I can tell. Suits are kind of lame looking and you have to choose between cool looking skin or useful suit. A ton of stuff to do, but nothing important or fun, this is very similar to the first game. I will say having the camouflage and the indicator that someone is safe to attack makes stealth doable, but its take 10 minutes doing stealth with a high probability that you will get caught and end up fighting or take 5 minutes to fight. Just depends. Typically I bleed the herd and finish with a fight. But in the end most missions are punch punch block/dodge. I found the last third of the first game to feel very repetitive, I am finding this just as repetitive and boring. In all reality the first game didnt need the DLC. It was a complete game and was already a bit bloated. The DLC was boring and every bearing. This game should have been the dlc and should have starting cost of $30. Honestly playing this made me realize i probably should just skip 2. So luckily I