zing experience playing this game. I highly recommend it for any fans of the Fate franchise or people interested in Musou style games. Preordered the Deluxe Edition when it was announced and I don\'t regret it. I was delivered a full and complete game on release day with no issues or bugs. Some other reviews talked about mouse and keyboard issues but I played on controller so can\'t comment there.Story: 8/10. Story was fun, immersive, and the endings were decent. I expect the DLC will expand upon the small aspects of the story I felt were lacking and will update this review when it comes out.Gameplay: 9/10. Never really played musou style games before but had an absolute blast. Enemies felt challenging to fight and were still balanced. Harder fights rewarded you with better loot and secret bosses were extremely difficult but fun.Characters: 10/10.Replayability: 10/10. Played 4 full playthroughs and currently waiting for DLC before my 5th.Graphics/Performance: 10/10 All settings were maxed out and found no graphical issues or a single thing out of place. Every single area in the game loaded just about instantly on an SSD.Bugs: Not a single bug/issue found with the game across all my playthroughs. Only a single achievement was a little messed up and I still think that was my own fault and not the game. Replayed the game 4 times on my way to get 100% all achievements for the game.I was very heavily immersed in the story, characters, and music. Gameplay was fun and interactive and I loved how the main characters interacted with each other. Figuring out the identities of the Servants in the game was a great challenge despite being a history buff.',''),(2750,'full reviewa historically informed fable which discourages reaching for the limitless sky. combat is pretty cool too. we love saber!',''),(2751,'I have over 50 hours in this game now and I\'m still not done. I\'ve been playing it on my Steam Deck and it runs really smoothly, although there can be the occasional frame