e, even during offline towers I am forced to wait 5 minutes between every fight now since it needs to load god knows what everytime.',''),(2894,'The price tag is a bit steep for a game that goes to black screen...over two months after being released!Holy...what happened to you guys?Refunding and avoiding you from now on.Fatality....',''),(2895,'Man, the cutscene\'s feel so beautifully made that It feels like you\'re watching a movie instead of playing a game',''),(2896,'KITANA IS BEST WAIFU NO CAP G',''),(2897,'Refunded almost instantlyGame throttles itself to \"30FPS\" in Fatalities, Menus, Fatal Blows and other features outside of the pure fighting. I say 30 in quotations as it actually stutters down to 10ish FPS between those transitions, and makes it horrible to fight anyone.I have a Ryzen 5900X and 3070Ti, and this problem happens no matter what graphics quality setting, or DLSS turned on or off.',''),(2898,'Imagine Warner Bros. Games was a restaurant. Warner Bros. That means quality. It means brilliant cartoons like \"The Looney Toons\", a cultural phenomena with characters like Bugs Bunny and Daffy Duck. A cinema giant with a hundred classics spanning decades of cinema. Warner Bros. uses quality ingredients. They wouldn\'t shovel heaping piles of manure onto your plate, right?Outside, it\'s a steakhouse: maybe it\'s Montana\'s.  \"Welcome in,\" the building whispers in your ear. \"We get you.\" A shiver down your spine as the warm breath of cheap, pressure treated wood hits your nostrils.  Finally, a restaurant that gets me.  Or, maybe it\'s the kind where a half-clothed man sprinkles salt through his chest hair onto your plate, and foils his steak in 24k gold. You order that Mortal Kombat you\'ve been craving. You know it\'s bad for you, but you like it anyway. But each time you go back you realize, \"this one\'s sprinkled with a few more turds this time.\" Each time you pay more, but you get less. Soon you\'re getting sliders: tiny slabs of beef hammered into waiver thin burgers, sprinkled with the secret seasoning: seasoned salt. When you put it in your mouth, it tastes like nothing. \"Flame broiled,\" says a balding corporate executive with a rotund little ass. \"It\'s flame grilled.\"You few hours later you\'ve got sliderrhea. You\'re 300 pounds. And it really didn\'t taste like anything: \"but it\'s flame grilled....\" will be your last words.You can hear St. Peter\'s bell. Until it goes mute and a voice whispers in your ear. A drunken, stroke-victim slurring micro transactions into your ear. \"Only 15.99 to unlock Shang Tsung\'s nipple-clamps.\"No, WB, I don\'t think I like green eggs and ham, and done eating your nasty sh*t I am.',''),(2899,'MK1 is a game you should avoid.  Especially if you played MK11.  Mk11 was fantastic and very fun to play.  MK1, however did away with the fun parts of combat and replaced it with painful combo mechanics, overly complicated support calls, and terrible controls. Overall this is a failure of a game and players will leave soon to go back to SF or to the next new shiny fighting game.  Don\'t waste your money on MK1 until it is extremely discounted. The good:Story mode stands out as a fun nod to the history of MK which is nice, easily the best part of the game.  Omni-man is broken, but at least he is true to character which shows a lot of care went into that.The bad:Online play is trash, abuse of broken attacks and the OP characters is most of what you\'ll see.  Just really boring to play against the same few characters.  Combo practice is trash since combos have been made insanely difficult.  Previous game I was able to get through them with practice and just \"getting good\".  MK1 has such terrible timing checks for combos.  Too fast and it won\'t even register the button, and too slow by micro-seconds means the move doesn\'t go off either.  That make that worse, the input buffer is garbage, easily the worse in any fighting game I\'ve ever seen.  Sometimes it keeps your input and sometimes it doesn\'t.  Sometimes it overwrites your input with the next move, and other times it does not. Invasions is interesting but not good enough to hold attention, and definitely not long enough for the high cost of the game.  Still no way to auto-skip fatalities in online play.  it\'s a feature people have been asking out of MK forever since no one wants to see the same fatality for the 100th time.  People just want to go to the next match.  So if you want to play online be prepared to waste hours having to watch fatalities over and over again.',''),(2900,'tl/dr: Mortal Kombat 1 is unreasonably priced for what it offers.MK1 is a 2d fighting game. Compared to previous titles, this MK has extremely few combo starters per character, leading to repetitive combat. The roster is fairly limited, which didn\'t stop the developers from locking 3 base game characters behind pay walls. This game on its own is not worth the $70, but if you want to play as the main villain? 8 bucks. Quan Chi? 8 bucks. Ermac? 8 bucks and unreleased. Even when you pay extra for those characters, they each have 20 mastery levels and two of them don\'t have any other skins at all. This game greedily uses in-game currency, which has no place in a 70 dollar game.As far as graphics, mk1 does alright when it isn\'t bugging all the way out. unfortunately, this game constantly bugs out. Variety of gameplay? there is none. My recommendation is not to buy this game or any DLCs until NetherRealm decides to fix their bugs and include what is expected of the base game and DLC. (announcer voices should not cost more than the character they belong to.',''),(2901,'Где моё детство? Игру установил, а играть времени нет :sadmoon:',''),(2902,'Garbage netcode, constantly forced to play against people with >100 MS ping or <60 FPS, can not decline ranked matches unless the ping is over 150. Both wired and wireless connections feel like trash when you cross 80ms. No WiFi filter either. Oh, and frequently you w