and the process is just enjoyable.Most of the maps in BOCW multiplayer are also very familiar, especially for those who play CODM. A sign of a bad map is when you get killed from behind frequently, and it\'s hard to find enemies, you won\'t encounter those issues here.The MINUS is that sometimes it\'s difficult to find a lobby, whether there\'s an issue when joining a game lobby or joining a friend\'s lobby, but sometimes you get a lobby right away and it seems like there won\'t be any more content updates for this game.Note: A moderate NAT type is recommended.In conclusion, BOCW is suitable for a fun playstyle, much like the OG core loop gameplay of COD multiplayer.ZombiesTo be honest, I don\'t play it, so sorry, and skip for this one :)',''),(2914,'Better than mwii/mwiii',''),(2915,'multiplayer lobbies filled with modders ruining the fun in this game but althought zombie mode is extremely fun to play',''),(2916,'Game was automatically linked to an Activison account I haven\'t used in like 5+ years and no longer have access to. Worst. Company. Ever.',''),(2917,'Multiplayer 9/10 . For me its better than MW. I love it!Zombie! 9/10 The zombie mode is very fun and its still round based which I preferred more. I wish they can bring back the story mode like the old Bo1-Bo3 Zombie.Recommended to buy! There are still many people playing this game. Just need to wait a longer time to get into a lobby . But its really worth it to buy even its for Zombies only.',''),(2918,'I love this game. the multiplayer is great the zombies is fun and the campaign though short is very fun. I highly recommend.',''),(2919,'Without having played a single match and an otherwise clean Steam, EA and Riot account and a link to my main phone number Activision shadow banned me. Support won\'t help, account is under review for several days. Perhaps the used hardware was HWID banned at some point, maybe an anticheat malfunction against ordinary software like RTSS, my case is unacceptable.EDIT: After about a week I have been unbanned. But no notification on this or why I have been falsely flagged.',''),(2920,'A fun call of duty campaign with varied missions and some new ideas for the series. It lacks the perfect direction and clear vision of other titles like modern warfare 2 (2009) and they try to replicate some moments from Black Ops 1 without nearly the same impact. The ending offers an interesting choice, but both options were unsatisfying to me. Still, It\'s very well made and has some really cool and unique missions.',''),(2921,'Its way better than MW3 that\'s for damn sure!',''),(2922,'Best story and good mp buy it on sale',''),(2923,'13 years has passed and i still don\'t know what the numbers mean',''),(2924,'The Campaign and Zombies are goated',''),(2925,'Among the recent Call of Duty games, Call of Duty: Cold War is definitely the best one to buy right now. It has a great campaign, similar to the old Black Ops 1, and if you\'re a fan of the classic zombie mode, you\'ll enjoy the Cold War Zombies. Plus, you can always find a match in multiplayer. Instead of wasting money on MW 2 and MW 3, go for Cold War to enjoy that classic COD experience.',''),(2926,'Yes.',''),(2927,'Its NTR free so far',''),(2928,'-- INTRO--It has been 4 years, since the events of the first game of the Secret series, both in game and both in real life. Time for Ryza and friends to return, for one last summer, one last adventure...-- GAMEPLAY --New game needs new gimmick, to separate itself from the first game. Last game it was the ruins exploration, now it is the secret keys. It is  a really fun, creative new system, especially since it is incorporated in the story, it is created by alchemy and it has a lot of uses. The only downgrade is the rng, but at one point, you can mass produce more keys than a sweatshop factory, so it will not mater.Alchemy system also got updated, with the keys and the new link morph system,and, in my opinion, it became the best in the series.The combat did not change too much, but it became much easier than in the previous games, taking away a lot of the early game challange.Unlike the previous games, the game became open world, with load screens only between the big regions. And to be honest, this is not as good as i hoped it will be. Exploring the game world takes a lot of time and many times, you can\'t explore parts of the region, because you are constrained by not having specific traversal items, since you get them alter at the game. But, when you return to said area, it will feel like, waiting did not worth it, since everything you can find in these areas are basically the same tier, as other things in the region. So other than exploring a new cool part of the world, it is not too rewarding. Another big problem here, is that the world is empty. I mean, yeah there are treause chests (with meh treasures in them), and a ton of monsters and resource nodes, but that is it. No activities, just some random, radiant quests, but they become boring fast. YOu can get some secret recipies from treausre nodes but that requires you to have Super Rare keys, so again, it just adds to the late game grind.10/7-- GRAPHICS --This is where the game got the biggest  upgrade. It looks way better than the previous 2 games, while keepeing the same art style. 10/8-- SOUNDS --The music uses a lot of tracks from previous games, and some new tracks. They are integrated really well into the game world, and it always matches the mood of the game.Voice acting, well, japanese voice acting industry is on a way different level, than the rest of the world, so from a game series with budget like this, it is expected to be really great. Both returning and new voice actors are perfect matches for their charaters, and put their whoel talent into makeing them alive.The ambient and combat sound design is also a great match for the game. As in the previous installements.10/9-- STORY --The story is a perfect way to finish the Ryza trilogy. Wholesome, cute, funny, and it takes care of a lot of things, that were in the air sicne the first game.My only problem here is the ending. Without spoilers, basically it ends like the second game. We knew this is the last, but instead of a \"The end\" ending, we got one that feels more like \"The end?\" or \"To be continued\".10/8-- CHARACTERS --11 character main cast. This is the biggest in Atelier history. Our old friends, from previous games return, with new characters in tow. Their storylines all get some concolusion, and we see some minor characters make their return too, though they did dirty with Roma and Pamila, by making their quests like just they are some random NPC-s.My biggest beef here is Clifford and Serri. Other than some mentions, we do not see them return, other than being in the frame of the epilogue for 1 second. They were important characters, especially Serri to the oren lore. They would have deserved some closure, at least in the form of a quest or something.10/8-- WORLD && WORLDBUILDING --As i said, the game world became much bigger and open world. So there is a lot to explore and a lot of lore to learn, trough quests and hidden memoires. And, one of the biggest update here are the monsters. We get new monsters models, not just reskins of the old ones, which makes the game feel more diverse and interesting.10/8-- REPLAYABILITY --This was never a strong point in the series. There is new game plus, there is a harder difficulty that unlcoks after finishing the game once, but that is it. Well, it can be good to return, and replay the game, after a couple of years, to once again set off to an adventure with the characters, but, if you fully finish the game once, there is nothing new in a second replay.10/5-- BUGS & SUPPORT --Sadly there are some bugs. Though, if you look up online, you can solve the issues, so there are no real, gamebreaking ones.--TL;DR--Every farewell is a sad one, including this one. Atelier Ryza 3 is a pretty great concolusion of the series, but, looking at how successful the Secret series were, compared to other entries in the Atelier franchise, i would no be surprised to see the gang return in one way or another in either a new series or in a Ryza 4, the aftermath game...If you are a fan of the series, you will have a great time with this game, if you are new here, go and play the first Ryza game first.10/9',''),(2929,'Read the community forums. No one can launch or play this game. It is completely broken on steam.Valve should be ashamed of themselves for allowing purchases to a game that does not work. Fraud to the extreme...especially putting this game on sale....',''),(2930,'If you\'re planning to play the new MW trilogy, don\'t bother buying MWII & III. This is still the best COD in the recent years and worth spending 20-30$ on ( at least compared to II & III\'s absurd 70$ pricing ).',''),(2931,'Amazing single player campaign',''),(2932,'just get this better than MW2 & MW3',''),(2933,'218 GB required to play this game',''),(2934,'Buy this game instead of MW2 and MW3.',''),(2935,'I own MW2 (2022) and now there is a free weekend to play MW3 (2023) but why am I still playing MW1 (2019) right now?PROS:1) Campaign: standard COD, approx 6-8 hours of good fun2) Multiplayer: on my way to my 2nd prestige round now, classic COD gun play3) Co-op: this is where I had the most fun - there are nice people out there still playing this gameCONS:1) Long waiting time in lobbies: approx 5-10 mins for multiplayer, 10-20 mins for Co-op2) COD games have a planned obsolescence so I don\'t know how long this title will be alive and maintainedRATING:8/10 - Although I got this on sale for €20, I would still recommend this title at full retail price over MW2 and MW3 any day.',''),(2936,'Singleplayer: -The plot is terrible. Just a mess of events. +Excellent animations. -Disposable mechanics are boring. Multiplayer:+ Great animations.+ Cool guns. + Good sounds. -long ADS. -long SRT. -Curved recoil from the weapon. -Curve system of modules. Crosshair makes ads bigger. What? -Sniper rifles messed up, only useful for campers. -netcode is bad. -64-24 tickrate -Delays 120ms -Terrible respawns. -Poor visibility of opponents. -Bad light. - Strafes don\'t work. - The jumps are bad. -Terrible level design, bad maps. - The compass is useless. -Weapon imbalance. -Handicap. -Donat. -SBMM.',''),(2937,'best story mode game ever',''),(2938,'Why release date is 2023 , when it\'s released in 2019?',''),(2939,'Got it during sale (Nov 2023). My experience:1. Start install, requires 250GB ...all right fine2. Install completes and I start the same, requires Activision account ...ughh3. Generate password for my account, password must not exceed 20 characters and must not contain certain characters ...yeah4. Games finally start, accidentally clicked Warzone which is not included ...woops5. Finally start campaign, game crashes 7 minutes in (around the time squad enters the compound)6. Restart PC and try again, game crashes around the same spot (\"Dev Error 6328\")7. Checked graphic drivers, yup I have the latest8. Uninstalled9. Refunded',''),(2940,'Call of Duty single player campaigns are my second guiltiest pleasure. I haven\'t played a new CoD since Black Ops II, and this is a review of the single player campaign only.I adore the original Modern Warfare trilogy. Mechanically this game is very similar to its predecessors, which are at this point over a decade old. The few advancements that are present are small, but welcome. Improved scope effects, the ability to mount your weapon on cover, and some novel night-vision sections. It\'s a mechanically competent FPS game, but so was Call of Duty 4, and this game feels an awful lot like its 16 year old big brother. It\'s also very short. Some of the missions can be completed in less than five minutes, and few last long enough to leave an impression. There are a few fun missions, but even at a steep discount I don\'t think you\'ll get your money\'s worth if you\'re only interested in playing the single player campaign. However, that isn\'t my chief criticism.The original Modern Warfare trilogy received some flak back in the day for its blatant and at times hamfisted attempts to up the shock value with each successive game. Going back and playing them after having experienced the harrowing nightmare that is Modern Warfare 2019 makes the absolute worst moments of the previous trilogy seem like a walk in the park by comparison. This game made me click through a disturbing content warning not once, not twice, but every time I booted it up, and for the first time ever I think it\'s actually warranted. Every level is No Russian. There\'s a war crime lurking around every corner. The game relentlessly ping-pongs back and forth between smooth FPS gameplay and excruciatingly realistic depictions of human suffering, and at times it even combines the two. If the cargo ship level from Call of Duty 4 were in this game all of the shipping containers below deck would be filled with underage refugees, and they\'d all go down with the ship begging for their lives as you heroically retreat to the helicopter.This game can\'t figure out whether it wants to be an action movie or a war documentary. On the one hand there\'s an argument to be made that military shooters shouldn\'t treat war like an amusement park, particularly considering how young their audiences can be, but on the other hand video games are fiction and their chief purpose is fun, and if it\'s not fun then why bother? And that\'s the worst part: this game, when it isn\'t wrenching control away to force you to witness some new atrocity, is fun. Never before has a grim treatise on the brutal realities of human conflict been so exhilarating. The medium is the message, and video games are for fun, so what\'s the message here? War is hell? Hell is fun? I\'m stumped.',''),(2941,'I just wanted to play the single-player campaign, with no interest in multiplayer features. Despite having an 80mbps internet connection, the initial 150GB installation consumed about three hours of my time. Subsequently, after completing this sizable download, I encountered another 70GB file that required an additional two hours. The frustration continued when the game demanded my phone number, leading to an additional 30-minute delay. Upon finally reaching the main screen, I was confronted with excessive non-game-related content for the original Modern Warfare 2019 game I had purchased.While I eventually succeeded in launching the Modern Warfare campaign, I encountered difficulty achieving a 120Hz output. Frustrated by the complications, I decided to request a refund. A smoother installation process could have significantly enhanced the overall experience. Despite my eagerness to play the game, the unnecessary bloat and obstacles to accessing the first campaign mission proved to be exasperatingly cumbersome.',''),(2942,'i am now racist',''),(2943,'Another great single player experience!',''),(2944,'im batublow',''),(2945,'-took some fiddling just to get the game to start-needs an Activision account even to play the offline campaign-assumes my mouse has buttons it doesn\'t have then tells me to press those buttons to do stuff-stutters so bad and so often I keep getting killed-seems to confuse which NPCs are enemy and which are \"civilians\"-cutscenes with the audio and video out of sync-crashed so hard I had to reboot my computerIf it\'s \"fixed\" now I can only imagine how bad it was at launch.',''),(2946,'This game has probably the best campaign out of the newer reboot series of the Modern Warfare games. It\'s fun and action packed. The multiplayer could be a bit better. I highly recommend gunfight though since a lot of the time it is actually based off of skill and not who has the better weapon. 7/10 not the best but still really good.',''),(2947,'Super fun and looks / plays better than MW3, how is that a thing?',''),(2948,'You either like COD or you don\'t,  played my fist COD twenty years ago and have played them all.Some are good and some are not this is one of the good one\'s.',''),(2949,'This is an incredible remake of the 2005 original that brings in new mechanics from RE2 and 3 remakes. The graphical fidelity is vastly improved from past entries. It feels like a roller coaster from beginning to end as you navigate as Leon across this haunted castle in Spain. Resident Evil 4 Remake is able to produce the best of both worlds in gameplay with both action and horror.',''),(2950,'You like thrill rides?',''),(2951,'Resident Evil 4 proved to be an immensely satisfying journey; thoroughly recommended from its inception to conclusion.',''),(2952,'September 30th, 1998. It\'s a day I\'ll never forget. The cop inside me died that day. And that night, Raccoon City was wiped out, thanks to the bioweapons created by Umbrella. Somehow, I made it out. But too many others...weren\'t so lucky. I was \"asked\" later to join a top-secret government program. Not that I had a choice. The training, the punishing missions...nearly killed me, but at least they kept my mind off everything. If I could just forget what happened that night - the pain, even for a second? This time, it can be different. It has to.',''),(2953,'Was afraid on how it was going to be adapted to modern gaming but capcom did a good job at nailing it.',''),(2954,'You can buy upgrade tickets as DLC',''),(2955,'Resident Evil 4 Remake brilliantly revitalizes a survival horror classic, seamlessly blending nostalgia with modern gaming aesthetics.Pros:-1.Enhanced Graphics: The remake features updated graphics, taking advantage of modern technology to provide a visually stunning and immersive experience.2.Improved Controls: Resident Evil 4\'s controls were criticized in the past; the remake offers revamped controls, making the gameplay more accessible and enjoyable for contemporary audiences.3.Expanded Story and Content: Remakes includes some additional story elements, characters, or areas, providing both newcomers and fans of the original game with fresh content and surprises.Cons:-1.Risk of Deviating from Original Atmosphere: For some players there\'s a potential risk that changes to the game\'s design, graphics, or mechanics may alter the iconic atmosphere and tension that made the original Resident Evil 4 memorable.2.Comparisons with the Original: The remake sometimes suffer from constant comparisons with the original Resident Evil 4, with some fans resistant to changes or critical of deviations from the original formula. Striking a balance between honoring the classic and introducing innovations is challenging and leads to divisive opinions among players.3.Unintended Changes to Game Dynamics: Despite the best intentions, significant changes introduced in the remake unintentionally alter the balance and dynamics of the original game. This impact the difficulty curve, puzzle-solving elements, or overall pacing, potentially diminishing the satisfaction for players familiar with the original Resident Evil 4.Overall, Resident Evil 4 Remake successfully honors its roots while delivering a captivating and visually stunning survival horror adventure.9.3/10',''),(2956,'The original RE4 is unmatched, but this one is decent too. The atmosphere isn\'t as \'mysterious\', and Leon and Ashley are portrayed a bit differently than in the original, yet it doesn\'t make the remake any worse. I might change my opinion later on, but so far the game seems quite entertaining.UPD: Missing some of the scenes/locations that were in the original. Apart from that, I really like it.',''),(2957,'Now this is the \"Big Cheese\"',''),(2958,'A faithful remake that sets the standards for remaking a classic, upgrading what made the original great, and expanding on it with new things not possible on old hardware.The story is still the lovable cheesy RE4 campy story, it\'s beautiful. Separate Ways is amazing and far superior to the original version.',''),(2959,'One of the best paced games i have played. Start to finish tight level design, great shooting. The depth in progression , weapons, inventory management everything is so well done. The level design , exploration , the enemy variety & complexity , puzzles everything was so varied and kept me engaged till the end. These are the perks of a linear level based game design which just cannot be matched in open worlds. The gameplay and difficulty felt perfectly balanced. Great job Capcom !!Visually the game presents great atmosphere and mood fit for the setting. RE Engine shines perfectly optimized , controls flawlessly a treat to play. My main complaint are the dialogues and characters. I get it that this is supposed to be a 2000\'s action movie kind of feel. But lot of times i felt the dialogues were just characters telling one another\'s name, speaking very brief 1 or sentences , never felt like real characters talking to one another. If the characters actually \"talk\" lot of the plot points would have been better. In terms of level design the island levels in later part of game felt rushed with mostly similar looking blocky buildings and corridors, I just loved the Spanish village and those levels more.8.5/10 . I havent played original RE games and having played RE2, 3, 4 remake I prefer these RE remakes over the new first person style and hope Capcom continues to make some third person RE games.',''),(2960,'The GOAT. My LOVE. With all due respect, I love the OG RE4 too but this is just on a whole another level!! Great job with this amazing remake Capcom. Or should I say, the *BEST* remake of all time? Ngl they did Ada\'s VA dirty, it\'s like someone is forcing her to voice the character or something. They should\'ve picked the VA from the OG, but hey not gonna complain about minor details here, she\'s still the hottest character in the series so...10/10',''),(2961,'This and RE:2 are exactly what remakes should look like in games.  Iconic moments kept and less impressive aspects of the original game (Krauser Knife fight QTE sequence comes to mind) changed.  Highly recommend',''),(2962,'yeh',''),(2963,'A great remake of an even greater game! Nothing comes close to experience RE4 first time on my PS2 (with by brother), in the Village scene itself, I knew that this was something different.In the RE4 Remake as well, the Village scene defines the quality of this remake, and I was blown away in the demo, I was blown away in the main game.Expertly designed, lovingly crafted, beautifully decorated masterpiece, well suited for multiple playthroughs with crazy unlocks (ripping through hordes with a fully infinite Tommy gun, in areas you struggled for ammo in the first run...nothing beats that)This, RE2 Remake, RE7 and RE8:Village are some of the greatest experiences in modern gaming, 2 great first persons, 2 great third persons, and these should be must play for fans and new players alike.',''),(2964,'nice. still i liked the old one better',''),(2965,'REMAKE THE MANSION PLEASE',''),(2966,'The influence Resident Evil 4 has had on gaming for the past 2 decades of action games can really not be overstated, it\'s template serving to create countless award winning games and franchises from Dead Space, to Gears of War, Last of Us, etc. And you\'d think with that kind of legacy, the devs would leave little changed, and many people before release hoped they would, but RE4:R somehow exceeds again in not only bringing RE4 into the 2020s, but making it such a blast with the new additions that are not only fun but increase the depth of the experience in combat and otherwise. The cinematics and characters, gorgeous. The sounds design - top notch. The story and the narrative experienced, ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ they fixed it. The games ability to juggle all of it\'s added features and keep it well paced - ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ astounding. It firmly retains the soul of the original but it\'s just better in almost every way.You simply gotta play this game',''),(2967,'THE GOAT!!!!',''),(2968,'caralho o wesker',''),(2969,'Since Curse of the Dead Gods, I\'m a big fan of this studio. I like their Mignola-esque art style, the enemy design, the pacing of combats, their sound design, and OSTs. CotDG became my favorite Roguelike.There\'s a lot to like in Ravenswatch, mostly the diverse characters/playstyles available, but I want to give an honest review about the CURRENT STATE of the game. I might switch it to positive at the end of the EA period, but right now I\'m frustrated and I don\'t want to lure potential buyers like a fanboy.To put it simply, I think the game needs at least 3 times its current amount of content to feel like a complete, satisfying game and/or proper Roguelike.They\'ve been creative with the open-world roguelike formula; I admire that even if the UX is a bit poor, but I can\'t help myself but feel I\'m playing the first 20% of something that should be massively bigger. It\'s quite fun to play, but in some way, it plays/feels like an online Diablo-like, and if you consider all the similarities with that genre, it terribly suffers from the comparison.The progression system is very limited, and the gameplay lacks depth. There\'s barely anything to unlock, and in two games, I feel I\'ve seen nearly everything I could learn about a playable character. What a shame.As I said earlier, I love their core concepts, but the experience of playing them lacks depth and variables. Playing the nameless hero from Curse of the Dead Gods is more satisfying, diverse, and deeper than all the characters I tried from Ravenswatch. In Ravenswatch, I can just spam the same combos over and over, more or less. It\'s very repetitive, I don\'t have to think that much about the fights or the builds. CotDG was much more thinky than that.The other non-negligible problem currently is the fragility of the matchmaking. There are dead hours where you wait forever (without any feedback) to find teammates. You don\'t even know which settings you should select to increase the odds of the matchmaking. So you\'re forced to use the discord to find some players currently available to play on the difficulty you want. It sucks, and I suspect it will get worse halfway between the major updates. Yes, it can potentially improve, but the truth is that it\'s annoying RIGHT NOW.My suggestions for the future of this game:This game doesn\'t need new characters. It needs depth and real variety. I checked the roadmap and based on CotDG\'s lifespan, I suspect the studio doesn\'t have the funds to support the game for multiple years of content, which is unfortunate because the game aggressively needs more content. This is why I honestly believe additional characters should be (should have been) DLCs while the content updates remain free. This is the only way I can see Ravenswatch reaching its full potential. And yes, I would pay for every DLCs because these devs are good. It\'s just that the game needs A LOT more to keep the players engaged.Buy the game only if you want to support the dev team. Don\'t buy it thinking you\'ll get a solid gameloop that will keep you engaged for a while. It\'s not there yet.',''),(2970,'I really love the game so It pains me to put a thumbs down but I also want the game to be better so I want to provide my experience.I played Ravenswatch completely solo and never touched co-op so my experience is solely single player and I\'ve finished all difficulties with Beowulf, Aladdin and Scarlet.The gameplay itself is great. It responds well and once you get a rhythm down with your favorite character you feel like a well-oiled evil slaying machine, but I have 2 gripes that slowly grew into a complaint that slowly made me enjoy the game less and less. First is the 3 in-game days/18 minutes per area time limit, I get that time is of the essence evil is awakening and the heroes must respond theme of the game but I just hate being rushed since I\'m the completionist/take your time in a single area type of player so being rushed from point A to point B to Point C is something I personally don\'t like, while I know people enjoy that choose your upgrades/items to prioritize before the boss awakens I wish there was also a customization feature to allow me to disable the timer and let me take my time and enjoy the view or learn a new hero. Second complaint is that most talent unlocks after the base talent feels weak/made some heroes weaker e.g. Beowulf. I finished all the difficulties with Beowulf using his base talents and I loved his base kit, but after getting his new talent that enhances his shield abilities I just failed run after run not because it was a skill issue but because I got his talents that enhances the shielding instead of the usual power/special upgrade to my sword swings or spin attack and I get that\'s the point of roguelikes/lites you\'re just really gonna get ♥♥♥♥♥♥ sometimes whether you like it or not but having only 2 choices of talents every level up and adding more talents you don\'t want expanded the talent pool really took me out of it. Aside from those 2 main complaints I have I really like this game and I\'ll check it out every major update hoping for at least a custom mode to solve my whining.',''),(2971,'This is a tepid thumbs up from me, with a recommendation that you wait for 1.0 unless you\'re really a hardcore fan of the genre. The game is mechanically far along, but missing some UI tweaks, story, tooltips, skill unlocks, map variation, boss variation, less grinding, better difficulty modifiers, and more that will make the game feel much fuller.You should be sure you know what you\'re getting too. This is a roguelike in that there\'s permadeath, but there\'s not a lot of random variation between runs. In Binding of Isaac, there\'s a chance you\'ll become god -- that\'s not really the case here. Instead, one run you\'ll have a better-than-average Power attack, the next run you\'ll have a better-than-average Defense. It\'s a bit like Hades, but with even less run-by-run variation.The main variation isn\'t random, but in choice -- you have a bunch of heroes to come from. These heroes are really, really well-designed and fun to play with, with a lot of interlocking systems and a high skill ceiling. The combat is phenomenal -- much better than Hades, in my opinion. If there\'s a downside, the lack of variation within runs means the beginning eventually becomes a bit boring, instead of exciting to see what happens.This is made worse by the map standardization. There\'s always everything in the map -- always two optional bosses, always three chests, always a wishing well. This makes things tight in the sense that RNG is relatively minimal (but still there) -- but I personally find it a bit dull, and I hope this changes in 1.0.You also don\'t feel in control of your character\'s development in this game. Shops sell \"5% damage boost\" twice, or you can upgrade a skill for 5% increased damage -- not very exciting, and not really impactful until near the end of a run once they start adding up. There\'s also no reroll system for perk selection, so as you unlock more and more items, you have less and less opportunity to steer toward a build -- you just take what you get. You can order how you complete events, or try to collect cursed items, but overall I was surprised at how little control I had.Similarly, there\'s no positive meta-progression, just potential traits unlocked, which is fine -- but there\'s also nothing else either: you don\'t unlocked maps, events, cosmetics, banishes, story, and so on. Right now, there\'s just a crazy grind to unlock all the possible traits for a single character. Several hours for each of the nine characters to unlock everything? I think they can come up with a better endgame system to keep dedicated players going, while making the unlocks faster for the rest of us.There were plenty of things I thought this game did well. In addition to the combat, the art style is nice, and the sound design (and especially voice acting) was really better than it has a right to be. But it tends toward a \"no fun\" design philosophy, with a dull map overcrowded with enemies you learn to ignore, and a general lack of vision outside their gameplay loop. So again, it\'s a tepid thumbs up -- but unless you\'re deeply interested in the gameplay, there\'s really no reason to not keep it waitlisted until 1.0. It\'s also not something I\'d recommend playing before other games in the genre, like Hades. (Note that I only played this game single-player, and so can\'t speak to how it feels in co-op.)',''),(2972,'great game, everyone should try',''),(2973,'I\'m pretty confused about why this game doesn\'t have more buzz. Compared with other early access games it\'s really polished. I like games like (older) Diablos, Path of Exile, etc. But I don\'t want to deal with lots of weird microtransactions, having to watch a video with spreadsheets to make a character, etc.There are so many lame time wasting junky diablo likes that are just microtansaction machines. (Diablo IV, Torchlight online, all the Eastern action rpgs, etc). PoE is slightly better but it\'s basically just a skinner box for hardcore players who can spend 80 hours a month (and the campaign is torture).This is just good clean fun. You log in, you play a game, it\'s really smooth, there are no issues (I don\'t think I\'ve ever seen a bug).Also, unlike recent diablo games, this game will kick your ___. You start the game and basically just die. It\'s not wasting your time. There is no 30 hour tutorial that you can play before the game gets slightly challenging. I started (maybe 6 months ago?) and I thought... \"this game is nuts, why is it so hard\". But the moment to moment gameplay was so crisp I went back for more. I had more fun losing in this game than \"winning\" in other games. And the cycle repeated. I couldn\'t unlock new characters because I couldn\'t beat the 1st boss for months. I now have everything unlocked and have completed the game, which felt completely unachievable even a month ago.(For the record I\'m old; I don\'t normally play dexterity games, I have a job and family, play infrequently and play on the steam deck with a controller; so I don\'t think the game is especially hard if you\'re really good at these games. But it\'s not a joke like the diablo games where you can play for hours without having a challenging moment)ProsArt style is really goodThe character voice lines are excellent (especially Beowulf and his wyrm)Gameplay is crisp and smooth (on steam deck haven\'t tried other platforms)Works great on controllerThe characters are really different from action rpg staples - the novelty is really appealing but there is no wizard or warrior or anythingThere are multiple paths to victory; depending on the items and talents you find different character builds work wellThe systems are a bit opaque, which gives it a surreal fairy tale vibe where I find it tricky to min-max (how useful is that lucky clover? which legendary item is useful?) it\'s a bit vagueThere are no bs microtransactions. You beat the game your reward is to play the game again, but on a harder difficulty.The UI is beautiful and uncluttered. There are no timed challenges or other junk. There is no meta currency. If you play with a character you get to unlock more things for that character and that\'s it. It\'s perfect.ConsThe systems are a bit opaque (it\'s a pro too but). I had an item that gave me more damage for each dreamshard so the run where I finally beat the game I was running around with 700+ dream shards. Was that good? Or should I just have bought 700 shards worth of items from the vendor? No idea.Needs more Content--Objectively there are a lot of monster types but they do get a bit samey if you play a lot. Some of the monster families repeat in Act 2 which made me a bit sad. Of course if you don\'t learn their attack patterns you will die so probably there is a trade off.--There should be more side quests (there is 1 per act right now) - they\'re hard, so a lot of times you don\'t succeed but some variety (where you get one 1 quest per run randomly) would be better--Some of the talents are overtuned (cough, laser eyes, cough)--The character who is easiest for old people with no dexterity to play (Geppetto) is not available initially; so old people have to play the hard characters first to unlock instead of just cruising around - j/k this is a pro',''),(2974,'Wait for devs to fix desync problems if you intend to play co-op',''),(2975,'It delicately scrathes that itch that was left by Dead Island Epidemic so many years ago... And, or maybe I\'m just this bad, very hard - which is cool and makes me more interested in playing and waiting for more to come of this title.',''),(2976,'game is fun BUT fu** it currently. a bit to ridiculous on difficulty and the whole timed crap where you cant just relax and explore and level up and go to boss when your ready and it forces you to fight boss after a certain time passes STINKS. the day night system is cool but stop forcing boss fights',''),(2977,'This could become the next Deep Rock Galactic. The groundwork for something amazing\'s there. Now we need to throw so much money at them, that it would be financially irresponsible of them to stop developing for the game. TAKE MY MONEY!I think the damage dealt and received feels just right. I think most people who are taking about the enemies feeling like damage sponges don\'t know they have to \"stun\" bigger enemies to deal full damage to them.',''),(2978,'Great coop',''),(2979,'Amazing visuals on the steam deck',''),(2980,'Great game. Highly recommend it. Now if they add a vampire character I would be even happier.',''),(2981,'good game',''),(2982,'monke',''),(2983,'This game has a great skeleton for potential, and maybe if you find it on sale, it might be worth it in its current state. My issue with this game in the current state is that it only has two chapters. Yeah they are tough, and at 9 hours currently, I have not technically beat the second chapter at base difficulty, but knowing someone who was able to clear it by themselves in way shorter time and discover that the rest of the game is just dragging new characters through the same chapters is kind of disheartening. I have played a similar game that had more variety of skills and more dynamic maps from run to run in Darksburg. I just hope the developers here keep with it and can add more to the game and surpass Darksburg with content and variety, but that is a low bar as the developers abandoned that game after completely reworking it from its base form.TLDR: Not a lot to this game outside playing the same maps on harder difficulties or with new characters. Keep an eye on this game and get it on sale or until it gets a larger update.',''),(2984,'I purchased this game for my son and I for Christmas. We were getting bored playing MWIII and decided to switch it up. We\'ve played some games like this. Raft, Stranded deep, a few other I can\'t think of. So far this is honestly the least buggy and most fun. It is lacking in content at the moment but I feel very strongly that with some dedication from the devs this game will be even more amazing. To be able to select \"easy\" and have a successful time playing with a 10 year old, that\'s worth every penny.',''),(2985,'Would I recommend?...Single player: YESCo-op: NOFor context: Having played video games for some 40+ years I am no stranger to early alpha games and my opinion is on only 100hrs in this game.This one has potential. Does it have glitches, quirks and WTF moments, of course! It\'s early alpha!Much will depend on how the team addresses current quirks and streamlines game play.Single player I feel I\'ll get my money\'s worth. Co-op it is NOT ready, go into it knowing that. The game breaker for us is that after some playing time folks who join the game can no longer access containers, doors etc. Also items the placed in containers don\'t show. Exiting steam and restarting/changing servers occasionally helps but the interval between it happening again becomes shorter with each occurrence. Just my thoughts, hope it helps, Enjoy!',''),(2986,'Overall a fun and interesting game. However there are a few things to highlight.1: can you come out with a few items like expert grills and advanced stove that provide options to cook/grill multiple quantity of food  as long as there is enough wood?2: some glitch during gunfight when both enemy and i cannot hit each other at all.  wasted a lot of ammo due to this glitch.3: can we provide options to build planters on the roof? it does\'t make sense to leave roof empty. 4: come out with solar panels and battery/electric storage system. this kind of items are common nowadays. 5: chemicals substances to make gasoline is pretty weird.  algae is a good source of bio-fuel....6: for single-player. it will be a good idea to have storyline to \"save\" some NPC that can do simple chores on the island like fishing, grilling, hunting and lastly fending against invades. that way. we can have a ease of mind going to further island to hunt for resources.',''),(2987,'Random people can join the game and completely destroy your base, even if you aren\'t currently playing.  People are joining games just to kill people and destroy their base and then leave the game.',''),(2988,'An interesting approach, but unfortunately far too many logical errors.Create a server, but don\'t give the creator an admin... The result is that there are hackers and nothing can be done about it.You can\'t use mousewheel in hotbar... Especially in a game like this that would be important.Foundations can\'t be adjusted in height... (if they can, it\'s not explained), which makes it difficult to build from top to bottom. But the engine can do that... the programmer can\'t...Stairs do not work on stairs.Getting damage from picking up sticks.Difficulty settings have no influence (at least on the raids)German translation is often too long and can\'t be read e.g. at the research table... Hover the mouse over it doesn\'t make the text pop up... but on items it does...You can\'t attach traps to some foundations (not on all sides)Ores that have been placed twice on top of each other.I could go on and on with this list.The errors in thinking are manifold and rather show a programmer who is not a player himself.The game is not bad and there are few bugs... but with so many logicerrors , it\'s really not recommended in its current state...',''),(2989,'Playing private server with bro and random bloke on a jet ski joins and begins shooting us.',''),(2990,'Don\'t be fooled by the glamorous screenshots, it\'s just an asset flip.If you\'ve played 7 Days to Die or Rust, you\'ve already played this game.',''),(2991,'Traded my Diamond ring for 7 cans of Tuna and 2 Pills! 10/10',''),(2992,'This game has SO much potential! It reminds me a little of Stranded Deep and that\'s why I got it. I bought it and I have enjoyed what I\'ve played so far. The combat can be a little weird at times but it\'s very manageable. I hope this game continues to be great. Gameplay: 9/10Graphics: 8/10Controls: 9/10Playability: 10/10Overall Score: 9/10',''),(2993,'A neat concept, but even in early access, this one is annoyingly rough. Gave it an hour, but now I don\'t want to play it again. Terrible combat, bad graphics, poorly designed UI, combat is extremely unsatisfying. Overall, this is just a bad experience. 3/10',''),(2994,'Pretty game with some of the worst combat I\'ve ever experienced. I hate that games can look this good and still have such bad mechanics. The character models look good but the uncanny valley is strong here. NPCs feel like mannequins. No movement, no life. There are games like this that feel better to play. More rewarding. Pressing \'F\' to salvage things or cut trees down needs to feel like more than pressing F. You only have an arm when you\'re wielding an item. You have no legs. You are just a disembodied restless soul roaming around pressing \'F\' to salvage entire sunken cars. Speaking of using items, why can I only wield one item at a time? Did my character lose one of his arms when he spawned into the world? I tried to equip my ax in one hand and the torch in another and it was not happening. If you can, it is not readily available. Seeing as you don\'t need sleep and the \"Simple Bed\" costs more materials than i ever had on me I just found myself waiting in the dark until the sun came back up so I could jump back in the water and dig around in trash. As for survival mechanics, You get hungry and thirsty and will die if you run out of air. You don\'t need to sleep as far as I could tell though I never actually slept, I just played for several in-game days straight. Hopefully it passes time or at the very least restores your health bar but I can\'t say it does either of those. When you\'re injured you can make bandages for immediate use but the cost in cloth is too expensive. You got a stamina bar. It works as intended. Cooking is fine. Nothing to it, just throw the food on the grill and forget about it. It doesn\'t burn and once its done it becomes lootable. Not rewarding. Researching things requires specific materials, once you have them you can immediately research a new item. Doesn\'t feel rewarding. Base building has the basic snapping square grid system seen in other games like this. The exception is that you cannot flatten the land to build, their attempt at working around this was to create foundations that work fine but again, this is done better in other games. Most rewarding aspect. I requested a refund after I farmed up materials to make a row boat thing. I get on it and start rowing and this giant ugly interface pops up as an overlay and shows me the controls for operation. Suddenly, my screen is cluttered just to tell me to press \'WSAD\' to move directions. It doesn\'t go away its just there and to make matters worse, the sound effects used to row are grating. In a game about being a survivor in Waterworld you would think the boat driving mechanics would feel responsive. Valheim does this far better. So, I row my boat up to the little trader lady\'s floating shop and make a few trades in their pleasing trading and bartering system. I buy what I need and sell some trash and I\'m ready to bounce back to the cribbo. I hustle back to my parked rowboat and hop back in. I parked it facing the trader\'s shop but far enough away to just turn around...or so I thought. However, as I turned left and began to row the boat was suddenly caught by the undertow riptide of a glitch that pulled me and my rowboat under the shop and permanently stuck looking at the trader\'s massive mommy milker\'s upside down through the clipped floor she was standing on. That\'s when I checked the time on how long I had been playing and it read 99 minutes. I really like that there are vendors and NPCs and enemies. But it all feels so skeletal. Like 25% of a great idea realized. It\'s a shame too because it has a lot of great ideas. Cut down the price and refine the gameplay a lot. Combat sucks so bad. Tasks are boring to do. Sea is empty very little life. Or just try again with a sequel if that\'s too much to do.',''),(2995,'Has more variety of POI\'s than Starfield.',''),(2996,'This game is like OLD rust vs NPC\'s.Honestly, it\'s pretty bad, kinda like a college student project sort of thing, god knows why it\'s so positively reviewed.',''),(2997,'Probably a fun game if the multiplayer worked... After around 4 hours container were bugged and could not be opened. Even worse after restarting the game the whole base was erased only the bugged chest was floating in the air.... well probably another dead game in my library',''),(2998,'My brother Gwaak and I have been checking this one out recently. It\'s really good, it has a Subnautica meets 7 days to die vibe (in a good way haha). It\'s still in early access, but the development