perience these sports first hand and it\'s not even difficult to get used to it overall. Graphics looks okay, controller support is pretty good and the story mode which is called Breaking Point, is enjoyable in my opinion. The multiplayer is alive, and there is even a multiplayer car upgrading part of F1 23, where you can get parts and members to your team and use their abilities in your races, this is called F1 World. It can give you challanges, where you can get additional parts, resources to upgrade and craft these componenets and collectibles, which can give some challanges for some of the players. There is of course the regular multiplayer racing with the well known F1 and F2 teams. The game however does have some bugs, which can make your races annoying or even break it completely, not even mentioning the unstable EA servers which can make your multiplayer experience horrible, due to the lag or desync issues, sometimes even disconnecting the player. Also, F1 World content feels compeletly useless, if you only want to do multiplayer races without any collecting.In my opinion F1 23 has its ups and downs and from a more casual point of view this is a likeable game, however it still has some old bugs and new issues which makes the game a bit disappointing, but I think you should give it a chance for around 30 - 25 €.',''),(3007,'TU TU TU MAX VERSTAPPEN',''),(3008,'Maybe the best Formula 1 game I\'ve played. The braking point 2, career mode... are much better than previous generations. Well, Codemasters, hope their next game can bring us more surprises.',''),(3009,'\"Tututudu Max Verstappen\"-me when doing last to first challenge with difficulty 20 ai (I used rewind only 154 times in 5 lap race: Great Success!)',''),(3010,'Good game add sex',''),(3011,'MAX! MAX! MAX! Super MAX!MAX! MAX! MAX! Super MAX!MAX! MAX! MAX! Super MAX!MAX! MAX! MAX! Super MAX!MAX! MAX! MAX! Super MAX!',''),(3012,'honestly game aint that bad( i have 63 hours... so it clearly can\'t be that bad) but the ai sucks donkey ♥♥♥♥ and the tire model is even worse, also why tf do I get spun by an ai and then I get a warning for a collision, doesn\'t make any sense, perchance?',''),(3013,'Worst VR in racing genre, developers have dropped fixing and updating the game.',''),(3014,'Max Verstappen won every race in my career mode 10/10',''),(3015,'Would I recommend this game?I would not recommend this game, primarily for this reason – it is brutally inconsistent.Background: I’ve been playing racing games since the 1990’s (yes, I’m an old git!). I’ve played most of the F1 games over the years. Just for context, I may be 70 but I was involved in ‘real’ motorsport from my teens – and quite good. On the computer (I have a very decent rig and high-end PC) I’ve got very close to world records. This week I recorded a pole lap of 1:16.62 in Australia (now my 3rd full season in F1 23), which ain’t too shabby I think. I have competed in thousands of races and I’m now at 243 hrs in F1 23. All this is said to hopefully indicate I ought to know how to race (but I know many will have laughed at a 70-year-old racer! I understand).Now to F1 23. Like many I found the cars in F1 22 very tricky to drive, very understeery and the A.I.  ‘challenging’. These issues were said to be resolved in F1 23; that was my experience when I began racing in F1 23. Initially I found it a joy compared to F1 22. That was for my first two 23 race seasons.Bizarrely, I’ve just completed 3 races in a 3rd season, and the car is behaving differently. It feels, oddly, as if F1 22 characteristics have crept back in. Less predictable handling and more understeer – and my set-ups are well developed and work. Also, the A.I. seem to have become more erratic again. They are set to 70, which I know is not very high, but age has its limitations!And just to cap what had been a very challenging Australian GP – in this 3rd series – the car suffered a sudden terminal failure of the MGU-K. That means a total DNF failure during only the 3rd race!! That has never happened to me before in the huge number of races I’ve competed in. There was no warning (other than just before the actual failure) and I had checked all car systems status before the race. All OK. As for the cars status, I have all ‘Performance’ (& durability) mods maxed out, all ‘Facilities’ mods maxed out and morale is ‘High’ in all depts. But that all seems to count for nothing in terms of durability if the car breaks after less than 3 races completed!My experiences in F1 23 during these first 3 races into my 3rd season have drained me of enthusiasm for this game. A huge disappointment after what had seems a promising improvement after F1 22.',''),(3016,'Waste of money. Don\'t buy this garbage. My 2 year old niece make better decisions than the AI in this piece of trash of a game.',''),(3017,'Could add sex with leclerc but still a 10/10 game',''),(3018,'du du du du max verstappen du du du du max verstappen du du du du max verstappen du du du du max verstappen du du du du max verstappen',''),(3019,'Country miles better than last year\'s game',''),(3020,'Superb visuals, white knuckle racing, and technical courses. Everything we wish Forza had on PC. Playing on a Wolverine Razer V2 controller the game feels great. Will be best played with a wheel and racing sim setup though. Love the presentation and visuals. It feels like you are in an episode of Drive to Survive on Netflix. AI is also unforgiving and with in depth difficulty and assist settings you can tweak pretty much everything to  your liking to create an enjoyable experience. The driver AI is also pretty based. I have had some epic duels with Hamilton in career and some photo finishes with Alonso. Think is a must have racing game for any fan of the genre. Coop Career is a blast with a friend as well! I would give it a 9/10!!',''),(3021,'I keep discovering new bugs in this game, whether it\'s randomly losing FFB on specific tracks or the UI randomly acting as if buttons are being pushed. Combine that with an over-emphasis on microtransactions and an online experience full of trolls, this game is just not worth the $$.',''),(3022,'this is a great revamping of the earlier F1-21 version. On sale and a beautiful game. Very fun and highly recommend this version of F1.',''),(3023,'The AI in this game is horrible.  Will constantly crash into you and make you lose races.  THANK GOD I ONLY PAID $21 FOR IT!',''),(3024,'This game is so close to being amazing and it kills me. There are a few things that prevent it from reaching the heights of greatness:- Your units can only shoot in A SINGLE DIRECTION from trenches, meaning if you capture an enemy trench, your soldiers will face YOUR TRENCHES and will be unable to shoot at enemy troops. This is utterly unacceptable in a game based on trench warfare. Until this issue is fixed my review will remain negative.- Suppressive barrage prevents ALL firing. Instead they should reduce firing efficiency, not prevent your men from shooting entirely.- Speaking of firing, it should be much easier to tell if your units are actually shooting. Sometimes I will see the target icon appear but I can\'t tell who or where they are shooting. Sometimes it doesn\'t even look like they are at all.- Battalions get wiped out WAY too quickly. This is partially justified because WWI, but even at the beginning of the game when it\'s entirely bolt action rifles your battalions will be destroyed in a matter of seconds.- There is no way to undo an order on the campaign map, leading to one misclick quite literally having the potential to ruin your entire game.The first issue is paramount and I am kind of miffed at why the game has been out for nine months and it still hasn\'t been fixed. It really sucks because there really are no good WWI RTS games on the market. I want this game to succeed.',''),(3025,'TLDR; The battle AI is bad, battles are hyper repetitive, and you can win WWI in 1915 without trying too hard. If I could give a \'mixed\' review, I would. Battles take place on what can charitably be called 10 maps, which is a problem because there *is* a dominant strategy. If you know anything about WWI, you know that sitting in your trench and *never attacking* is the correct move. To its credit, this game gets correct in a neat historical fashion. The problem is that you learn to just sit back and let the enemy fight into you, even when you are attacking. Yes. This is how WWI was fought, but it doesn\'t make for interesting gameplay. I got to thinking about this and began wondering if there even *is* a way to make a WWI RTS game *fun*. WWII games can be fun often due to the volatility of the situation. WWI is so static that even major advantages on either side were often nullified by virtue of trenches with modern rifles being historically defensible.Also, the game macroeconomy is kind of terrible? Like, I played as the Entente and won the game in 1915 (!) by bankrupting Germany (!!) because the AI kept attacking me over and over. I didn\'t need tanks, gas shells, aircraft, or even infantry helmets. The AI is so terrible at battle tactics that it burns through all of its macroeconomic power in... 4 battles? 5?The concept of a cool game is here, but this one just fails to live up.',''),(3026,'TOTAL INFANTRY DEATH',''),(3027,'love playing the game  only changes I would like to see are, starting the war earlier and to have more unit types.',''),(3028,'Become a WW1 commander in this trench warfare game with the worst intro to Trench warfare since.. well..Trench warfare.✔️ Tackles a genre that is not commonly done.❓If you absolutely love the logistics of trench planning you MIGHT enjoy this. This is not a combat focused game but is an insanely complicated planning game. ❌ INSANELY overpriced.❌ The tutorial might be the WORST tutorial i have ever seen, it is SO confusing, so much information is thrown at the player every 10 seconds a new important mechanic is shown, it takes 10 mins to even get to the battle screen and then you are presented with a complete mess of a UI, at this point i called it a day and refunded.',''),(3029,'It is interesting to play a game focused on WW1 instead of WW2.  I enjoyed the strategy of sending columns of men into trenches and using artillery to suppress enemy fire (allowing you to reach the trench).  It is a different kind of tactic, and one I found fun.  The game also has a lot of historical references that means that I an learning about history at the same time I am enjoying the game.The game seems to have a lot of replayability.  The first 2 campaigns, I focused on super soldiers to help me reach and win in the trenches.  In my next playthrough, I focused on gas attacks via artillery (aka mustard gas), and found that to be a very effective way to win.  I have barely scratched air craft and tanks, so hopefully that gives me even more hours of fun.My biggest complaint is the game focuses too much on the \"Great Victory\" to take land in the game.  I would rather that even minor victories move you closer to your goal, even if it took a lot of them.  I would also prefer if the goals assigned to you were toned down a bit.  Instead of being told to take X territory, I would rather decide for myself which territory is a priority.  The territory goals seem to be the same for each play-through, so you either forgo the bonuses or you keep following the same routes to attack.',''),(3030,'An absolute hidden gem. They really shoud ditch Denuvo and allow people to try it through a demo before buying. It is worth it full price, however.',''),(3031,'all hail the ultimate game performance killer (The Denuvo).  quite a good game but..... performance is terrible......i want refund.... better spend my money on something else',''),(3032,'It\'s a very simplistic game, with AI that is so unbelievably inept that the historical strategy of \"throw a bunch of men at them mindlessly\" will ensure you win every time.',''),(3033,'It feels slow, AI is garbage, Devs have given up. Don\'t buy.',''),(3034,'I really wanted to like this game, followed it for a while, and snagged it on sale. It was just not very fun. The UI is not very intuitive. The graphics are ok, it has a charming color palette. The main problem with this is the AI. It seems the AI isn\'t effected by LOS or fog of war, and immediately knows the weakest part of your defenses to attack, both in battle and campaign map. Very disappointing this turned out this way, as there aren\'t nearly enough games made from this time period.',''),(3035,'After 10 years I\'m finally caught up with Trails.',''),(3036,'Great game but the older I get, the less I can play games like this. To be honest, it\'s just too difficult for me.',''),(3037,'I know Kung Fu',''),(3038,'Positives: + Excellent fast-paced combat system. + Rewarding game design. + Fluid animations. + A steep learning curve but with a sense of mastery and satisfaction when you manage to complete all the moves and counterattacks. + Interesting death system.Negatives: - Mediocre and overly repeated phrases. - The camera isn\'t perfect. - You can finish the \"story\" part in a very short amount of time and the arena challenges are getting tedious.',''),(3039,'god hand is never coming back, so we have god hand at home',''),(3040,'Sifu is one of those games that impressed me a lot with its art direction, action set pieces and the vibe of Hong Kong Kung Fu flicks. The lore is nothing to write laurels about but gets the job done. The strength of the game is the core gameplay loop with fluid action set pieces where something badass is always happening and its the player controlling the character doing it, not a prerendered cutscene.The game has five different stages excluding the prologue and has a ton of replay value. Each stage is visually distinct as well as feature variety of enemy types. The stages offers a level of lore connectivity that makes replaying the same level albeit with a collectible from a future stage give more lore into the individual bosses as well as the overarching story.The tutorial of the game does a not so good job of explaining the various defensive mechanics of the game. Each defensive mechanic is equally important however the tutorial seems to emphasize on parrying as the go to defensive mechanic. Remember to watch a tips and tricks short tutorial to derive maximum value out of the gameplay.Definitely worth the price if you even remotely enjoyed flicks like Oldboy, Enter the Dragon, A Game of Death to name a few. Good OST, great artstyle, goated gameplay.',''),(3041,'Game is very addictive. There is no boring encounter, BUT technical issues are present and ruin the game for me. Very, very bad camera for starts, focus range and no target selection or lock on. I finished the game after I would say 15-20 hours, but I felt disapointed. Game is short and only 5 small levels are not enough. I would recommend the game for 10 bucks. But no more than that.',''),(3042,'very good {im gonna break something}',''),(3043,'---{ Graphics }---☐ You forget what reality is☐ Beautiful☑ Good☐ Decent☐ Bad☐ Don‘t look too long at it☐ MS-DOS---{ Gameplay }---☐ Very good☐ Good☑ A bit too repetitive (It\'s a fighting game what u expect)☐ It\'s just gameplay☐ Mehh☐ Watch paint dry instead☐ Just don\'t---{ Audio }---☐ Eargasm☑ Very good☐ Good☐ Not too bad☐ Bad☐ I\'m now deaf---{ Audience }---☐ Kids☑ Teens☑ Adults☐ Grandma---{ PC Requirements }---☐ Check if you can run paint☐ Potato☑ Decent☐ Fast☐ Rich boi☐ Ask NASA if they have a spare computer---{ Difficulty }---☐ Just press \'W\'☐ Easy☐ Easy to learn / Hard to master☐ Significant brain usage☐ Difficult☑ Dark Souls---{ Grind }---☐ Nothing to grind☐ Only if u care about leaderboards/ranks☐ Isn\'t necessary to progress☑ Average grind level☐ Too much grind☐ You\'ll need a second life for grinding---{ Story }---☐ No Story☐ Some lore☐ Average☑ Good☐ Lovely☐ It\'ll replace your life---{ Game Time }---☐ Long enough for a cu