-only mode and the Ubisoft launcher, there\'s enough said about that, as you can imagine, it is as bad as people say- the game is EMPTY and feels like you\'re playing a demo if you didn\'t get the expansion packs. From what I\'ve seen, as I didn\'t get the standard edition, there is a paywall and I can\'t fathom it. The audacity to charge $60 USD as a full retail price is crazy- the first 2 hours of gameplay feel like slightly more advanced guerilla ops as you have NO gear besides a silenced pistol and whatever you grabbed from the enemies you kill. seriously, the game starts with a 10 minute run and the enemies pose NO threat, because, as I said, the AI is trash. The looter-shooter aspect is warzone-ish in the most horrible way possible. You just run around opening crates with a lot of stopping power, and none of it is great or even good- the lines NPCs repeat over and OVER AND OVER again makes me feel like Ubisoft really made NO progress since the early Assassin\'s Creed titles which is a completely different topic for discussion- the drones. I ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ hate them- special enemies like the heavy are more of a nuisance than a challengethere IS a reason it\'s always on discounti only spent 1,5 odd hours in this game, but it felt like a lifetime, just because it was so damn boringthe game feels cheap and unbelievably generic as if you got a CD copy of some no-name dev\'s debut title for 50% off in the gaming aisle at your local storeUbisoft\'s season pass/DLC BS is pissing me offalso, why should I give the game 3-5 tries until it gets fun?do NOT buy this game for its full priceif you get the game expecting to get a tactical milsim experience, in that regard similar to Arma etc., prepare yourself for the most mediocre game you have experienced in a while, same goes for stealth-action fansalso I never tried co-op, that makes me feel like the only way to really have some fun in this game is to play it with a friend or a groupin conclusion, to be honest, I hated every single moment I spent playing breakpoint, it really crushed my hopes and expectationsthe only positive notes I can really admire is the visuals, the graphics, e.g. the lighting in this game is impressive, but besides that it\'s just an asinine arcadish kind of battle-royalish gameside noteas a fan of Splinter Cell games I feel incredibly underwhelmed by the DLC they provide with the Y1 pass, it\'s NOT funjust please give us the Splinter Cell remake for Christ\'s sake',''),(3143,'Feel like Wildlands was a bit better. Get it when in sale, for sure.....',''),(3144,'An absolute tragedy. The game was fun and I enjoyed it a lot. HOWEVER, after coming back from an extended break, the game will no longer launch under any settings thanks to this ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ UBISOFT connect screen. I can\'t even sign in, since I don\'t have an account. The game is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ gone. I can\'t even launch it. I\'m ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ pissed.',''),(3145,'No one will read this and realize I am a straight white male.',''),(3146,'I have no idea how people paid $60 for this game jesus christ. Gunplay feels OK at best, and everything else is in a menu. Everything you do has to go through a menu I\'m surprised you don\'t need to press yes or no to a \"Are you sure you want to shoot?\" prompt. Feels straight out of 2013 for real Im surprised its 2023 and that it\'s $60. I almost feel ripped off and I bought it for 12 lol.',''),(3147,'Refunded. Cant switch to offline mode. You need to be ONLINE ALL THE TIME to play.',''),(3148,'Two words: Ubisoft Connect. Something I have to fix a problem with literally every time I log in.',''),(3149,'Cannot connect to ubisoft server',''),(3150,'Ghost Recon Breakpoint falls flat with a lackluster storyline and forgettable characters. The open-world design is tedious, offering a lifeless environment filled with repetitive tasks.',''),(3151,'The game in immersive mode is nice, nice gameplay, not much character depth for now, but it\'s a nice game for a while.why the negative? Mandatory external