\'t recommend.A game that actually allows you to play the game you bought? I will recommend.',''),(3155,'Game is not connecting to server since i buy this game',''),(3156,'Just go buy wildlands',''),(3157,'Missions fail out of nowhere, gameplay mechanics are wonky, menus are overflowing with information. First hour is clicking your way through tutorials and listening to mediocre cutscenes. Has lost all of the Ghost Recon charme and is yet another open-world looter shooter.',''),(3158,'The Real Indie GOTY',''),(3159,'horribly robbed by game awards but no matter what you\'ll always be number one to us',''),(3160,'Writing this review after seeing Pizza Tower get screwed out of an award it rightly deserved - this game is probably my singleplayer game of the year for 2023. Tight controls that when learned facilitate some of the most satisfying high-speed movement I have ever experienced in any platformer, levels with satisfying layouts and gimmicks that make coming back to discover every little detail, P-rank them, do it again, and then do it with mods that add even more laps, nothing but fun all the way through. Bosses that\'re fun to fight against and avoid sugarcoating until you can defeat them without taking a single hit; an artstyle that\'s absolute eyecandy to look at, and a soundtrack that must have aimbot since it never misses to match, which provide a steady stream of enjoyment and nostalgia for \'90s and 2000s cartoons and internet animation in tandem with the gameplay. It\'s not often that I call a game outright perfect, and I suppose nothing is perfect, but I\'d say this game\'s extremely close, especially after patches that helped deal with the few rough edges that remained when the game initially launched; this is a game that I can see myself coming back to constantly for years to come, and is a game I can endorse wholeheartedly whether you\'re a casual player looking for a solid platformer to pick up and enjoy at your own pace, or someone that\'s willing to dump hundreds of hours into the game to do insane things some can only dream of. Best Debut Indie, Best Soundtrack, Indie GOTY. 11/10, would type \"pizza\" to get a free pizza again.',''),(3161,'Fat Italian dude goes wroom wroom',''),(3162,'i mean its ok',''),(3163,'good game... I\'m writing this review for the steam awards',''),(3164,'In a year that gave us The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom, Baldur\'s Gate 3, Street Fighter 6, Resident Evil 4 Remake, and Super Mario Bros. Wonder, it is nothing short of flabbergasting that Pizza Tower is EASILY game of the year.',''),(3165,'Genuinely robbed at game awards 2023. I literally had never heard of Coccoon until it won, and no wonder, is has like 2,000 reviews compared to Pizza Tower\'s 44,000 at the time of writing.In any case, if you are reading this, buy this game if you haven\'t. It\'s just good.',''),(3166,'PIZZA TOWER WILL BE AVENGED',''),(3167,'Pizza Tower should have won the indie game awards',''),(3168,'My indie game of the year, this got ROBBED.',''),(3169,'stop looking at reviews and get my favorite indie game of 2023',''),(3170,'Shoulda Won imo',''),(3171,'they should make a not game of the year edition',''),(3172,'Indie Game of the Year 2023',''),(3173,'This is one the best indie games. It\'s up there with Cuphead, Hollow Knight and Celeste. This game shows that you can make a game out of everything. With artstyle made in MS paint this game looks so visually pleasing. Each level is so different from each other with different mechanics in EACH LEVEL. The OST absolutely SLAPS it goes so hard and is one of the best game OSTS. The bosses which i thought where going to be bad due to the game\'s mechanics are actaully really well made. The amount of stuff you can do in this game (even after completing the game) is insane that it feels like DLC. The movement is VERY fast based which makes it hard playing the game for the first time, but eventually you learn how to control it and you get very good with it. T